{"timestamp": "2026-04-22T23:12:06.341070", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "So in order to test autopilot, should I test on both upstream autopilot-selftest and forked autopilot-selftest ?", "session_title": "autopilot-selftest"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-22T23:12:23.191719", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Short answer: only if you want to exercise the fork\u2192upstream PR flow. Otherwise one repo is enough.\n\n- **Upstream-only autopilot-selftest** covers the common path: `issues` trigger \u2192 `run.yml` \u2192 agent runs in Docker \u2192 PR opened back to the same repo. This validates ~90% of the surface (runner dispatch, image pull, constraint check, create-pr composite).\n- **Fork + upstream pair** is only needed to validate the `UPSTREAM_PR_TOKEN` branch in `create-pr` (agent runs on a fork, opens PR to upstream). That code path is genuinely different \u2014 different token, different `gh pr create --repo` target \u2014 so if you ship it as a supported mode, it needs its own selftest.\n\nRecommendation: start with upstream-only; add the fork pair as a second selftest matrix entry once the single-repo path is green. Don't test them as a replacement for each other \u2014 they cover disjoint code paths."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-22T23:13:28.695870", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "Which creds should I add to those repos to test all modes?", "session_title": "autopilot-selftest"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-22T23:13:41.046820", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Based on the autopilot surface, here's the cred matrix by mode:\n\n**Upstream selftest repo (minimum):**\n- `RUNNERS_PAT` \u2014 PAT with `read:org` + `read:user` on the runner-owner account; used by `issue-trigger.yml` to resolve which self-hosted runner label to dispatch to. Required if you trigger via `issues` events.\n- `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` \u2014 only if you want to exercise the **GitHub-hosted runner** path (`runner_label: ubuntu-latest`). Self-hosted runners read creds from `DOCKER_FILES` mounts instead, so skip this if you're only testing self-hosted.\n- `GITHUB_TOKEN` \u2014 auto-provided, don't add manually. Covers same-repo PR creation.\n\n**Fork selftest repo (for fork\u2192upstream mode):**\n- Same `RUNNERS_PAT` / `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` as above.\n- `UPSTREAM_PR_TOKEN` \u2014 PAT with `repo` scope on the **upstream** repo. This is what lets `create-pr` open a PR from fork head into upstream base. Without it, `create-pr` falls back to same-repo (fork\u2192fork) which defeats the point of this selftest.\n\n**Nothing needed on the upstream repo** for the fork\u2192upstream mode \u2014 the PR is opened using `UPSTREAM_PR_TOKEN`'s identity, so the upstream just sees an incoming PR from an authorized user.\n\nGotcha: `UPSTREAM_PR_TOKEN` must be a user/fine-grained PAT, not `GITHUB_TOKEN` \u2014 `GITHUB_TOKEN` is scoped to the repo it runs in and cannot push/PR cross-repo."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-22T23:14:01.165442", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "forget ANTHROPIC_API_KEY - it is not relevant", "session_title": "autopilot-selftest"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-22T23:14:05.717110", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Got it \u2014 dropping `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` from the picture. Revised matrix:\n\n**Upstream selftest repo:**\n- `RUNNERS_PAT` \u2014 for `issue-trigger.yml` to resolve self-hosted runner label.\n- `GITHUB_TOKEN` \u2014 auto-provided, covers same-repo PR creation.\n\n**Fork selftest repo (for fork\u2192upstream mode):**\n- `RUNNERS_PAT` \u2014 same as above.\n- `UPSTREAM_PR_TOKEN` \u2014 PAT with `repo` scope on upstream, so `create-pr` can open fork\u2192upstream PRs. Must be a user/fine-grained PAT, not `GITHUB_TOKEN`.\n\nSelf-hosted runner creds travel via `DOCKER_FILES` mounts on the runner host, not repo secrets."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
