{"timestamp": "2026-04-22T23:14:55.055297", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Added a \"Required secrets\" section to README.md covering both repos and the self-hosted runner note."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-22T23:15:53.950061", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "if I add RUNNERS_PAT - will it affect other users or jusat me?", "session_title": "autopilot-selftest"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-22T23:16:08.425323", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Just you, in terms of identity \u2014 but anyone with write access to the repo can *use* it.\n\n- A PAT acts as **its creator**. When `issue-trigger.yml` calls the GitHub API with `RUNNERS_PAT`, the API sees your account, uses your org/user visibility. Other users don't get the PAT value handed to them \u2014 GitHub masks secrets in logs.\n- But: anyone with **write access** to the repo (or who can merge a PR that touches workflows) can author a workflow step that exfiltrates the secret (e.g. POSTs it somewhere). GitHub has some guardrails (secrets aren't passed to workflows triggered by PRs from forks by default), but inside the repo they're fair game. So \"who can abuse it\" = your repo's write-access set.\n- Blast radius if leaked: whatever the PAT's scopes allow on your account \u2014 for `read:org` + `read:user`, that's read-only visibility into your org memberships and profile. Low-impact but non-zero.\n\nMitigations: use a **fine-grained PAT** scoped to the specific org, with only the needed read permissions and a short expiry. Keep repo write access tight."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-22T23:16:39.919280", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "pat is mine, how do gate it?", "session_title": "autopilot-selftest"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-22T23:16:53.611905", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Use a **fine-grained PAT** (Settings \u2192 Developer settings \u2192 Personal access tokens \u2192 Fine-grained tokens) and narrow every axis:\n\n- **Resource owner**: the specific org/user that owns the runners \u2014 not \"all resources I own\".\n- **Repository access**: \"Public repositories (read-only)\" if runners are in public repos, or select only the repos `issue-trigger.yml` needs to query. Don't pick \"All repositories\".\n- **Permissions**: only what the workflow actually reads. For runner-label lookup that's typically:\n  - Organization \u2192 *Members*: Read\n  - Account \u2192 *Profile*: Read\n  - Nothing else. No `repo`, no `workflow`, no write anywhere.\n- **Expiration**: 30\u201390 days. Rotate on expiry.\n\nOn the repo side:\n- Store as a **repo secret** (or better, an **environment secret** on an environment with required reviewers, so a workflow referencing it pauses for your approval).\n- Lock down write access: only people you trust not to exfiltrate it.\n- In repo Settings \u2192 Actions \u2192 General: set \"Fork pull request workflows from outside collaborators\" to \"Require approval for all outside collaborators\", and disable \"Send write tokens/secrets to workflows from forks\".\n- Turn on branch protection for `main` / any branch that workflows run from on push, so no one can land a secret-stealing workflow unreviewed.\n\nIf you want the hardest gate: put `RUNNERS_PAT` in a GitHub **Environment** with you as a required reviewer. Every run that references it will block until you click approve \u2014 annoying, but it means nothing uses the PAT without your explicit say-so."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
