{"timestamp": "2026-04-22T23:18:06.727821", "event": "Edit", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "PreToolUse", "tool_name": "Edit", "tool_input": {"file_path": "/workspace/README.md", "old_string": "### Self-hosted runner", "new_string": "### Gating `RUNNERS_PAT`\n\nThe PAT acts as its creator. Anyone with write access to the repo can author a workflow that exfiltrates it, so narrow it:\n\n- Use a **fine-grained PAT**, not classic.\n- Resource owner: the specific org/user; repository access: only the repos `issue-trigger.yml` queries.\n- Permissions: Organization *Members* \u2014 Read; Account *Profile* \u2014 Read. Nothing else.\n- Expiration: 30\u201390 days; rotate on expiry.\n- Store as an **environment secret** on an environment with yourself as a required reviewer \u2014 every run that uses it pauses for approval.\n- Repo Settings \u2192 Actions \u2192 General: require approval for outside-collaborator fork PRs; don't send secrets to fork workflows.\n- Branch-protect any branch workflows run from on push.\n\n### Self-hosted runner", "replace_all": false}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_01PD1zBZ5kd1EdbFg2J2iF7S"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-22T23:18:06.944348", "event": "Edit", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "PostToolUse", "tool_name": "Edit", "tool_input": {"file_path": "/workspace/README.md", "old_string": "### Self-hosted runner", "new_string": "### Gating `RUNNERS_PAT`\n\nThe PAT acts as its creator. Anyone with write access to the repo can author a workflow that exfiltrates it, so narrow it:\n\n- Use a **fine-grained PAT**, not classic.\n- Resource owner: the specific org/user; repository access: only the repos `issue-trigger.yml` queries.\n- Permissions: Organization *Members* \u2014 Read; Account *Profile* \u2014 Read. Nothing else.\n- Expiration: 30\u201390 days; rotate on expiry.\n- Store as an **environment secret** on an environment with yourself as a required reviewer \u2014 every run that uses it pauses for approval.\n- Repo Settings \u2192 Actions \u2192 General: require approval for outside-collaborator fork PRs; don't send secrets to fork workflows.\n- Branch-protect any branch workflows run from on push.\n\n### Self-hosted runner", "replace_all": false}, "tool_response": {"filePath": "/workspace/README.md", "oldString": "### Self-hosted runner", "newString": "### Gating `RUNNERS_PAT`\n\nThe PAT acts as its creator. Anyone with write access to the repo can author a workflow that exfiltrates it, so narrow it:\n\n- Use a **fine-grained PAT**, not classic.\n- Resource owner: the specific org/user; repository access: only the repos `issue-trigger.yml` queries.\n- Permissions: Organization *Members* \u2014 Read; Account *Profile* \u2014 Read. Nothing else.\n- Expiration: 30\u201390 days; rotate on expiry.\n- Store as an **environment secret** on an environment with yourself as a required reviewer \u2014 every run that uses it pauses for approval.\n- Repo Settings \u2192 Actions \u2192 General: require approval for outside-collaborator fork PRs; don't send secrets to fork workflows.\n- Branch-protect any branch workflows run from on push.\n\n### Self-hosted runner", "originalFile": "# autopilot-selftest\n\nSelftest repo for [Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot](https://github.com/Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot). Exercises the reusable workflow end-to-end against a real GitHub repo.\n\n## Test modes\n\n| Mode | Repo setup | Covers |\n|---|---|---|\n| Same-repo | This repo alone | `issues` trigger \u2192 `run.yml` \u2192 agent \u2192 PR back to this repo |\n| Fork\u2192upstream | This repo + a fork | `create-pr` opening a PR from fork head into upstream base |\n\nRun each mode independently \u2014 they cover disjoint code paths in `create-pr`.\n\n## Required secrets\n\n### Upstream selftest repo\n\n- `RUNNERS_PAT` \u2014 PAT with `read:org` + `read:user` on the runner-owner account. Used by `issue-trigger.yml` to resolve the self-hosted runner label.\n\n### Fork selftest repo (fork\u2192upstream mode only)\n\n- `RUNNERS_PAT` \u2014 same as above.\n- `UPSTREAM_PR_TOKEN` \u2014 user / fine-grained PAT with `repo` scope on the upstream repo. Required for `create-pr` to open a PR from fork head into upstream base. Cannot be the default workflow token \u2014 that one is scoped to the repo it runs in and cannot PR cross-repo.\n\n### Self-hosted runner\n\nCredentials consumed by the agent inside Docker (e.g. Anthropic API key) travel via `DOCKER_FILES` mounts on the runner host, **not** as repo secrets.\n", "structuredPatch": [{"oldStart": 22, "oldLines": 6, "newStart": 22, "newLines": 18, "lines": [" - `RUNNERS_PAT` \u2014 same as above.", " - `UPSTREAM_PR_TOKEN` \u2014 user / fine-grained PAT with `repo` scope on the upstream repo. Required for `create-pr` to open a PR from fork head into upstream base. Cannot be the default workflow token \u2014 that one is scoped to the repo it runs in and cannot PR cross-repo.", " ", "+### Gating `RUNNERS_PAT`", "+", "+The PAT acts as its creator. Anyone with write access to the repo can author a workflow that exfiltrates it, so narrow it:", "+", "+- Use a **fine-grained PAT**, not classic.", "+- Resource owner: the specific org/user; repository access: only the repos `issue-trigger.yml` queries.", "+- Permissions: Organization *Members* \u2014 Read; Account *Profile* \u2014 Read. Nothing else.", "+- Expiration: 30\u201390 days; rotate on expiry.", "+- Store as an **environment secret** on an environment with yourself as a required reviewer \u2014 every run that uses it pauses for approval.", "+- Repo Settings \u2192 Actions \u2192 General: require approval for outside-collaborator fork PRs; don't send secrets to fork workflows.", "+- Branch-protect any branch workflows run from on push.", "+", " ### Self-hosted runner", " ", " Credentials consumed by the agent inside Docker (e.g. Anthropic API key) travel via `DOCKER_FILES` mounts on the runner host, **not** as repo secrets."]}], "userModified": false, "replaceAll": false}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_01PD1zBZ5kd1EdbFg2J2iF7S"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-22T23:18:09.084091", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Added a \"Gating `RUNNERS_PAT`\" subsection to README.md before the self-hosted runner note."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-22T23:19:01.177804", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "after adding this as noted, what other can do / use it?", "session_title": "autopilot-selftest"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-22T23:19:18.733244", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "With the gating in place, here's what remains possible:\n\n**Repo collaborators with write access:**\n- Can queue workflow runs that reference `RUNNERS_PAT` \u2014 but every run **pauses at the environment gate until you approve**. They can't use it without you clicking approve.\n- Can open issues / push commits / modify workflows, which may queue more pending-approval runs. Annoyance, not risk.\n- If you approve a run, the workflow can exercise the PAT's capabilities for that run only: list org members, read profile. Nothing else, because the PAT is fine-grained.\n\n**Outside contributors (fork PRs):**\n- Zero secret access. GitHub blocks secrets from fork-triggered workflows, and your \"don't send secrets to fork workflows\" setting double-confirms it. They can open PRs that run CI without secrets, nothing more.\n\n**Worst case if someone exfiltrates the PAT** (e.g. you approve a malicious run without reading the diff):\n- Enumerate members of the one org the PAT is scoped to.\n- Read public profile fields of your account.\n- Cannot push, cannot read private repos, cannot modify anything, cannot access other orgs \u2014 the fine-grained scope prevents it.\n- Expires in 30\u201390 days regardless.\n\nNet: the only thing \"others\" can do is **request** a run that uses the PAT. You're the sole decider on whether it executes, and the damage ceiling even on misuse is org-membership enumeration."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-22T23:20:03.244675", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "so if other member add the same PAT, will it interfere with mine?", "session_title": "autopilot-selftest"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-22T23:20:13.272836", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "No \u2014 they're separate values in separate scopes, and GitHub has no concept of \"the `RUNNERS_PAT` secret\" as a shared global.\n\n- A repo/environment secret named `RUNNERS_PAT` is just a named slot holding a string. If another member adds one in **a different repo** (or a different environment), it's a different secret, independent from yours.\n- If they overwrite `RUNNERS_PAT` in the **same repo/environment** you configured, they replace your value \u2014 workflows then run under their PAT's identity, not yours. Not \"interference\" in the sense of collision; it's a straight overwrite. You'd see it in the secret's \"Last updated\" timestamp.\n- Only users with **admin** on the repo (or on the environment) can add/update/read-name secrets. Write-access alone isn't enough. So gate this by keeping the repo's admin list to yourself.\n- Environment-scoped secrets have their own access list \u2014 an environment with you as sole reviewer and admin means no one else can overwrite the secret there even if they're a repo admin elsewhere.\n\nSo: two people can't have \"competing\" `RUNNERS_PAT` values active at the same time in the same scope. Either it's yours, or someone with admin replaced it. Lock repo/environment admin to prevent the replace case."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
