{"timestamp": "2026-04-22T23:21:27.357239", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "```\nBootstrap autopilot-selftest\n\nWire up the selftest repo against Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot: caller\nworkflows (agent, issue-trigger, check-constraints), autopilot submodule,\nand an initial selftest spec. README documents test modes (same-repo\nand fork->upstream), required secrets, and RUNNERS_PAT gating.\n```"}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-22T23:22:59.833459", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "After I add these secrets, how exactly we can trigger workflows from cmdline", "session_title": "autopilot-selftest"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-22T23:23:16.725782", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Two trigger paths from the CLI, matching the two workflows:\n\n**1. Direct dispatch (`workflow_dispatch`, agent.yml)** \u2014 you pick the issue and runner yourself:\n\n```bash\ngh workflow run agent.yml \\\n  -R <owner>/autopilot-selftest \\\n  -f runner_label=<your-github-username> \\\n  -f issue_number=<NNN>\n```\n\nThen watch the run:\n```bash\ngh run watch -R <owner>/autopilot-selftest\n# or list\ngh run list -R <owner>/autopilot-selftest --workflow=agent.yml\n```\n\n**2. Issue-triggered path (`issue-trigger.yml` \u2192 `agent.yml`)** \u2014 simulates the real marketplace UX. Create or label an issue; the trigger workflow dispatches `agent.yml` for you:\n\n```bash\n# open a fresh issue (triggers on: opened)\ngh issue create -R <owner>/autopilot-selftest \\\n  --title \"selftest: <what>\" \\\n  --body \"$(cat <<'EOF'\nmerge_into_upstream: false\ntimeout_mins: 10\nmodel: claude-haiku-4-5\n---\n<task body>\nEOF\n)\"\n\n# or label an existing one (triggers on: labeled)\ngh issue edit <NNN> -R <owner>/autopilot-selftest --add-label agent\n```\n\nRequires `RUNNERS_PAT` to be set, since `issue-trigger.yml` uses it to resolve the runner label from the sender's GitHub username.\n\n**Fork\u2192upstream mode** \u2014 run the dispatch against the *fork* repo (`-R <you>/autopilot-selftest-fork`), with `UPSTREAM_PR_TOKEN` set there. The agent opens the PR back to the upstream repo using that token.\n\nQuick view of the in-flight run's logs:\n```bash\ngh run view --log -R <owner>/autopilot-selftest $(gh run list -R <owner>/autopilot-selftest -L1 --json databaseId -q '.[0].databaseId')\n```"}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
