{"timestamp": "2026-04-22T23:35:01.547222", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "A few layers of \"automatic,\" smallest to biggest:\n\n**1. Static lint on the workflow YAML** \u2014 catches typos, missing inputs, bad expressions before any dispatch:\n```yaml\n# .github/workflows/lint.yml\non: [push, pull_request]\njobs:\n  actionlint:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - uses: raven-actions/actionlint@v2\n```\nCheap, runs on every push, no secrets needed.\n\n**2. Scheduled selftest run** \u2014 dispatch `agent.yml` against a pinned canary issue on a cron, assert the run succeeded:\n```yaml\n# .github/workflows/nightly-selftest.yml\non:\n  schedule: [{cron: '0 6 * * *'}]\n  workflow_dispatch:\njobs:\n  smoke:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - name: Dispatch and wait\n        env: { GH_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.SELFTEST_DISPATCH_PAT }} }\n        run: |\n          gh workflow run agent.yml -R ${{ github.repository }} \\\n            -f runner_label=yaroslav -f issue_number=1\n          sleep 10\n          rid=$(gh run list -R ${{ github.repository }} --workflow=agent.yml -L1 --json databaseId -q '.[0].databaseId')\n          gh run watch $rid -R ${{ github.repository }} --exit-status\n```\n`SELFTEST_DISPATCH_PAT` just needs `workflow` scope on this repo. `--exit-status` fails the job if the dispatched run fails, so a red X on the cron job = autopilot regression.\n\n**3. Post-run assertions** \u2014 after the dispatched run completes, verify side effects (a PR was opened, spec-checks.k.json was updated, constraint count matches). Add a step in the smoke job:\n```yaml\n- name: Assert PR opened\n  run: |\n    pr=$(gh pr list -R ${{ github.repository }} --search \"issue-1 in:title\" --json number -q '.[0].number')\n    [ -n \"$pr\" ] || { echo \"no PR opened for canary issue\"; exit 1; }\n    gh pr close $pr --delete-branch -R ${{ github.repository }}\n```\n\n**4. PR-triggered canary against in-flight autopilot** \u2014 for testing autopilot PRs. When a PR is opened against autopilot, flip `@main` to `@<pr-branch>` in this repo on a test branch, dispatch, assert, flip back. The README note already hints at this manual loop; automating it needs a small workflow in *autopilot* that calls back into this repo via `repository_dispatch`:\n```bash\ngh api repos/<you>/autopilot-selftest/dispatches \\\n  -f event_type=autopilot-pr-smoke \\\n  -f 'client_payload[ref]=pr-branch-name'\n```\nThen `on: repository_dispatch: types: [autopilot-pr-smoke]` here swaps the ref and runs the smoke job.\n\nRecommendation in order of effort:\n1. Add actionlint today \u2014 3 lines, catches everything static.\n2. Add nightly smoke job once you have one canary issue that's idempotent (agent can run it repeatedly and produce a PR each time, which the assertion step closes).\n3. Add PR-triggered canary only when autopilot itself starts getting PRs worth smoke-testing.\n\nThe smoke job is the real \"automatic check\" \u2014 it verifies end-to-end that dispatch works, the runner picks up, the agent runs, and a PR lands. Everything else is supporting infrastructure."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
