{"timestamp": "2026-04-22T23:39:33.606941", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Created:\n- `scripts/selftest.sh` \u2014 dispatches `agent.yml` against upstream or fork, watches the run to completion, asserts the PR landed in the expected repo (and, for fork mode, that the PR head actually points at the fork \u2014 catches silent fallback to same-repo PRs).\n- `scripts/selftest-all.sh` \u2014 runs both modes sequentially.\n\nConfig via env vars at top of `selftest.sh`: `UPSTREAM`, `FORK`, `RUNNER` \u2014 edit the defaults to your actual `owner/repo` and runner-label values.\n\nUsage:\n```\nscripts/selftest.sh upstream        # or: upstream 7  to use issue #7\nscripts/selftest.sh fork\nscripts/selftest-all.sh\n```\n\nNote: `chmod +x` was blocked by the sandbox \u2014 run `chmod +x scripts/selftest.sh scripts/selftest-all.sh` yourself, or invoke with `bash scripts/selftest.sh ...`."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
