{"timestamp": "2026-04-23T00:04:14.214984", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "I  see it looks like usually, different from waht I saw in rslite. But I wonder if those ugly jobs names can be shrinked to just last name?", "session_title": "autopilot-selftest"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-23T00:04:36.011290", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "No \u2014 GitHub Actions has no setting to show only the leaf. The `outer / inner / leaf` path is how the UI represents reusable-workflow nesting, and it's baked in. There's a long-standing feature request for it (search \"reusable workflow job name\" on the actions/runner and community forums); still not landed as of now.\n\nWhat you *can* control:\n\n- **Shorten each segment.** Rename `jobs.<id>` in each callee, or set `jobs.<id>.name: \"...\"` to override the display. `name:` overrides the segment but doesn't remove it. So `delegate / image-digest / fetch-manifest` with `name: fetch` on the leaf becomes `delegate / image-digest / fetch` \u2014 still three segments, each shorter.\n- **Reduce segment count.** Every `uses:` adds a segment. Collapse nested reusable workflows into inline jobs (or merge sibling jobs into steps, as discussed for `image-digest.yml`). This is the only way to actually get closer to a leaf-only display.\n- **Name the caller job empty-ish.** The top segment is the caller's `jobs.<id>`. If you rename `delegate` to `d` or `_`, the path shortens visually \u2014 not great for readability of your own YAML, but it does compress the UI.\n\nThe combination that gets closest to \"just the leaf\":\n1. Collapse `image-digest.yml` to one job (kills the `fetch-manifest` / `parse-digest` split).\n2. Inline single-job reusable workflows into the parent workflow instead of `uses:`'ing them, when they're not reused elsewhere.\n3. Use `name:` on each remaining job to give it a concise display.\n\nYou'll still see at least two segments for any cross-repo `uses:` chain \u2014 that boundary is what the path represents. Accepting one level of nesting (`delegate / digest`) is usually the practical floor; zero segments isn't reachable without eliminating reusable workflows entirely."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-23T00:04:56.687298", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "so setting display name is possible?", "session_title": "autopilot-selftest"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-23T00:05:10.418162", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Yes. Two places you can set it, both using `name:`:\n\n**1. On the job inside the callee workflow** (the reusable one):\n```yaml\n# autopilot/.github/workflows/image-digest.yml\njobs:\n  fetch-manifest:\n    name: fetch          # overrides the segment shown in callers\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    ...\n  parse-digest:\n    name: parse\n    ...\n```\nEffect in the caller: `delegate / image-digest / fetch-manifest` \u2192 `delegate / image-digest / fetch`.\n\n**2. On the caller job that invokes the reusable workflow:**\n```yaml\n# autopilot-selftest/.github/workflows/issue-trigger.yml\njobs:\n  delegate:\n    name: trigger        # overrides the outermost segment\n    uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/workflows/issue-trigger.yml@main\n    ...\n```\nEffect: `delegate / image-digest / fetch` \u2192 `trigger / image-digest / fetch`.\n\nNotes:\n\n- `name:` changes **display only**. The job id (`delegate`, `fetch-manifest`) still exists and is what `needs:`, `jobs.<id>.outputs`, and API queries use. You don't break anything by renaming.\n- The **middle segment** (`image-digest`) comes from `jobs.<id>` in the *parent* of the callee \u2014 i.e. the job in the callee's caller that has `uses: ...image-digest.yml`. To rename it, set `name:` on that job, wherever it's defined (in autopilot's `check-constraints.yml` or `issue-trigger.yml`, there's a job like `image-digest: uses: ./.github/workflows/image-digest.yml` \u2014 add `name:` there).\n- `name:` accepts expressions, so you can make it dynamic: `name: \"digest (${{ inputs.image_repo }})\"`.\n- It does **not** affect log file names in `gh run view --log` \u2014 those still use the id-path.\n- It does **not** collapse segments. Three segments stay three, just with prettier labels. To reduce count, you still need to merge jobs or inline workflows.\n\nSo: rename per segment for cosmetics, merge jobs for structural shortening. Both are orthogonal."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
