{"timestamp": "2026-04-23T00:10:28.412779", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Mapping the three segments in `delegate / image-digest / fetch-manifest` to who owns each:\n\n| Segment | Owned by | Why |\n|---|---|---|\n| `delegate` | **autopilot-selftest** | It's the top-level `jobs.delegate` in this repo's `.github/workflows/check-constraints.yml` (line 13). Rename or `name:` here. |\n| `image-digest` | **autopilot** | It's the `jobs.image-digest` in autopilot's `.github/workflows/check-constraints.yml` (the job whose body is `uses: ./.github/workflows/image-digest.yml`). Rename or `name:` in autopilot. |\n| `fetch-manifest` | **autopilot** | It's `jobs.fetch-manifest` inside autopilot's `.github/workflows/image-digest.yml`. Rename or `name:` in autopilot. |\n\nRule of thumb: **the job at depth N is defined in the workflow file at depth N**. Depth 0 = the caller (selftest). Depth 1+ = the reusable workflows (autopilot) being called, one step deeper per `uses:`.\n\nSo to clean up that specific path:\n- Change `delegate` \u2192 in selftest.\n- Change `image-digest` and `fetch-manifest` (and already-done `parse-digest`, `check-constraints`) \u2192 in autopilot, which is what we just did. Those changes take effect once pushed to `Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot@main`, since the selftest calls `@main`.\n\nThe selftest's local submodule copy doesn't affect CI \u2014 GitHub resolves `uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/...@main` from the remote repo, not from the submodule here."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
