{"timestamp": "2026-04-23T00:12:47.880520", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "not sure you get it. Names I hate is long and I need to latest part (after / )m for them: delegate / image-digest / fetch-manifest, delegate / image-digest / parse-digest, delegate / check-constraints. Is this clear?", "session_title": "autopilot-selftest"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-23T00:13:19.708471", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Clear \u2014 and I need to be direct: **GitHub Actions does not support displaying only the leaf segment**. The `a / b / c` path is how the UI renders reusable-workflow nesting, and there is no setting, `name:` trick, or workflow syntax that collapses it to just `c`. I was describing this earlier; \"rename per segment\" is the most you can do, not \"hide segments.\"\n\nYour three current paths decompose as:\n\n| Path | Structural reason |\n|---|---|\n| `delegate / image-digest / fetch-manifest` | selftest caller \u2192 autopilot/check-constraints.yml's `image-digest` job \u2192 autopilot/image-digest.yml's `fetch-manifest` job |\n| `delegate / image-digest / parse-digest` | same, different leaf |\n| `delegate / check-constraints` | selftest caller \u2192 autopilot/check-constraints.yml's `check-constraints` job |\n\nTo actually reach a display of just `fetch-manifest`, `parse-digest`, `check-constraints`, the structural nesting has to go. Two realistic options:\n\n**Option A \u2014 Accept two segments, not one.** The selftest caller job is unavoidable (that's what makes this a caller). The deepest option without giving up reusable workflows: merge `image-digest.yml` into `check-constraints.yml` so `fetch-manifest` and `parse-digest` become direct jobs of the constraints workflow. Paths become:\n- `delegate / fetch-manifest`\n- `delegate / parse-digest`\n- `delegate / check-constraints`\n\nRename `delegate` \u2192 `run` (or drop it \u2014 you can set `jobs.run.name: \"\"` gets ignored, but a one-char id like `_` at least minimizes it). Best you can reasonably get: `run / fetch-manifest`, `run / parse-digest`, `run / check-constraints`. Two segments, and the second one is what you wanted.\n\n**Option B \u2014 Give up the reusable workflow entirely.** Inline the whole constraint-check logic into `autopilot-selftest/.github/workflows/check-constraints.yml` as plain jobs. Then the UI shows just `fetch-manifest`, `parse-digest`, `check-constraints`. Cost: you lose the library boundary \u2014 every consumer repo duplicates the logic, defeating the point of autopilot being a marketplace workflow.\n\nThere is no option C. If you want one-segment display, it's Option B. If you want to keep the library, Option A is the floor.\n\nWhich do you want?"}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
