{"timestamp": "2026-04-23T00:17:57.890144", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Reusable workflows in play for autopilot-selftest, enumerated by `on: workflow_call` files and where they're called from:\n\n**In `Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot`** (all public, all reusable):\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/workflows/issue-trigger.yml` | Reacts to issue events forwarded by caller; resolves runner, dispatches the agent workflow |\n| `Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/workflows/coding-agent.yml` | Main pipeline: fetch/parse issue, validate runner, run agent in Docker, open PR |\n| `Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/workflows/check-constraints.yml` | Runs `check_spec_constraints.py` against the caller's checked-out tree |\n| `Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/workflows/image-digest.yml` | Resolves the `ghcr.io/clockwork-pilot/autopilot-ws:latest` manifest to a pinned `@sha256:` ref |\n| `Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/workflows/act-step-runner.yml` | Runs a single step via `act` for local/CI testing (not consumed by selftest) |\n\n**In `Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot-selftest`** (this repo, consumers \u2014 *not* reusable, they have real triggers):\n\n| File | Trigger | Calls |\n|---|---|---|\n| `.github/workflows/agent.yml` | `workflow_dispatch` | `Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/workflows/coding-agent.yml@main` |\n| `.github/workflows/issue-trigger.yml` | `on: issues` | `Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/workflows/issue-trigger.yml@main` |\n| `.github/workflows/check-constraints.yml` | `on: push` / `pull_request` | `Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/workflows/check-constraints.yml@main` |\n\n**Cross-calls inside `Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot`** (same repo, local `./` refs \u2014 these are what add a middle segment to the path):\n\n- `Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/workflows/check-constraints.yml` \u2192 `uses: ./.github/workflows/image-digest.yml`\n- `Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/workflows/coding-agent.yml` \u2192 `uses: ./.github/workflows/image-digest.yml`\n\nSo for a selftest constraints run, the nesting chain is:\n\n```\nClockwork-Pilot/autopilot-selftest/.github/workflows/check-constraints.yml  (caller)\n  \u2514\u2500 Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/workflows/check-constraints.yml      (reusable)\n       \u2514\u2500 Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/workflows/image-digest.yml      (reusable, called locally)\n```\n\nThat's why the UI shows three segments \u2014 one per file in the chain."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
