{"timestamp": "2026-04-23T13:55:42.044068", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "choose-branch, parse-digest, parse-issue", "session_title": "autopilot-selftest"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-23T13:57:04.815291", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Before I cut code: there's a complication I want to surface. The three jobs you named \u2014 `parse-issue`, `choose-branch`, `parse-digest` \u2014 are **already covered by step-output tests in autopilot's own spec.k.json** (features/step_output_checks: `parse_issue_cases`, `choose_branch_cases`, `parse_digest_cases`). They work today by calling `run-act-step-checks.sh <workflow> <job-id>` against fixtures.\n\nThis changes \"list outdated\" from a vague question to a concrete one: **the three existing constraints in autopilot's spec will be outdated** once their job ids stop existing at the original workflow paths. And because those constraints are verified (`fails_count > 0`), their `cmd` field is **locked** per the constraint-protection rules \u2014 I can't edit them in place. They have to be deleted and replaced.\n\nPlan I'm proposing, all inside **autopilot** (this is an autopilot-side refactor; autopilot-selftest is a consumer and isn't affected):\n\n1. **Create three composite actions** with the same input/output contracts as the existing jobs:\n   - `autopilot/.github/actions/parse-issue/action.yml`\n   - `autopilot/.github/actions/choose-branch/action.yml`\n   - `autopilot/.github/actions/parse-digest/action.yml`\n2. **Rewrite the original jobs** in `coding-agent.yml` and `image-digest.yml` to call the composite actions via `uses: ./.github/actions/<name>` at step level, preserving workflow-level outputs for runtime consumers.\n3. **Add test wrapper jobs** in `act-step-runner.yml` \u2014 one per composite action, job ids `parse-issue`, `choose-branch`, `parse-digest` \u2014 so fixtures don't need to move and the test harness keeps working.\n4. **Add new constraints** in autopilot/spec.k.json pointing the test script at `act-step-runner.yml`:\n   - `parse_issue_via_action`\n   - `choose_branch_via_action`\n   - `parse_digest_via_action`\n   - Plus structural constraints: each `.github/actions/<name>/action.yml` exists.\n5. Run `check_spec_constraints.py`. Confirm the new ones fail (zero-state), implement until they pass.\n6. **List outdated**: the three original `*_cases` constraints target workflow/job pairs that will no longer exist at the original path if step 2 collapses the jobs to pure wrappers. Those become the \"outdated\" list to report.\n\nThree points of confirmation I need from you:\n\n**a.** Scope is autopilot-side, not autopilot-selftest \u2014 correct? (autopilot-selftest's spec has `selftest_shape`; none of its constraints reference these jobs, so nothing there goes outdated.)\n\n**b.** The original jobs in `coding-agent.yml` / `image-digest.yml` should **remain** (as thin wrappers calling the composite action) so runtime callers still see workflow-level outputs \u2014 or do you want them deleted entirely? If deleted, every downstream `needs.parse-issue.outputs.*` reference in `coding-agent.yml` breaks. Keeping thin wrappers is the backward-compatible move.\n\n**c.** Fixtures at `.github/scripts/test/fixtures/parse-issue/*` etc. stay where they are; the test script is re-pointed to `act-step-runner.yml`. Agree?\n\nSay \"yes, proceed with a/b/c as described\" and I'll execute in one pass."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
