{"timestamp": "2026-04-23T14:14:18.611254", "event": "Stop", "status": "blocked", "reason": "Constraint checks failed", "recurring_failures": [], "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace/autopilot", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": true, "last_assistant_message": "On the immediate constraint: moving past the `GITHUB_WORKSPACE` issue, it now fails because `docker` isn't installed in this sandbox. That's a real environmental limitation \u2014 the constraint asserts autopilot's docker-based runtime works, which it does in CI but not here. Unless this sandbox is expected to have docker, this constraint will stay red locally regardless of how the script is fixed.\n\n**On your question \u2014 the streamlined method after the refactor:**\n\nBefore (per-workflow, varied file names):\n```bash\nbash .github/scripts/test/run-act-step-checks.sh coding-agent.yml parse-issue\nbash .github/scripts/test/run-act-step-checks.sh coding-agent.yml choose-branch\nbash .github/scripts/test/run-act-step-checks.sh image-digest.yml parse-digest\n```\n\nAfter (single workflow file, one entry point):\n```bash\nbash .github/scripts/test/run-act-step-checks.sh act-step-runner.yml <step>\n```\n\nWhere `<step>` is `parse-issue` / `choose-branch` / `parse-digest` \u2014 same step ids, fixtures unchanged. The first arg is now always `act-step-runner.yml`, because every composite-action test wrapper lives there.\n\nWhy this is streamlined:\n\n- **Single target file.** Adding a new composite action means one new wrapper job in `act-step-runner.yml` + a fixtures dir. No new workflow file per action.\n- **Discoverable.** One place to grep for \"what step outputs can I test?\" \u2014 `yq '.jobs | keys' act-step-runner.yml`.\n- **The spec reflects it.** The three new constraints in autopilot/spec.k.json all point at `act-step-runner.yml`:\n  ```\n  bash .github/scripts/test/run-act-step-checks.sh act-step-runner.yml parse-issue\n  bash .github/scripts/test/run-act-step-checks.sh act-step-runner.yml choose-branch\n  bash .github/scripts/test/run-act-step-checks.sh act-step-runner.yml parse-digest\n  ```\n\nOne-liner to run the whole step-output suite:\n```bash\nfor s in parse-issue choose-branch parse-digest; do\n  bash .github/scripts/test/run-act-step-checks.sh act-step-runner.yml \"$s\"\ndone\n```\n\nIf you want it even more streamlined \u2014 \"run all wrappers without naming them\" \u2014 that's a small script change: iterate over job ids in `act-step-runner.yml` that have a matching fixtures dir. Let me know if you want me to add that as a `--all` flag to `run-act-step-checks.sh`.\n\n**For the full constraint suite** (not just step outputs), the streamlined entrypoint is still the one from CI:\n```bash\ncd autopilot && bash .github/scripts/run-in-docker-no-claude.sh check_spec_constraints.py\n```\nRequires docker + the autopilot-ws image. This is what the failing selftest constraint invokes."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
