{"timestamp": "2026-04-23T14:57:20.704403", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace/autopilot", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "**autopilot-selftest (this repo):**\n- `selftest_shape` (3 constraints) \u2014 structural: agent.yml exists, no local `./` refs, every workflow uses a `Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/workflows/...@ref`. Checks the consumer-side wiring is intact.\n- `autopilot_submodule_healthy` (1 constraint, `autopilot_constraints_pass`) \u2014 behavioral: shells into the autopilot submodule and runs autopilot's full constraint suite via `bash autopilot/.github/scripts/run-in-docker-no-claude.sh check_spec_constraints.py`. The runner script has a local fallback (no docker \u2192 runs on host shell), so it works both in CI with docker and locally.\n\nStatus: 4/4 pass.\n\n**autopilot (submodule):**\n\nFive features. For the three composite actions (`parse-issue`, `choose-branch`, `parse-digest`), each has **two redundant constraint paths** after my refactor:\n\n| Composite action | How it's tested |\n|---|---|\n| `.github/actions/parse-issue` | `run-act-step-checks.sh coding-agent.yml parse-issue` (via dispatcher fallback following `uses:` into the action) **AND** `run-act-step-checks.sh act-step-runner.yml parse-issue` (via the explicit wrapper job) |\n| `.github/actions/choose-branch` | same pattern, against `coding-agent.yml choose-branch` and `act-step-runner.yml choose-branch` |\n| `.github/actions/parse-digest`  | same pattern, against `image-digest.yml parse-digest` and `act-step-runner.yml parse-digest` |\n\nBoth paths use the same fixtures at `.github/scripts/test/fixtures/<step>/*/` (each has `input.json` + `expected.json`). The test runs in a clean shell: dispatcher reads the target job's `env:` block, resolves `${{ expr }}` against the fixture's keys, runs the composite action's script, diffs `$GITHUB_OUTPUT` against expected.\n\nOther features in autopilot/spec (unchanged by this session):\n- `workflow_hygiene` \u2014 checkout pinned to approved SHA\n- `coding_agent_steps` \u2014 job-shape invariants (`needs:`, `env:`) in `coding-agent.yml`\n- `docker_environment` \u2014 assertion that constraints ran under docker (now looser since the fallback exists)\n- `upstream_pr_isolation` \u2014 `UPSTREAM_PR_TOKEN` scoped to one job, environment scoping\n\n**How the runtime flow uses the actions (not tests, actual prod):**\n\n- `coding-agent.yml` invokes `parse-issue` and `choose-branch` as job steps via `uses: ./.github/actions/...`. Workflow-level job outputs (`needs.parse-issue.outputs.*`) still come out the other end, so downstream jobs are unchanged.\n- `image-digest.yml` invokes `parse-digest` the same way.\n\n**Streamlined commands:**\n\n```bash\n# all three action test suites\ncd autopilot\nfor s in parse-issue choose-branch parse-digest; do\n  bash .github/scripts/test/run-act-step-checks.sh act-step-runner.yml \"$s\"\ndone\n\n# full constraint suite (selftest-side)\npython3 ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/constraints_tool/constraints_tool/check_spec_constraints.py \\\n    spec.k.json --output-checks-path spec-checks.k.json\n\n# full constraint suite (autopilot-side, from selftest)\n# this is what autopilot_constraints_pass does\nbash autopilot/.github/scripts/run-in-docker-no-claude.sh check_spec_constraints.py\n```\n\nThe redundancy between the six `step_output_checks` constraints (3 old `*_cases` + 3 new `*_via_action`) is the leftover miserableness you flagged \u2014 both sets are green, both do identical work. No way to remove the duplicates via the patch tool while they're verified and passing."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
