{"timestamp": "2026-04-23T15:24:54.848719", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace/autopilot", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Yes, pairwise duplicates. Each `*_cases` and its `*_via_action` twin runs the same fixtures, same script, same expected outputs \u2014 just entered through a different workflow file:\n\n| Pair | Both reach |\n|---|---|\n| `parse_issue_cases` / `parse_issue_via_action` | `.github/actions/parse-issue/script.sh` with the parse-issue fixtures |\n| `choose_branch_cases` / `choose_branch_via_action` | `.github/actions/choose-branch/script.sh` with the choose-branch fixtures |\n| `parse_digest_cases` / `parse_digest_via_action` | `.github/actions/parse-digest/script.sh` with the parse-digest fixtures |\n\nThe only difference is the first arg to `run-act-step-checks.sh`:\n- `*_cases` \u2014 targets the production workflow (`coding-agent.yml`, `image-digest.yml`) and relies on the dispatcher's `uses:` fallback to reach the action's script\n- `*_via_action` \u2014 targets `act-step-runner.yml` and reaches the same script via the explicit wrapper job\n\nBoth exit 0 in exactly the same set of conditions. If the script breaks, both fail together; if the fixtures change, both update together. Keeping both just means every fixture run costs 2\u00d7 the CI time. The `*_via_action` trio is the redundant one I added \u2014 the `*_cases` trio has seniority and gets the canonical slot."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
