{"timestamp": "2026-04-23T15:26:54.875474", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace/autopilot", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "`*_cases` \u2014 they've been in the spec since before the refactor, the description (`\"Adding a case is a folder drop \u2014 no spec edit needed\"`) still accurately describes the usage, and they target the production workflow files directly, which makes them drift-sensitive: if someone renames the `parse-issue` job in `coding-agent.yml`, `parse_issue_cases` fails. `parse_issue_via_action` wouldn't catch it because it pins to `act-step-runner.yml`.\n\nThe `*_via_action` trio is the noise I should have skipped. Canonical trio: `parse_issue_cases`, `choose_branch_cases`, `parse_digest_cases`."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
