{"timestamp": "2026-04-23T15:37:43.793110", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace/autopilot", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "They're on disk but uncommitted. Looking at the autopilot submodule's git state:\n\n**New (untracked):**\n- `.github/actions/parse-issue/` (action.yml + script.sh)\n- `.github/actions/choose-branch/` (action.yml + script.sh)\n- `.github/actions/parse-digest/` (action.yml + script.sh)\n\n**Modified (unstaged):**\n- `.github/workflows/coding-agent.yml` \u2014 `parse-issue` / `choose-branch` jobs now delegate via `uses:`\n- `.github/workflows/image-digest.yml` \u2014 `parse-digest` job delegates\n- `.github/workflows/act-step-runner.yml` \u2014 added wrapper jobs\n- `.github/scripts/act-step-dispatch.sh` \u2014 follow-`uses:` fallback\n- `.github/scripts/run-in-docker-no-claude.sh` \u2014 defaults + no-docker fallback\n- `spec.k.json` / `spec.k.md` \u2014 7 new constraints (the redundant pairs you flagged)\n\n`git log` in the submodule still shows only the three pre-existing commits (`first commit`, `draft`, `renames`) \u2014 nothing I did is committed. Until you commit and push inside `Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot`, the changes:\n- Won't show on GitHub\n- Won't affect CI (which resolves `@main` from the remote)\n- Only exist in this workspace's submodule working tree\n\nWant me to stage + commit them in the submodule (without pushing)? That'd leave the branch ahead of origin locally; you'd push manually when ready."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
