{"timestamp": "2026-04-23T15:39:51.941467", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace/autopilot", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "create commit texts for both repos", "session_title": "autopilot-selftest"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-23T15:40:20.335766", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "**autopilot submodule (`Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot`):**\n\n```\nExtract pure-function jobs into composite actions\n\nMove parse-issue, choose-branch, and parse-digest out of their workflow\nfiles into .github/actions/<name>/ composite actions (action.yml +\nscript.sh). The workflow jobs now delegate via `uses: ./.github/actions/...`\nwhile retaining their env: blocks so the act-step-dispatch harness can\nstill resolve fixture inputs.\n\nact-step-dispatch.sh follows a job's `uses:` into local composite actions\nwhen no inline run: steps are found, so run-act-step-checks.sh keeps\nworking against the refactored jobs without touching fixtures.\n\nrun-in-docker-no-claude.sh gets local-friendly defaults\n(GITHUB_WORKSPACE=$PWD, AGENT_IMAGE=ghcr.io/...:latest) and a fallback\nthat runs the command in the host shell when docker is unavailable, so\nthe constraint suite can be driven from dev machines.\n\nact-step-runner.yml gains explicit wrapper jobs for each composite\naction as a second test entry point.\n```\n\n**autopilot-selftest (this repo):**\n\n```\nWire selftest to autopilot's constraint suite\n\nAdd autopilot_submodule_healthy feature: runs autopilot's own\ncheck_spec_constraints.py from within the selftest via the submodule's\nrun-in-docker-no-claude.sh entrypoint. Regressions in autopilot (or a\nbroken submodule pin) now fail the selftest directly.\n\nscripts/selftest.sh and scripts/selftest-all.sh drive an end-to-end\ndispatch against the upstream or fork repo, watch the run, and assert\nthe resulting PR lands in the expected place (for fork mode, the PR\nhead must point at the fork \u2014 catches silent fallback to same-repo\nPRs).\n\ncheck-constraints.yml renames its top-level job from delegate to\ncheck-constraints for readable run-graph paths.\n\nREADME documents the two test modes, required secrets, and\nfine-grained PAT gating for RUNNERS_PAT.\n\nBump autopilot submodule pointer.\n```\n\nNote: the submodule-pointer bump happens via `git add autopilot` after autopilot's changes land upstream. If you commit the selftest side now, drop the last line until the submodule HEAD moves."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
