{"timestamp": "2026-04-23T15:55:49.178278", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "why I'm still seeing  check-constraints / image-digest / fetch-manifest\nsucceeded 13 minutes ago in 5s  in autopilot-selftest? Do you know the reason why we erver started workflow jobs refactoring ?", "session_title": "autopilot-selftest"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-23T15:56:22.596450", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Two honest answers:\n\n**1. Why you still see the long path:**\n\nThe autopilot changes are uncommitted in this workspace's submodule. CI for autopilot-selftest resolves `uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/workflows/check-constraints.yml@main` from the *remote* repo, not the local submodule. The remote autopilot hasn't received my refactor, so CI runs the old code.\n\n**2. But even after pushing, the path won't shrink.**\n\nThis is the uncomfortable part. Your original complaint was:\n\n> fuck. thats too much. [...] I hate ugly names like `delegate / image-digest / fetch-manifest`\n\nThe root cause of that path was the **job graph structure** inside autopilot:\n- `check-constraints.yml` has a job `image-digest` that `uses: ./image-digest.yml` (adds segment 2)\n- `image-digest.yml` has separate jobs `fetch-manifest` and `parse-digest` (adds segment 3)\n\nTo flatten the graph, one of these had to go \u2014 merging `fetch-manifest` + `parse-digest` into one job inside `image-digest.yml`, or inlining `image-digest.yml` into `check-constraints.yml`. I described these options and labeled them A/B/C.\n\nThen we drifted. The composite-action conversion we actually did (parse-issue, choose-branch, parse-digest) moves **logic** out of jobs, not **jobs** out of the graph. Composite actions are invoked as steps, not as separate jobs, so they don't reduce path segments. The graph is unchanged: `delegate / image-digest / fetch-manifest` is still three jobs.\n\nSo I did a real refactor \u2014 just not the one that fixes what you complained about.\n\n**To actually shorten the path**, the smallest change is: merge `jobs.fetch-manifest` and `jobs.parse-digest` in `image-digest.yml` into a single `jobs.digest` job with two steps. Result path: `delegate / image-digest / digest` \u2014 still three segments. To get two, `image-digest.yml` has to stop being a separate workflow entirely (inlined into `check-constraints.yml`).\n\nI should have pointed this out before agreeing to the composite-action path. That's on me."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-23T15:57:11.742622", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "it is committed indeed", "session_title": "autopilot-selftest"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-23T15:57:36.263053", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace/autopilot", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "You're right \u2014 I got it wrong. Commit `7a84c15` is on `origin/main`. So the refactor is live. Which means my point stands even more plainly: the path you're still seeing in CI (`check-constraints / image-digest / fetch-manifest`) is the **post-refactor** state, and it's unchanged from before because:\n\n- `autopilot/.github/workflows/check-constraints.yml` still has `jobs.image-digest` that `uses: ./image-digest.yml` \u2192 segment 2\n- `autopilot/.github/workflows/image-digest.yml` still has two separate jobs (`fetch-manifest`, `parse-digest`) \u2192 segment 3\n\nThe composite actions moved code out of job bodies but didn't merge any jobs. Segment count is tied to job count, not to where the implementation lives.\n\nTo actually shorten this path, the minimum change in autopilot is:\n\n```yaml\n# image-digest.yml \u2014 collapse two jobs into one\njobs:\n  digest:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    outputs:\n      digest: ${{ steps.parse.outputs.digest }}\n      image:  ${{ steps.parse.outputs.image }}\n    steps:\n      - id: fetch\n        run: |\n          manifest=$(docker manifest inspect \"${{ inputs.image_repo }}:latest\")\n          echo \"manifest_json<<EOF\" >> $GITHUB_OUTPUT\n          echo \"$manifest\"          >> $GITHUB_OUTPUT\n          echo \"EOF\"                >> $GITHUB_OUTPUT\n      - id: parse\n        uses: ./.github/actions/parse-digest\n        with:\n          manifest_json: ${{ steps.fetch.outputs.manifest_json }}\n          image_repo:    ${{ inputs.image_repo }}\n```\n\nPath becomes `check-constraints / image-digest / digest` (or `digest` if renamed). Still three segments \u2014 can't eliminate the middle one without inlining `image-digest.yml` into `check-constraints.yml`.\n\nWant me to do this collapse in the autopilot submodule?"}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
