{"timestamp": "2026-04-23T17:44:12.751849", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace/autopilot", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Single segment: `check-constraints`.\n\n**The transformation:**\n\nTurn `check-constraints` from a **reusable workflow** into a **published marketplace action** \u2014 composite, lives at `Clockwork-Pilot/check-constraints-action@v1` (or as a subdir action of autopilot itself).\n\nStructure:\n```\nClockwork-Pilot/check-constraints-action/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 action.yml                         \u2190 composite action definition\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 scripts/\n    \u251c\u2500\u2500 image-digest.sh                \u2190 fetch + parse inline (no separate jobs)\n    \u2514\u2500\u2500 run-in-docker.sh\n```\n\n`action.yml` has `inputs:` (image_repo, constraint_script), `runs: using: composite` with steps that:\n1. Resolve image digest (one shell step, no separate job)\n2. Pull + cache docker image\n3. Run `check_spec_constraints.py` inside the container\n\nConsumer caller (autopilot-selftest):\n```yaml\n# .github/workflows/check-constraints.yml\non: [push, pull_request]\njobs:\n  check-constraints:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - uses: Clockwork-Pilot/check-constraints-action@v1\n        with:\n          image_repo: ghcr.io/clockwork-pilot/autopilot-ws\n```\n\nRun-graph path: **`check-constraints`**. One segment. Gone:\n- Reusable-workflow nesting (actions are steps, not jobs)\n- The `image-digest` middle segment (now a step inside the action, invisible in the graph)\n- The `fetch-manifest` / `parse-digest` split (both become shell lines in one step)\n\n**What you give up vs. the current reusable workflow:**\n\n| Feature | Reusable workflow | Composite action |\n|---|---|---|\n| Separate jobs per phase | \u2705 | \u274c (all in one job) |\n| Independent `runs-on` per phase | \u2705 | \u274c |\n| Workflow-level secrets/environments | \u2705 | \u274c (caller-scoped) |\n| Per-phase retry / re-run from UI | \u2705 | \u274c |\n| Marketplace listing page | \ud83d\udfe1 partial | \u2705 first-class |\n| Discoverable via `uses: org/name@v1` | \u274c (needs full `.github/workflows/...@ref`) | \u2705 |\n| Nested path in run graph | 2\u20133 segments | 1 segment |\n\n**What you keep for testability:**\n\nThe composite action's logic lives in shell scripts under `scripts/`. Same `run-act-step-checks.sh`-style fixtures still work \u2014 just pointed at a test-harness workflow that `uses:` the action and captures outputs. No regression in the fixture story.\n\n**Realistic naming on Marketplace:**\n\nYou'd list it as e.g. \"Clockwork-Pilot: Check Spec Constraints\" with the canonical ref `Clockwork-Pilot/check-constraints-action@v1` (actions need their own repo OR can live as subdirs of autopilot at `Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/check-constraints@v1`). Either way the consumer gets the short `uses:` line and the single-segment run graph.\n\n**Tradeoff summary:**\n\n- Current `uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/workflows/check-constraints.yml@main` \u2192 3-segment path, verbose ref, full reusable-workflow features.\n- Best-case `uses: Clockwork-Pilot/check-constraints-action@v1` \u2192 1-segment path, short ref, composite-action limits.\n\nFor check-constraints specifically, the composite-action limits don't bite \u2014 it's a single-runner, single-job operation. That's why this one is a good marketplace candidate. For `coding-agent`, probably not: it splits across runners (issue parsing on hosted, agent execution on self-hosted), which composite actions can't express."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
