{"timestamp": "2026-04-23T20:16:39.791003", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace/autopilot", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Got it now. The architecture is pure-function testing in isolation:\n\n**The contract:**\n\n| Piece | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `input.json` keys | Literal `${{ expression }}` paths the dispatcher resolves against (e.g. `needs.fetch-issue.outputs.title`, `inputs.issue_number`). |\n| Job `env:` block | Maps those expressions to env-var names the script reads. |\n| Script's `run:` body | Reads env vars, writes `$GITHUB_OUTPUT`. No git, no gh, no docker, no network. |\n| `expected.json` | Expected parsed form of `$GITHUB_OUTPUT`. |\n| Dispatcher | Simulates the env, runs the script, diffs. |\n\n**What makes a unit testable under this architecture:**\n\n1. Logic is a **pure function** of `${{ expression }}` inputs.\n2. It lives in a job (or composite-action `uses:` \u2014 my fallback).\n3. It emits structured `$GITHUB_OUTPUT` key-values.\n4. No external side effects.\n\n**Mapping autopilot's units:**\n\n| Unit | Pure? | Fixture-testable? | Current coverage |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `parse-issue` action | \u2705 string parsing | \u2705 | `fixtures/parse-issue/*` (4 cases) |\n| `choose-branch` action | \u2705 branch-selection logic | \u2705 | `fixtures/choose-branch/*` (1 case) |\n| `parse-digest` action | \u2705 JSON parsing | \u2705 | `fixtures/parse-digest/*` (2 cases) |\n| `check-constraints` action | Mixed | Partial | Its digest-resolution step now delegates to `parse-digest` (after my edit), so that slice is covered by parse-digest fixtures. The docker-run slice is not pure (network + docker), cannot be fixture-tested, and correctly isn't. |\n| `fetch-issue` job | \u274c (calls `gh api`) | \u274c | Correctly not fixtured. |\n| `validate-runner` job | \u274c (calls `gh api`) | \u274c | Correctly not fixtured. |\n| `gather-repo-facts` job | \u274c (calls `gh api`) | \u274c | Correctly not fixtured. |\n\n**Conclusion:**\n\nThe check-constraints action slots into this architecture by **delegating its pure-function slice to `parse-digest`** \u2014 which I did. Result: no new fixtures, no new constraints. The existing `parse_digest_cases` constraint implicitly covers check-constraints' digest step because the same composite action is invoked.\n\nIf you want me to verify this end-to-end in autopilot, one command:\n```bash\ncd autopilot && bash .github/scripts/test/run-act-step-checks.sh image-digest.yml parse-digest\n```\nThat run now exercises the same `parse-digest` composite action that check-constraints pulls in. A regression in the digest-parsing logic would fail this test, and through it, fail check-constraints behaviorally in CI.\n\nSo the check-constraints transformation doesn't *add* fixture-level testability \u2014 it preserves it by reusing `parse-digest` rather than reinlining the logic. That's the right architectural answer."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
