{"timestamp": "2026-04-23T20:18:25.070403", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace/autopilot", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "**Current state of the transformation:**\n\n| Piece | Before | After |\n|---|---|---|\n| `autopilot/.github/actions/check-constraints/action.yml` | didn't exist | Composite action; its digest step delegates to `./.github/actions/parse-digest` (existing composite action) |\n| `autopilot/.github/workflows/check-constraints.yml` | ~60 lines with its own jobs + `uses: ./image-digest.yml` | 18-line shim: one job that runs the action |\n| `autopilot/.github/workflows/check-constraints-action-test.yml` | didn't exist | Test harness for act (doesn't fit the fixture dispatcher) |\n| `autopilot-selftest/.github/workflows/check-constraints.yml` | unchanged | Still `uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/workflows/check-constraints.yml@main` |\n\n**Run-graph path (after push):** `check-constraints / check-constraints` \u2014 2 segments. Was `check-constraints / image-digest / check-constraints` = 3.\n\nTo get to 1 segment the consumer would have to bypass the reusable workflow and reference the action directly, which would break selftest's `uses_marketplace_workflow` invariant. 2 segments is the floor while keeping that invariant.\n\n**Test coverage preserved** \u2014 check-constraints' pure-function slice (digest parsing) is now implicitly covered by `parse_digest_cases` fixtures, because both paths invoke the same `./.github/actions/parse-digest` composite action. No new fixtures needed.\n\n**Outdated / problematic constraints:**\n\n| Constraint | State | Action needed |\n|---|---|---|\n| `check_constraints_action_runs` | **Locked failing** \u2014 uses raw `act workflow_dispatch`, which needs docker (unavailable in this sandbox). My mistake \u2014 I added this before you clarified \"act dispatcher\" meant our own `act-step-dispatch.sh`. | Force-delete in the autopilot repo (patch tool blocks it). |\n\nNo other constraints go stale from this transformation:\n- `parse_digest_cases` / `parse_digest_via_action` \u2014 still passing\n- `parse_issue_cases` / `choose_branch_cases` / etc. \u2014 untouched\n- `workflow_hygiene` \u2014 still passing (the new action.yml and test workflow use the approved checkout SHA)\n- `coding_agent_steps`, `upstream_pr_isolation`, `docker_environment` \u2014 untouched\n\n**What remains of the original motivation:**\n\nYour original complaint was \"ugly long names like `delegate / image-digest / fetch-manifest`\". After this session:\n\n- `delegate` \u2192 renamed to `check-constraints` (done earlier, in the selftest)\n- `image-digest / fetch-manifest` and `/ parse-digest` for the check-constraints path \u2192 collapsed into one step inside the action (done)\n- For the coding-agent path, `image-digest.yml` still exists as a separate reusable workflow called by `coding-agent.yml`, so `coding-agent` runs still show `image-digest / fetch-manifest|parse-digest`. That path wasn't part of this transformation.\n\nIf you want the coding-agent path flat too, the same move applies: extract image-digest logic into a composite action inside `.github/actions/image-digest/`, have `coding-agent.yml` use it as a step in the `prepare-image` job, delete `image-digest.yml` (or leave as a secondary shim)."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
