heck-constraints composite action.\n# Exists so consumers that want workflow-level composition (matrix, env,\n# reviewer gates) can still `uses:` this file. Consumers that want the\n# flat run-graph form can bypass this and reference the action directly:\n#   uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/actions/check-constraints@<ref>\non:\n  workflow_call:\n\njobs:\n  check-constraints:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@de0fac2e4500dabe0009e67214ff5f5447ce83dd\n      - uses: ./.github/actions/check-constraints\n", "structuredPatch": [{"oldStart": 13, "oldLines": 4, "newStart": 13, "newLines": 7, "lines": ["     runs-on: ubuntu-latest", "     steps:", "       - uses: actions/checkout@de0fac2e4500dabe0009e67214ff5f5447ce83dd", "-      - uses: ./.github/actions/check-constraints", "+      # Reference the action by repo-qualified ref: inside a reusable workflow", "+      # `./` resolves against the CALLER's checkout, not the workflow's home", "+      # repo, so `uses: ./.github/actions/...` would fail in consumer runs.", "+      - uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/actions/check-constraints@main"]}], "userModified": false, "replaceAll": false}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_011V4X2cqMpnLk1ncyPwF3r5"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-23T20:28:11.921724", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "The bug: inside a reusable workflow, `uses: ./.github/actions/<x>` resolves against the **caller's** checkout, not the repo that owns the workflow file. Your CI log shows exactly that \u2014 it looked in `autopilot-selftest/.github/actions/check-constraints`, which doesn't exist.\n\n**Fix applied:** reference the action by its repo-qualified ref \u2014 `uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/actions/check-constraints@main` \u2014 so GitHub fetches it from the autopilot repo regardless of the caller's workspace.\n\nCaveats to know:\n\n- The ref (`@main`) is pinned in the workflow file. When `autopilot@main` rolls forward, consumers pick it up automatically. If you want a stable ref per-release, change to `@v1` (requires tagging).\n- The coding-agent.yml workflow has the same pattern with `uses: ./.github/actions/parse-issue` etc. \u2014 those work because they're invoked from job steps *after* `actions/checkout` of autopilot itself happens in the run-agent job. But anywhere a reusable workflow's step does `uses: ./...`, the same bug applies. Worth grepping: `grep -n 'uses: \\./' .github/workflows/*.yml` in autopilot and sanity-checking each hit is either inside a step after an autopilot checkout, or converted to the repo-qualified form.\n\nCommit message addendum for the autopilot commit:\n\n```\ncheck-constraints.yml: pin action ref to Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot@main\n\nInside a reusable workflow, `uses: ./.github/actions/...` resolves\nagainst the caller's checkout, not this repo, so consumers got\n\"Can't find action.yml\" at runtime. Reference the action by\nrepo-qualified ref instead.\n```"}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
