{"timestamp": "2026-04-23T20:33:51.446207", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "what is using: composite ?", "session_title": "autopilot-selftest"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-23T20:34:14.459926", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/52dd771c-b9eb-4144-8085-1b2d99eb1964.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "`using: composite` declares that an action is a **composite action** \u2014 i.e. built from a sequence of `steps` (shell commands and/or other actions) defined in YAML, rather than a runnable program.\n\nEvery `action.yml` must declare one of three `using:` values:\n\n| `using:` | What the action is |\n|---|---|\n| `composite` | A YAML list of steps. Runs in the caller's job, on the caller's runner. No build artifacts. Our `parse-issue`, `parse-digest`, `check-constraints` are all of this kind. |\n| `docker` | A Dockerfile or pre-built image. The runner starts a container, runs your entrypoint inside it. Slower cold-start, better isolation. |\n| `node20` (or `node16`) | A JavaScript/TypeScript bundle. The runner executes your `main:` entry with Node. Fastest, used by most `actions/*` actions like `actions/checkout`. |\n\nIn our `action.yml`:\n\n```yaml\nruns:\n  using: composite\n  steps:\n    - id: p\n      shell: bash\n      env: { ... }\n      run: bash \"$GITHUB_ACTION_PATH/script.sh\"\n```\n\n- The `runs:` block describes *how the action executes*.\n- `using: composite` \u2014 shell-based, inline steps.\n- `steps:` \u2014 a list just like a job's steps, with two restrictions: `shell:` is required on every `run:` step (no default), and `runs-on:` doesn't apply (inherits caller's).\n\nWhy use composite:\n\n- Reuse shell/YAML logic across workflows without writing JS or a Dockerfile.\n- Zero build step \u2014 just YAML files.\n- Can call other actions: `uses: actions/checkout@...`, `uses: ./sub-action`, etc. \u2014 makes `check-constraints` able to delegate to `parse-digest`.\n\nLimits vs. docker/node20:\n\n- Steps run in the caller's OS \u2014 you get whatever's on that runner, no guaranteed toolchain.\n- No `runs-on:` \u2014 can't pin to a different runner class inside the action.\n- Secrets passthrough is manual (via `with:` inputs); there's no implicit `${{ secrets.* }}` like in a job.\n- Outputs have to be explicitly declared and wired: `outputs.x.value: ${{ steps.<id>.outputs.x }}`.\n\nSo `using: composite` = \"this is a bundle of steps; run them on the caller's runner.\" That's the flavor of action we've been writing in autopilot."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
