{"timestamp": "2026-04-23T21:21:35.262175", "event": "Stop", "status": "blocked", "reason": "Constraint checks failed", "recurring_failures": [], "data": {"session_id": "86fd98f9-f2ea-428d-98e1-adcabe381cf4", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/86fd98f9-f2ea-428d-98e1-adcabe381cf4.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace/autopilot", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "The remaining (single) real failure, buried in the nested check, is:\n\n**`coding_agent_steps / dispatcher_fails_on_missing_step`**\n\n```\ncd $PROJECT_ROOT && ERR=$(.github/scripts/act-step-dispatch.sh coding-agent.yml nonexistent_step_xyz 2>&1 1>/dev/null); RC=$?; [ $RC -ne 0 ] && echo \"$ERR\" | grep -q \"Step 'nonexistent_step_xyz' not found\"\n```\n\n(The other 4 `coding_agent_steps` constraints and all of `upstream_pr_isolation` / `step_output_checks` are just **skipped dependencies** cascading off this one \u2014 they aren't independent failures.)\n\nWhy it fails under the outer selftest:\n\n- Outer constraint in `/workspace/spec.k.json` reads\n  `PROJECT_ROOT=$PROJECT_ROOT/autopilot python3 \u2026check_spec_constraints.py \u2026`\n- But the checker resolves `$PROJECT_ROOT` from **`CLAUDE_PROJECT_ROOT`** (via `config.py`), not from the shell's `PROJECT_ROOT`.\n- `CLAUDE_PROJECT_ROOT` stays `/workspace` (inherited), so inside the nested run `$PROJECT_ROOT` expands to `/workspace` instead of `/workspace/autopilot`.\n- Result: `cd /workspace && .github/scripts/act-step-dispatch.sh \u2026` \u2014 that script lives at `/workspace/autopilot/.github/scripts/\u2026`, so stderr is \"No such file or directory\" rather than the expected `Step 'nonexistent_step_xyz' not found`, and the `grep -q` fails.\n\nRan standalone: `CLAUDE_PROJECT_ROOT=/workspace/autopilot python3 \u2026` \u2192 **16/16 pass**. So the implementation is fine; only the outer constraint's env override is wrong.\n\n**Fix**: change the outer constraint command from\n`PROJECT_ROOT=$PROJECT_ROOT/autopilot python3 \u2026`\nto\n`CLAUDE_PROJECT_ROOT=$PROJECT_ROOT/autopilot python3 \u2026`\n\nWant me to apply that patch to `/workspace/spec.k.json`?"}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
