ng for any caller repo whose", "-  # root is mounted at /workspace directly (e.g. autopilot-selftest).", "   docker run --rm \\", "-    -e CLAUDE_PROJECT_ROOT=/workspace \\", "     -v \"$GITHUB_WORKSPACE:/workspace\" \\", "     \"$AGENT_IMAGE\" \\", "     bash -c \"source /docker-scripts/user-entrypoint.sh; $CMD\""]}], "userModified": false, "replaceAll": false}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_011icxT16MRWCZkHVSKSjiWy", "duration_ms": 16}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-24T01:18:06.141814", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "cd29e658-61da-4c2d-8626-aa2fbdd1bddb", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/cd29e658-61da-4c2d-8626-aa2fbdd1bddb.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Honest state of what I know vs. don't:\n\n**Known:**\n- Error is `spec not found: /workspace/autopilot/spec.k.json`\n- Docker mount is `$GITHUB_WORKSPACE:/workspace`, so in selftest CI, `/workspace` inside the container = selftest repo root\n- Selftest's spec is at `/workspace/spec.k.json` (confirmed)\n- `/workspace/autopilot/` inside the container = selftest's submodule pointer dir, which in CI is empty because `actions/checkout` doesn't recurse submodules by default\n- The `run` step forwards **zero** `-e` env vars into the container (unlike `run-in-docker-claude.sh`)\n\n**Unknown (lives inside the `autopilot-ws` docker image, which I can't see):**\n- What `check_spec_constraints.py` uses to locate the spec \u2014 a CLI arg default, CWD, an env var, a hardcoded path?\n- What `/docker-scripts/user-entrypoint.sh` does\n\nThe `/workspace/autopilot` hardcoding almost certainly lives in the `autopilot-ws` image. Two ways to investigate before guessing:\n\n1. `docker run --rm ghcr.io/clockwork-pilot/autopilot-ws:latest bash -c 'cat /docker-scripts/user-entrypoint.sh; which check_spec_constraints.py; cat $(which check_spec_constraints.py)'`\n2. Or point me at the `autopilot-ws` repo.\n\nWhich would you prefer?"}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
