{"timestamp": "2026-04-24T01:24:10.842373", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "cd29e658-61da-4c2d-8626-aa2fbdd1bddb", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/cd29e658-61da-4c2d-8626-aa2fbdd1bddb.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "A few known-unresolved things:\n\n1. **Autopilot changes aren't pushed.** The `fix/cross-repo-local-refs` branch (with the `./`\u2192repo-qualified refs) plus the new `submodules` input on `check-constraints.yml` \u2014 neither is on `origin/main`. Until they land there, selftest's caller will:\n   - hit the old `./` bug (from the original failure), and\n   - fail with *\"Invalid input 'submodules'\"* because the `@main` workflow doesn't have that input yet.\n   \n   Also, the submodules-input change is still uncommitted in my local autopilot checkout.\n\n2. **Private-submodule auth.** `actions/checkout` with `submodules: recursive` uses `GITHUB_TOKEN`, which only has access to the calling repo. If `Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot` is private, the submodule fetch will 403. Your selftest README mentions `RUNNERS_PAT`; if so, checkout needs `token: ${{ secrets.RUNNERS_PAT }}` or an equivalent.\n\n3. **The docker image's spec resolution is still unverified.** We're assuming `check_spec_constraints.py` will find `/workspace/autopilot/spec.k.json` once the submodule is populated. The error message says it was looking there, so it should \u2014 but the image's internal logic (user-entrypoint.sh, any `cd`, any env defaults) is opaque from here.\n\n4. **Untracked/modified files in selftest** that look like they belong with this work: `project.k.json`, `project.k.md`, `spec-checks.k.json`, `spec-checks.k.md`, plus modifications to `.protected_files.txt`, `spec.k.json`, `spec.k.md`. None committed.\n\n5. **Submodule pointer bump.** Even after autopilot main is updated, `autopilot/` in selftest points at an older commit. Not required for `uses: ...@main` (GitHub fetches that directly), but a stale pointer is a future footgun.\n\nWant me to commit the autopilot `submodules`-input change and line up the push, then cover the selftest side after?"}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
