{"timestamp": "2026-04-24T01:32:25.612728", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "cd29e658-61da-4c2d-8626-aa2fbdd1bddb", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/cd29e658-61da-4c2d-8626-aa2fbdd1bddb.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Full report of what's still broken / suspect for cross-repo consumers like selftest:\n\n## Remaining cross-repo bugs in `coding-agent.yml` (same class as the `./` fixes)\n\nThree shell invocations execute relative to the **caller's** `$GITHUB_WORKSPACE`, not autopilot's checkout:\n\n| Line | Command |\n|------|---------|\n| 273  | `bash .github/scripts/run-in-docker-claude.sh` |\n| 287\u2013289 | `bash .github/scripts/run-in-docker-no-claude.sh 'check_spec_constraints.py --dry-run' > /tmp/constraints.md 2>&1` |\n| 316  | `bash .github/scripts/run-in-docker-claude.sh --allow-git-commit` |\n\nWhen this reusable workflow is called from selftest, cwd is selftest's checkout, which has no `.github/scripts/run-in-docker-*.sh` \u2014 the bash calls will fail with `No such file or directory`. The `uses: ./...` fixes I pushed don't cover this; those were action references, these are raw shell invocations.\n\n**Fixes (pick one):**\n- **(a) Wrap in composite actions** (cleanest): create `actions/run-agent` and `actions/check-constraints-dryrun` composite actions, move the `bash .github/scripts/...` calls inside (where `$GITHUB_ACTION_PATH` reliably points at autopilot's fetched action dir), and invoke via repo-qualified `uses:`.\n- **(b) Resolve scripts via `$GITHUB_ACTION_PATH`** from an adjacent composite action that re-exports a path to `run-in-docker-*.sh`.\n- **(c) Checkout autopilot into a side dir** (e.g. `actions/checkout@... with repository: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot, path: _autopilot`) and call `bash _autopilot/.github/scripts/...`. Ugly but minimal diff.\n\n## Other suspect items (not verified, flagging only)\n\n1. **`run-in-docker-no-claude.sh` forwards zero envs to docker.** The claude variant forwards several (`MODEL`, `PROMPT`, `CLAUDE_HOOKS_LOG_FILE`, proxy wrapper, etc.). The no-claude variant passes nothing \u2014 if `check_spec_constraints.py` or the image's `user-entrypoint.sh` reads host env, it gets nothing. Confirmed *today* this isn't the root cause of the `/workspace/autopilot/spec.k.json` error (that's the submodule-missing issue), but it's a latent gap.\n\n2. **Docker run has no `-w` / working-dir flag.** Relies entirely on image default. If the image default is `/workspace/autopilot` (which fits the error pattern we saw), any consumer whose repo root is mounted directly at `/workspace` may see confusing behavior. Can't verify without looking at the image.\n\n3. **Submodule checkout auth.** If `Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot` is private, `submodules: recursive` under the default `GITHUB_TOKEN` will 403. Needs `token: ${{ secrets.RUNNERS_PAT }}` (or similar) on the library's checkout.\n\n4. **Version skew hazard.** All the repo-qualified refs pin `@main`. For selftest CI, that means \"latest autopilot main at the moment the runner fetches it\" \u2014 reproducible builds of old selftest commits won't pin. Fine for a dogfood repo; would want shas for anything production.\n\n## Unchanged on disk, still pending\n\n- `fix/cross-repo-local-refs` branch in `/workspace/autopilot` has the `./` fix commit but **not** the new `submodules` input commit. The submodules-input change is currently uncommitted.\n- Nothing pushed to `Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot` \u2014 can't from this sandbox (no ssh/no token).\n- Selftest's workflow edits and untracked `project.k.*` / `spec-checks.k.*` files are uncommitted.\n\nWant me to commit the pending autopilot change and prep a patch for the coding-agent.yml script-path bugs?"}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
