{"timestamp": "2026-04-24T09:44:22.111566", "event": "Stop", "status": "blocked", "reason": "Constraint checks failed", "recurring_failures": [], "data": {"session_id": "b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "## Proposed constraint changes\n\nCurrent state: both constraints are verified (`fails_count: 1`), so per skill rules their `cmd` is locked. Changing them means **remove + add** (and the skill warns removal is contested \u2014 you'd need to override that).\n\n### Keep as-is\n- **`no_local_uses_paths`** \u2014 still correct. The consumer/implementation boundary rule doesn't depend on workflows-vs-actions. No `./` references exist, and none should.\n\n### Remove\n- **`uses_marketplace_workflow`** \u2014 its regex hard-codes the reusable-workflow shape:\n  ```\n  Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/workflows/<name>.yml@<ref>\n  ```\n  We intentionally switched to `Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/actions/check-constraints@<ref>` (composite action) so the consumer can own `checkout` with `submodules: recursive`. This constraint can no longer be satisfied without reverting that design choice.\n\n### Add (replacement)\n- **`uses_marketplace_autopilot`** \u2014 same intent (prove active consumption of the marketplace surface) but accepts either shape:\n  ```\n  id:  uses_marketplace_autopilot\n  cmd: for f in $PROJECT_ROOT/.github/workflows/*.yml; do \\\n         grep -qE 'uses:[[:space:]]*Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/\\.github/(workflows/[a-z0-9_-]+\\.yml|actions/[a-z0-9_/-]+)@' \"$f\" \\\n         || { echo \"$f does not reference a Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot marketplace workflow or action via uses:\"; exit 1; }; \\\n       done\n  description: Positive: every workflow file must reference the Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot marketplace surface \u2014 either a reusable workflow (.github/workflows/<name>.yml@<ref>) or a composite action (.github/actions/<name>@<ref>). Proves active consumption of autopilot, while allowing either integration shape.\n  ```\n  This would pass today against `.github/workflows/check-constraints.yml` (which calls the composite action), and would also pass if we ever move back to a reusable workflow.\n\n### Optional addition (tightening)\n- **`checks_constraints_consumed`** \u2014 narrower: require that specifically the check-constraints surface is consumed somewhere.\n  ```\n  cmd: grep -rqE 'uses:[[:space:]]*Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/\\.github/(workflows/check-constraints\\.yml|actions/check-constraints)@' $PROJECT_ROOT/.github/workflows/\n  ```\n  Guards against someone satisfying `uses_marketplace_autopilot` with an unrelated autopilot action while silently dropping the actual constraint check.\n\n### Summary\n| Action | Constraint |\n|---|---|\n| Keep | `no_local_uses_paths` |\n| Remove | `uses_marketplace_workflow` |\n| Add | `uses_marketplace_autopilot` |\n| Add (optional) | `checks_constraints_consumed` |\n\nWant me to proceed with the remove+add? Note the skill will resist removal of a verified constraint \u2014 may need manual intervention on `spec.k.json`."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
