{"timestamp": "2026-04-24T10:29:50.777842", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "data": {"session_id": "b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "so which of them worked to update constraint? \u25cf Bash(printf 'name: verify-stub\\non: workflow_dispatch\\njobs:\\n  noop:\\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\\n    steps:\\n      - run: \"true\"\\n' >\n      /workspace/.github/workflows/\u2026)\n  \u23bf \u00a0PASS\n\n     \u26a0\ufe0f   1 constraint(s) now locked (cmd cannot be changed):\n     \u2026 +19 lines (ctrl+o to expand)\n\n\u25cf Bash(python3 -c \"import json; d=json.load(open('/workspace/spec.k.json'));\n      print(d['features']['selftest_shape']['constraints']['uses_marketplace_autopilot'].get('fa\u2026)\n  \u23bf \u00a01\n\n\u25cf Constraint is verified (fails_count=1) and the full suite passes.\n", "session_title": "autopilot-selftest"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-24T10:30:03.623965", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "The **first `${PLUGIN_ROOT}/bin/check`** run \u2014 the one executed while `_verify_stub.yml` existed in `.github/workflows/` \u2014 is what did the work.\n\nSequence inside that single Bash call:\n1. `printf ... > _verify_stub.yml` \u2014 stub created (doesn't reference `Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/...`).\n2. **`${PLUGIN_ROOT}/bin/check`** \u2014 ran the constraint's `cmd`; the `for`-loop hit the stub and `grep -qE` returned non-zero \u2192 exit 1 \u2192 checker recorded a failure \u2192 `fails_count` 0 \u2192 1. This is the step that verified the constraint. Its on-screen output printed the *pre-run* status (`fails_count=0`, \"unverified blocking\"), which is why it looked like nothing happened \u2014 but the persisted value in `spec.k.json` got bumped afterwards.\n3. `rm _verify_stub.yml` \u2014 stub removed.\n4. Second `${PLUGIN_ROOT}/bin/check` \u2014 with `fails_count` now 1 and no offending file, both constraints passed \u2192 overall `PASS`.\n\nThe `python3 ... fails_count` readback just confirmed persistence; it didn't change anything."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
