{"timestamp": "2026-04-24T11:08:33.704186", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Two supported paths, both documented in `autopilot/README.md` \u2192 \"Installing extra dependencies\":\n\n**Option A \u2014 `image_setup_script`**\n- Inline bash snippet passed as a workflow input.\n- Self-hosted runner layers it onto `ghcr.io/clockwork-pilot/autopilot-ws` as a single `RUN` (as root), tags by `sha256(script)`, reuses docker's layer cache.\n- Workspace is **not** mounted at build time \u2192 can't read `pyproject.toml`/`package.json`.\n- Cap ~65k chars (workflow_call input limit).\n- Nothing pushed to a registry.\n\n**Option B \u2014 `agent_image`**\n- Build your own image `FROM ghcr.io/clockwork-pilot/autopilot-ws`, push to GHCR, pass the tag as `agent_image:`.\n- `templates/user-image/` has a ready-to-copy `Dockerfile` + `build-and-push.yml`.\n- Private GHCR images require `docker login ghcr.io` before `uses:` in the caller.\n- Can combine with `image_setup_script` for one-off additions without rebuilding.\n\n**Runtime contract both must satisfy** (this is the \"support level\"):\n- `USER node` at runtime.\n- Tools on `PATH` for the `node` user.\n- Based on (or ABI-compatible with) `autopilot-ws`.\n\nAnything meeting that contract runs. Migration A\u2192B is mechanical (paste script into `RUN`, swap the input). No other custom-image hooks are exposed \u2014 no pre/post entrypoint hooks, no mount customization, no alternative base image guarantee."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
