{"timestamp": "2026-04-24T11:31:05.695427", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "data": {"session_id": "b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "So we may need custom image (runtime injections) in agent.yml, check-constraints.yml. Since agent using local runner it could preinstall user's related packages and then mount them using docker-files. But we also have check-constraints which executed on ubuntu-latest.", "session_title": "autopilot-selftest"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-24T11:31:35.417074", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Good instinct \u2014 partially already there, partially a gap.\n\n### Current state\n- **`coding-agent.yml`** \u2192 input `agent_image:` (+ `image_setup_script:`). Agent jobs run on self-hosted; the runner builds/pulls the image locally. Caching is effectively \"free\" (local docker layer cache on your own disk).\n- **`.github/actions/check-constraints/action.yml`** \u2192 input `image_repo:` (default `ghcr.io/clockwork-pilot/autopilot-ws`). Already supports swapping in a custom image. Pulls by digest on `ubuntu-latest`, saves to `/tmp/autopilot-ws.tar`, keys `actions/cache` by digest.\n- **`.github/workflows/check-constraints.yml`** (reusable shim) \u2192 only forwards `submodules:`. Does **not** expose `image_repo`. So today, consumers who use the shim can't select a custom image, even though the underlying action supports it.\n\n### The asymmetry you're pointing at\n- Agent side: self-hosted runner \u2192 build-once-and-keep, can preinstall user packages freely; `image_setup_script` composes layers on top with near-zero marginal cost.\n- Check side: `ubuntu-latest` is ephemeral \u2192 every run pays a pull (mitigated by `actions/cache` keyed on digest, not on setup script). `image_setup_script`-style inline builds would have to happen inside that ephemeral runner every cache miss, which is slower and less cacheable than just pulling a prebuilt image.\n\n### Implication\nFor check-constraints on GitHub-hosted runners, the right primitive is **not** `image_setup_script` (which is great on a warm self-hosted runner and poor on cold ephemeral ones) \u2014 it's a **prebuilt image**. Which is exactly what `image_repo` already gives you at the action level.\n\n### Concrete gap / suggested change\n1. Expose `image_repo` (and probably `command`) on the reusable `check-constraints.yml` so workflow-level consumers get parity with action-level consumers.\n2. Naming: `coding-agent.yml` uses `agent_image` (full tag), `check-constraints` uses `image_repo` (no tag \u2014 always `:cached` inside). Worth unifying the input name, or at least documenting the divergence, so a user setting a custom image sets the same variable in both callers.\n3. Decide whether `image_setup_script`-style inline layering should exist on the check side at all. My take: no \u2014 it creates cold-cache build time on every GitHub-hosted run, and if the constraint-check toolchain needs extra packages, the user already has a prebuilt image (for the agent) that can be reused here.\n\nWant me to (a) add `image_repo` passthrough to the reusable workflow, (b) rename for parity with `agent_image`, or (c) just document the current surface?"}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
