{"timestamp": "2026-04-24T12:11:11.416323", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "data": {"session_id": "b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "Develop a GitHub Action for Unified Docker Image Building\n\n1. Goal: Create a reusable GitHub Action, available in the GitHub Marketplace, that provides a consistent interface for building Docker images. The action should work seamlessly on both GitHub-hosted runners and self-hosted runners.\n\n2. Functionality:\n\n   * Accept a user-defined Dockerfile as input, which is based on a base Docker image provided by the action\u2019s base image.\n   * For GitHub-hosted runners, check if a matching image exists in the cache. If not, build the image and cache it.\n   * For self-hosted runners, always build the image locally if no applicable image is available.\n\n3. Interface: Ensure that the action provides a simple, standardized set of inputs\u2014such as the Dockerfile path, tag name, and build arguments\u2014so users have a single, clear interface regardless of the runner type.\n\n4. Key Requirements:\n\n   * Ensure cache keys are user or project specific to avoid cross-project interference.\n   * Document guidelines so users understand how to define unique cache keys, preventing cache collisions.\n   * Ensure the action is well-documented and user-friendly, so users can easily integrate it into their workflows.\n\n5. Deliverables:\n\n   * A fully implemented GitHub Action with the described logic.\n   * Clear documentation on how to use the action, set unique keys, and interpret the outputs.\n   * A sample workflow illustrating both GitHub-hosted and self-hosted use cases.\n\n", "session_title": "autopilot-selftest"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-24T12:11:41.709745", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Before I write this, let me surface the design decisions I'd bake in so you can redirect. Short version \u2014 want to confirm before implementing?\n\n### Proposed shape\n\n**New composite action**: `Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/actions/build-agent-image` (composite, not Docker container action \u2014 so it works on self-hosted without Docker-in-Docker gymnastics).\n\n**Inputs** (unified across runner types):\n| Input | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `dockerfile` | Path to user Dockerfile (default: `Dockerfile`). Must `FROM` an autopilot-ws-compatible base. |\n| `build_args` | Newline-separated `KEY=VALUE` build args. |\n| `base_image` | Base image to pin (default `ghcr.io/clockwork-pilot/autopilot-ws:latest`); resolved to digest for cache keying. |\n| `tag` | Local tag to produce (default: `autopilot-ws-custom:local`). |\n| `cache_key_prefix` | **Required, no default.** Forces callers to namespace \u2014 \"project-name\" or \"repo-slug\". Guideline: `${{ github.repository }}-agent-img`. |\n| `cache_scope` | `github` \\| `self-hosted` \\| `auto` (default). Auto = detect `runner.environment`. |\n\n**Outputs**:\n| Output | |\n|---|---|\n| `image` | Tag that downstream steps should reference. |\n| `cache_hit` | `true`/`false`. |\n| `digest` | sha256 of built image (for pinning). |\n\n### Behavior\n\n- **Cache key**: `${cache_key_prefix}-${hashFiles(dockerfile)}-${base_image_digest}-${hash(build_args)}`. Deterministic, survives across runs with identical inputs, invalidates on any input change.\n- **GitHub-hosted**: use `actions/cache` keyed above, path `/tmp/<tag>.tar`. Miss \u2192 `docker build` \u2192 `docker save` \u2192 cache save. Hit \u2192 `docker load`.\n- **Self-hosted**: skip `actions/cache` entirely. Docker's native layer cache on the persistent runner disk is strictly better than round-tripping a tarball through `actions/cache`. Check `docker image inspect ${tag}-${cache_key}` \u2192 present \u2192 reuse; missing \u2192 build. Tag includes the hash so stale images coexist harmlessly and `docker image prune` is the cleanup path.\n- **Both paths produce identical outputs** \u2014 caller doesn't branch on runner type.\n\n### Integration with existing surface\n\n- `coding-agent.yml` and `check-constraints` composite action get an optional `build_image_from:` input that, if set, invokes this new action and uses the resulting tag in place of `agent_image`/`image_repo`.\n- Existing `image_setup_script` stays for simple cases; new action covers the \"Dockerfile with multiple dependencies\" case.\n- New action is **marketplace-publishable** because it lives at `.github/actions/<name>/action.yml` with its own `README.md` and semver tags \u2014 GH Marketplace picks up composite actions this way.\n\n### Design decisions I'd like you to weigh in on\n\n1. **Is the cache key design right?** I want to force `cache_key_prefix` with no default so users can't accidentally share cache across projects. Alternative: default to `${{ github.repository }}` and document the override.\n2. **Self-hosted: skip `actions/cache` or use it as a backup?** My take: skip. Docker's local cache dominates. But if you want cross-runner cache portability (multiple self-hosted runners), using `actions/cache` as a secondary makes sense.\n3. **Docker Buildx vs plain `docker build`?** Buildx gives better layer caching and multi-arch; requires a setup step. I'd default to Buildx with `docker/setup-buildx-action`.\n4. **Should this subsume `image_setup_script`** over time, or stay parallel? Parallel for now, subsume later once stable.\n\nConfirm the shape (or push back on any of #1\u20134) and I'll implement: action.yml + README.md + a sample consumer workflow + wiring into `coding-agent.yml` and `check-constraints`. Rough scope ~250 lines action + ~150 lines docs."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-24T12:22:27.045431", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "data": {"session_id": "b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "1 - right. 2 self-hosted don't need any other caching layer except of adding local tags. 3 - lets use buildx. 4 - no need anymore image_setup_script. Also autopilot-selftest should have test workflows checking both options (with dockerfile, and without) for both check-constraints, agent workflows", "session_title": "autopilot-selftest"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-24T12:24:55.872177", "event": "Write", "data": {"session_id": "b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "PreToolUse", "tool_name": "Write", "tool_input": {"file_path": "/workspace/autopilot/.github/actions/build-agent-image/action.yml", "content": "name: Build Agent Image\ndescription: |\n  Build a Dockerfile-based agent/check image with a unified interface across\n  GitHub-hosted and self-hosted runners. Uses Buildx. On GitHub-hosted runners,\n  caches the built image via actions/cache keyed by (cache_key_prefix, Dockerfile\n  content, base image digest, build args). On self-hosted runners, relies on\n  local docker tags keyed by the same hash \u2014 no tarball round-trips.\n\ninputs:\n  dockerfile:\n    description: Path to the Dockerfile, relative to $GITHUB_WORKSPACE. Must FROM an autopilot-ws-compatible base (USER node at runtime).\n    required: false\n    default: Dockerfile\n  context:\n    description: Build context directory, relative to $GITHUB_WORKSPACE.\n    required: false\n    default: \".\"\n  build_args:\n    description: |\n      Newline-separated KEY=VALUE build args. Forwarded as --build-arg entries to buildx.\n      Included in the cache key, so changing any arg invalidates the cache.\n    required: false\n    default: \"\"\n  base_image:\n    description: |\n      Base image reference used only for cache-key stability. The action does not\n      rewrite the Dockerfile's FROM \u2014 the Dockerfile still decides the base. Set\n      this to the same image you `FROM` so the cache invalidates when the upstream\n      autopilot-ws image is republished.\n    required: false\n    default: ghcr.io/clockwork-pilot/autopilot-ws:latest\n  tag:\n    description: Local tag base. The computed content hash is appended, producing `<tag>:<hash>`.\n    required: false\n    default: autopilot-ws-custom\n  cache_key_prefix:\n    description: |\n      REQUIRED. Namespace for the actions/cache entry and the local docker tag.\n      Use a project-specific value (e.g. `${{ github.repository }}-agent-img`).\n      Distinct projects MUST use distinct prefixes to avoid cache collisions on\n      shared GitHub-hosted cache scopes and to keep self-hosted docker tags\n      disambiguated. There is no default: omitting this is a usage error.\n    required: true\n\noutputs:\n  image:\n    description: Fully qualified local tag of the produced image. Ready to `docker run`.\n    value: ${{ steps.finalize.outputs.image }}\n  cache_hit:\n    description: \"true\" if the image was available without rebuilding (cache restore on GitHub-hosted, local tag present on self-hosted).\n    value: ${{ steps.finalize.outputs.cache_hit }}\n  digest:\n    description: Local image ID (sha256) of the produced image.\n    value: ${{ steps.finalize.outputs.digest }}\n\nruns:\n  using: composite\n  steps:\n    - id: env\n      shell: bash\n      run: |\n        # runner.environment is 'github-hosted' or 'self-hosted'\n        case \"${{ runner.environment }}\" in\n          self-hosted) echo \"is_self_hosted=true\"  >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\" ;;\n          *)           echo \"is_self_hosted=false\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\" ;;\n        esac\n\n    - id: base\n      shell: bash\n      env:\n        BASE: ${{ inputs.base_image }}\n      run: |\n        set -euo pipefail\n        # Resolve the base image's manifest digest for cache-key stability.\n        # Falls back to pull+inspect if manifest inspect is unavailable.\n        DIGEST=$(docker manifest inspect \"$BASE\" 2>/dev/null \\\n          | sha256sum | cut -c1-16) || DIGEST=\"\"\n        if [ -z \"$DIGEST\" ]; then\n          docker pull \"$BASE\" >/dev/null\n          DIGEST=$(docker inspect --format='{{.Id}}' \"$BASE\" | sed 's/^sha256://' | cut -c1-16)\n        fi\n        echo \"digest=$DIGEST\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n\n    - id: key\n      shell: bash\n      env:\n        DOCKERFILE:  ${{ inputs.dockerfile }}\n        BUILD_ARGS:  ${{ inputs.build_args }}\n        BASE_DIGEST: ${{ steps.base.outputs.digest }}\n        PREFIX:      ${{ inputs.cache_key_prefix }}\n        TAG_BASE:    ${{ inputs.tag }}\n      run: |\n        set -euo pipefail\n        if [ -z \"$PREFIX\" ]; then\n          echo \"::error::cache_key_prefix is required \u2014 see action README\"\n          exit 1\n        fi\n        DF_HASH=$(sha256sum \"$DOCKERFILE\" | cut -c1-16)\n        ARG_HASH=$(printf '%s' \"$BUILD_ARGS\" | sha256sum | cut -c1-16)\n        HASH=\"${DF_HASH}-${BASE_DIGEST}-${ARG_HASH}\"\n        SAFE_PREFIX=$(printf '%s' \"$PREFIX\" | tr '/ ' '__')\n        echo \"hash=$HASH\"                         >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n        echo \"tag=${TAG_BASE}:${SAFE_PREFIX}-${HASH}\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n        echo \"cache_key=${PREFIX}-buildimg-${HASH}\"   >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n\n    - id: local\n      if: steps.env.outputs.is_self_hosted == 'true'\n      shell: bash\n      env:\n        TAG: ${{ steps.key.outputs.tag }}\n      run: |\n        if docker image inspect \"$TAG\" >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n          echo \"hit=true\"  >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n        else\n          echo \"hit=false\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n        fi\n\n    - id: cache\n      if: steps.env.outputs.is_self_hosted != 'true'\n      uses: actions/cache@0057852bfaa89a56745cba8c7296529d2fc39830\n      with:\n        path: /tmp/build-agent-image.tar\n        key:  ${{ steps.key.outputs.cache_key }}\n\n    - id: load\n      if: steps.env.outputs.is_self_hosted != 'true' && steps.cache.outputs.cache-hit == 'true'\n      shell: bash\n      env:\n        TAG: ${{ steps.key.outputs.tag }}\n      run: |\n        set -euo pipefail\n        out=$(docker load < /tmp/build-agent-image.tar)\n        echo \"$out\"\n        if ! docker image inspect \"$TAG\" >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n          src=$(printf '%s\\n' \"$out\" \\\n            | sed -n -e 's/^Loaded image: //p' -e 's/^Loaded image ID: //p' | head -n1)\n          if [ -n \"$src\" ]; then\n            docker tag \"$src\" \"$TAG\"\n          else\n            echo \"::warning::Cache restored but could not resolve loaded image \u2014 will rebuild\"\n            echo \"rebuild=true\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n            exit 0\n          fi\n        fi\n        echo \"rebuild=false\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n\n    - name: should_build\n      id: should_build\n      shell: bash\n      env:\n        IS_SELF_HOSTED: ${{ steps.env.outputs.is_self_hosted }}\n        LOCAL_HIT:      ${{ steps.local.outputs.hit }}\n        CACHE_HIT:      ${{ steps.cache.outputs.cache-hit }}\n        REBUILD:        ${{ steps.load.outputs.rebuild }}\n      run: |\n        if [ \"$IS_SELF_HOSTED\" = \"true\" ]; then\n          [ \"$LOCAL_HIT\" = \"true\" ] && echo \"yes=false\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\" || echo \"yes=true\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n        else\n          if [ \"$CACHE_HIT\" = \"true\" ] && [ \"$REBUILD\" != \"true\" ]; then\n            echo \"yes=false\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n          else\n            echo \"yes=true\"  >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n          fi\n        fi\n\n    - if: steps.should_build.outputs.yes == 'true'\n      uses: docker/setup-buildx-action@c47758b77c9736f4b2ef4073d4d51994fabfe349\n\n    - id: build\n      if: steps.should_build.outputs.yes == 'true'\n      shell: bash\n      env:\n        DOCKERFILE: ${{ inputs.dockerfile }}\n        CONTEXT:    ${{ inputs.context }}\n        TAG:        ${{ steps.key.outputs.tag }}\n        BUILD_ARGS: ${{ inputs.build_args }}\n      run: |\n        set -euo pipefail\n        ARGS=()\n        while IFS= read -r line; do\n          [ -z \"$line\" ] && continue\n          ARGS+=(--build-arg \"$line\")\n        done <<< \"$BUILD_ARGS\"\n        docker buildx build --load -t \"$TAG\" -f \"$DOCKERFILE\" \"${ARGS[@]}\" \"$CONTEXT\"\n\n    - name: save_tarball\n      if: steps.env.outputs.is_self_hosted != 'true' && steps.should_build.outputs.yes == 'true'\n      shell: bash\n      env:\n        TAG: ${{ steps.key.outputs.tag }}\n      run: docker save \"$TAG\" > /tmp/build-agent-image.tar\n\n    - id: finalize\n      shell: bash\n      env:\n        TAG:            ${{ steps.key.outputs.tag }}\n        IS_SELF_HOSTED: ${{ steps.env.outputs.is_self_hosted }}\n        LOCAL_HIT:      ${{ steps.local.outputs.hit }}\n        CACHE_HIT:      ${{ steps.cache.outputs.cache-hit }}\n        REBUILD:        ${{ steps.load.outputs.rebuild }}\n      run: |\n        set -euo pipefail\n        if [ \"$IS_SELF_HOSTED\" = \"true\" ]; then\n          HIT=\"$LOCAL_HIT\"\n        else\n          if [ \"$CACHE_HIT\" = \"true\" ] && [ \"$REBUILD\" != \"true\" ]; then HIT=true; else HIT=false; fi\n        fi\n        DIGEST=$(docker inspect --format='{{.Id}}' \"$TAG\")\n        {\n          echo \"image=$TAG\"\n          echo \"cache_hit=$HIT\"\n          echo \"digest=$DIGEST\"\n        } >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n"}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_01RkaUeQqaenhE2XXwgPms6G"}}
