e `dockerfile` input path through the\n# Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot coding-agent.yml reusable workflow, proving that\n# consumers can build a custom agent image (e.g. layering extra tooling on\n# top of autopilot-ws) and dispatch the agent against it.\n#\n# Like agent.yml, this is workflow_dispatch only \u2014 running it requires a\n# self-hosted runner labeled with your GitHub username and an issue_number\n# to act on. The sibling workflow (agent.yml) covers the default path with\n# no Dockerfile (base autopilot-ws as-is).\n\non:\n  workflow_dispatch:\n    inputs:\n      runner_label:\n        description: GitHub username (matches self-hosted runner label)\n        required: true\n        type: string\n      issue_number:\n        description: Issue number to work on\n        required: true\n        type: string\n\npermissions:\n  contents: write\n  pull-requests: write\n  issues: write\n\njobs:\n  run:\n    uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/workflows/coding-agent.yml@main\n    with:\n      runner_label:     ${{ inputs.runner_label }}\n      issue_number:     ${{ inputs.issue_number }}\n      dockerfile:       Dockerfile.agent-sample\n      cache_key_prefix: ${{ github.repository }}-agent-img\n    secrets:\n      UPSTREAM_PR_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.UPSTREAM_PR_TOKEN }}\n", "structuredPatch": [], "originalFile": null, "userModified": false}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_01XX8nV2eu1TqiuBFsDAacX8", "duration_ms": 19}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-24T12:29:25.300997", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Done. Summary:\n\n### New action \u2014 `autopilot/.github/actions/build-agent-image/`\n- `action.yml` \u2014 Buildx-based builder via `docker/build-push-action@v6`.\n  - **GitHub-hosted**: `cache-from/to: type=gha,scope=<prefix>-buildimg` \u2192 layer-level caching through the Actions Cache service. Yes, cache is preserved \u2014 layers, not tarballs, which is strictly better than the old approach (cross-Dockerfile layer reuse within scope).\n  - **Self-hosted**: no external cache layer; relies on the docker daemon's persistent local cache. Adding `actions/cache` here would just duplicate what the daemon does for free.\n  - Fast-path skip: if the content-hashed local tag already exists, build is skipped entirely.\n  - `cache_key_prefix` is **required**, no default (prevents cross-project collisions).\n- `README.md` \u2014 inputs, outputs, cache-key guidelines, usage examples for both runner types, migration guide from `image_setup_script`.\n\n### Autopilot integrations\n- `autopilot/.github/actions/check-constraints/action.yml` \u2014 added `dockerfile` / `build_args` / `cache_key_prefix` inputs; delegates to `build-agent-image` when `dockerfile` is set, otherwise keeps the existing pull+cache path.\n- `autopilot/.github/workflows/check-constraints.yml` \u2014 forwards the three new inputs.\n- `autopilot/.github/workflows/coding-agent.yml`:\n  - Removed `image_setup_script` input entirely.\n  - Added `dockerfile` / `build_args` / `cache_key_prefix` inputs.\n  - Rewrote the `prepare-image` job to call `build-agent-image` when a Dockerfile is provided, else fall back to `agent_image` override or resolved autopilot-ws digest.\n\n### autopilot-selftest (this repo)\n- `Dockerfile.agent-sample` \u2014 minimal autopilot-ws derivative adding `jq`.\n- `.github/workflows/check-constraints-with-dockerfile.yml` \u2014 variant passing `dockerfile:`.\n- `.github/workflows/agent-with-dockerfile.yml` \u2014 `workflow_dispatch` variant passing `dockerfile:`.\n- Existing `check-constraints.yml` and `agent.yml` remain as the \"without Dockerfile\" cases.\n\n### Validation\n- Constraints pass (`${PLUGIN_ROOT}/bin/check` \u2192 PASS on both the autopilot submodule and selftest specs).\n- All new workflow files satisfy `uses_marketplace_autopilot`.\n\n### Remaining work outside this change\n- **Commit**: the autopilot submodule has uncommitted changes (new action, edited action/workflows). Selftest has new files too. Both need separate commits (submodule bump follows).\n- **`templates/user-image/`**: still present; consider retargeting its docs to point at `build-agent-image` since the \"build your own image and push to GHCR\" flow now has a lighter-weight alternative.\n- **Marketplace publication**: `build-agent-image` is structured for Marketplace (composite action with `name`, `description`, own README). Publishing just needs a tag on the autopilot repo.\n\nWant me to open a PR in the autopilot submodule and another in autopilot-selftest?"}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
