{"timestamp": "2026-04-24T14:39:44.939640", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Here's the perspective \u2014 what `check-constraints.yml` (the reusable workflow shim) looks like if `build-agent-image` becomes a **visible, separate step** in the job rather than being called from inside the `check-constraints` action.\n\n### What changes\n\n**`check-constraints` action shrinks**: it stops caring about Dockerfiles or build args. It accepts a pre-built image (or defaults to pulling `autopilot-ws`) and runs the check. Single responsibility.\n\n**`build-agent-image` becomes a first-class step** that the shim invokes conditionally before the check.\n\n### The reusable workflow\n\n```yaml\nname: Check Constraints\n\non:\n  workflow_call:\n    inputs:\n      submodules:\n        required: false\n        type: string\n        default: \"\"\n      dockerfile:\n        description: Optional Dockerfile. When set, the build-image step runs; otherwise skipped and the default autopilot-ws image is used.\n        required: false\n        type: string\n        default: \"\"\n      build_args:\n        required: false\n        type: string\n        default: \"\"\n      cache_key_prefix:\n        description: Required when `dockerfile` is set. See build-agent-image/README.md.\n        required: false\n        type: string\n        default: \"\"\n\njobs:\n  check-constraints:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@de0fac2e4500dabe0009e67214ff5f5447ce83dd\n        with:\n          submodules: ${{ inputs.submodules }}\n\n      # Visible, skippable step. Shows up in the run graph as \"Build agent image\"\n      # when the user passed a Dockerfile, or collapses to a single \"skipped\" line\n      # otherwise. Cache hits/misses are legible here, not buried inside another action.\n      - id: build-image\n        if: inputs.dockerfile != ''\n        uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/actions/build-agent-image@main\n        with:\n          dockerfile:       ${{ inputs.dockerfile }}\n          build_args:       ${{ inputs.build_args }}\n          cache_key_prefix: ${{ inputs.cache_key_prefix }}\n\n      - uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/actions/check-constraints@main\n        with:\n          # Empty string \u2192 check-constraints pulls autopilot-ws (its default path).\n          # Non-empty \u2192 check-constraints runs against that exact tag, no build logic inside.\n          image: ${{ steps.build-image.outputs.image }}\n```\n\n### What the `check-constraints` action becomes\n\nStripped down to two paths:\n\n```yaml\ninputs:\n  image:\n    description: Pre-built image ref. If empty, the action pulls ghcr.io/clockwork-pilot/autopilot-ws and caches it.\n    required: false\n    default: \"\"\n  command:\n    required: false\n    default: check_spec_constraints.py\n\nruns:\n  using: composite\n  steps:\n    # Path A: user passed an image \u2192 just tag-alias it for run-in-docker-no-claude.sh\n    - if: inputs.image != ''\n      shell: bash\n      run: docker tag \"${{ inputs.image }}\" ghcr.io/clockwork-pilot/autopilot-ws:cached\n\n    # Path B: no image \u2192 existing pull+cache autopilot-ws logic (unchanged)\n    - if: inputs.image == ''\n      # ... fetch / digest / actions/cache / load / pull (as today) ...\n\n    - shell: bash\n      env:\n        AGENT_IMAGE: ghcr.io/clockwork-pilot/autopilot-ws:cached\n        CMD:         ${{ inputs.command }}\n      run: bash \"$GITHUB_ACTION_PATH/../../scripts/run-in-docker-no-claude.sh\" \"$CMD\"\n```\n\nNo `dockerfile`, no `build_args`, no `cache_key_prefix` \u2014 those moved out.\n\n### Trade-offs\n\n| | Nested (current) | Separated (proposed) |\n|---|---|---|\n| Shim input count | 4 | 4 (same) |\n| User visibility of build | Hidden inside action | Explicit step in run graph |\n| Log clarity | Build + check interleaved under one step | Two named steps, clean timing |\n| Reuse of built image across jobs | Impossible (image dies with the action) | Possible: publish step outputs, pass to other steps |\n| Duplication risk | None | Slightly: the `action-only` direct-call path (bypassing the shim) loses the separation unless consumers wire both actions themselves |\n| Action surface | `check-constraints` has dockerfile inputs | `check-constraints` doesn't \u2014 cleaner contract |\n\n### My read\nThe separated shape is cleaner. The one real cost \u2014 consumers who bypass the reusable workflow and call `check-constraints` directly need to also wire `build-agent-image` themselves \u2014 is a feature, not a bug: it pushes them toward the standard shape and makes the caching step legible. The shim hides that friction for everyone using `uses: ...workflows/check-constraints.yml`.\n\nSame pattern applies to `coding-agent.yml`: the `prepare-image` job calls `build-agent-image` as an explicit step, and `run-agent` consumes its output \u2014 which it already does structurally; the proposed change just drops the `prepare-image` wrapper's \"decide-and-maybe-build\" branching.\n\nWant me to refactor to this shape?"}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
