{"timestamp": "2026-04-24T14:55:46.282675", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Got it \u2014 so `build-agent-image` becomes the single authority on \"what image to use\", with or without a Dockerfile. Here's the revised shape:\n\n### Behavior matrix\n\n| `dockerfile` | What the action does | `image` output |\n|---|---|---|\n| unset | Resolve `base_image` digest, pull, tag locally, cache (GHA cache on github-hosted; docker daemon on self-hosted) | `<tag>:<prefix>-base-<digest>` |\n| set | Build the Dockerfile on top of `base_image`, cache layers | `<tag>:<prefix>-<content-hash>` |\n\nConsumers always get one `image` output; `check-constraints` just consumes it.\n\n### Revised `action.yml` (key sections)\n\n```yaml\ninputs:\n  dockerfile:\n    description: Optional. When unset, the action only pulls+tags `base_image` and outputs that.\n    required: false\n    default: \"\"\n  base_image:\n    description: |\n      The upstream image to pull, and the FROM contract for any Dockerfile.\n      Always pulled and tagged locally, whether or not a Dockerfile is built on top.\n    required: false\n    default: ghcr.io/clockwork-pilot/autopilot-ws:latest\n  build_args:\n    required: false\n    default: \"\"\n  context:\n    required: false\n    default: \".\"\n  tag:\n    required: false\n    default: autopilot-ws-custom\n  cache_key_prefix:\n    description: REQUIRED. Namespaces the cache and the local tag for both pull-only and build paths.\n    required: true\n\noutputs:\n  image:      # final tag (base-only or Dockerfile-built)\n  cache_hit:\n  digest:\n\nruns:\n  using: composite\n  steps:\n    - id: env          # detect runner.environment\n    - id: base         # resolve base_image digest\n\n    # -- compute target tag & cache scope --\n    - id: key\n      # dockerfile empty \u2192 tag = <prefix>-base-<digest>\n      # dockerfile set   \u2192 tag = <prefix>-<df-hash>-<base-digest>-<args-hash>\n\n    # -- fast path: local tag already present, skip everything --\n    - id: local\n\n    # ================================================================\n    # PATH A: dockerfile empty \u2014 pull+tag base (with GHA cache when hosted)\n    # ================================================================\n    - id: cache-pull\n      if: inputs.dockerfile == '' && steps.env.outputs.is_self_hosted != 'true' && steps.local.outputs.hit != 'true'\n      uses: actions/cache@...\n      with:\n        path: /tmp/build-agent-base.tar\n        key:  ${{ inputs.cache_key_prefix }}-baseimg-${{ steps.base.outputs.digest }}\n\n    - if: inputs.dockerfile == '' && steps.cache-pull.outputs.cache-hit == 'true'\n      run: |\n        out=$(docker load < /tmp/build-agent-base.tar)\n        src=$(echo \"$out\" | sed -n 's/^Loaded image[^:]*: //p' | head -n1)\n        docker tag \"$src\" \"${{ steps.key.outputs.tag }}\"\n\n    - if: inputs.dockerfile == '' && steps.local.outputs.hit != 'true' && steps.cache-pull.outputs.cache-hit != 'true'\n      run: |\n        docker pull \"${{ inputs.base_image }}\"\n        docker tag \"${{ inputs.base_image }}\" \"${{ steps.key.outputs.tag }}\"\n        # Save tarball on github-hosted only (self-hosted relies on daemon cache)\n        if [ \"${{ steps.env.outputs.is_self_hosted }}\" != \"true\" ]; then\n          docker save \"${{ steps.key.outputs.tag }}\" > /tmp/build-agent-base.tar\n        fi\n\n    # ================================================================\n    # PATH B: dockerfile set \u2014 build with buildx (as today)\n    # ================================================================\n    - if: inputs.dockerfile != '' && steps.local.outputs.hit != 'true'\n      uses: docker/setup-buildx-action@...\n\n    - if: inputs.dockerfile != '' && steps.local.outputs.hit != 'true' && steps.env.outputs.is_self_hosted != 'true'\n      uses: docker/build-push-action@...\n      with:\n        file: ${{ inputs.dockerfile }}\n        tags: ${{ steps.key.outputs.tag }}\n        load: true\n        cache-from: type=gha,scope=${{ inputs.cache_key_prefix }}-buildimg\n        cache-to:   type=gha,mode=max,scope=${{ inputs.cache_key_prefix }}-buildimg\n\n    - if: inputs.dockerfile != '' && steps.local.outputs.hit != 'true' && steps.env.outputs.is_self_hosted == 'true'\n      uses: docker/build-push-action@...\n      with:\n        file: ${{ inputs.dockerfile }}\n        tags: ${{ steps.key.outputs.tag }}\n        load: true\n\n    - id: finalize   # emit image / cache_hit / digest\n```\n\n### What `check-constraints` action becomes\n\n```yaml\ninputs:\n  image:\n    description: Image ref produced by build-agent-image. Required.\n    required: true\n  command:\n    default: check_spec_constraints.py\n\nruns:\n  using: composite\n  steps:\n    - shell: bash\n      run: docker tag \"${{ inputs.image }}\" autopilot-check:cached\n    - shell: bash\n      env:\n        AGENT_IMAGE: autopilot-check:cached\n        CMD:         ${{ inputs.command }}\n      run: bash \"$GITHUB_ACTION_PATH/../../scripts/run-in-docker-no-claude.sh\" \"$CMD\"\n```\n\nNo pulling, no caching, no branching. It's a dumb runner.\n\n### What `check-constraints.yml` (reusable workflow) becomes\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  check-constraints:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@...\n        with:\n          submodules: ${{ inputs.submodules }}\n      - id: build-image\n        uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/actions/build-agent-image@main\n        with:\n          dockerfile:       ${{ inputs.dockerfile }}     # may be empty \u2192 base-only\n          build_args:       ${{ inputs.build_args }}\n          cache_key_prefix: ${{ inputs.cache_key_prefix }}\n      - uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/actions/check-constraints@main\n        with:\n          image: ${{ steps.build-image.outputs.image }}\n```\n\nAlways two steps, always legible, always the same shape regardless of Dockerfile presence.\n\n### Trade-offs vs current design\n\n**Wins:**\n- One action owns all image lifecycle (pull, build, cache, tag).\n- `check-constraints` becomes trivially small \u2014 dumb consumer.\n- The `prepare-image` job in `coding-agent.yml` also collapses: it just calls `build-agent-image` unconditionally, drops the `agent_image` fallback branching.\n- `cache_key_prefix` is consistent semantics for both paths \u2014 no \"required when X set\" footnote.\n\n**Costs:**\n- `cache_key_prefix` now required for every consumer, including default (no Dockerfile) case. Users who did nothing before must now pass a prefix. Not a big ask, but it is a breaking change to the reusable workflow's interface.\n- Slight duplication in the action: pull-path uses `actions/cache` + tarball (because `type=gha` is buildx-specific and doesn't help for plain `docker pull`), build-path uses `type=gha`. Two caching mechanisms in one action.\n\nWant me to implement this?"}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
