f-hosted (both paths) \u2192 docker daemon's persistent local layer cache (no external layer).\n    - Fast path: when a local tag with the computed content hash already exists, build/pull is skipped entirely.\n\ninputs:\n  dockerfile:\n    description: Path to the Dockerfile, relative to $GITHUB_WORKSPACE. Leave empty to only pull+tag `base_image`.\n    required: false\n    default: \"\"\n  context:\n    description: Build context directory, relative to $GITHUB_WORKSPACE. Only used when `dockerfile` is set.\n    required: false\n    default: \".\"\n  build_args:\n    description: |\n      Newline-separated KEY=VALUE build args, forwarded to the builder.\n      Included in the content hash, so a change invalidates the local tag (but not\n      necessarily the GHA layer cache, which buildx reuses at layer granularity).\n    required: false\n    default: \"\"\n  base_image:\n    description: |\n      Image reference to pull and tag locally, and to use as the FROM contract for\n      any Dockerfile. REQUIRED. The action does NOT rewrite the Dockerfile's FROM \u2014\n      the Dockerfile still decides the base; this input is what drives the pull+tag\n      path and the cache-key stability.\n    required: true\n  tag:\n    description: Local tag base. A `<prefix>-<hash>` suffix is appended, producing `<tag>:<prefix>-<hash>`.\n    required: false\n    default: cached-image\n  cache_key_prefix:\n    description: |\n      REQUIRED. Namespace for the cache and the local docker tag.\n      Use a project-specific value (e.g. `${{ github.repository }}-img`).\n      Distinct projects MUST use distinct prefixes to avoid cross-project cache\n      interference on shared cache scopes and to keep self-hosted docker tags\n      disambiguated. There is no default: omitting this is a usage error.\n    required: true\n\noutputs:\n  image:\n    description: Fully qualified local tag of the produced image. Ready to `docker run`.\n    value: ${{ steps.finalize.outputs.image }}\n  cache_hit:\n    description: \"true\" if the local tag pre-existed and neither build nor pull ran; \"false\" otherwise.\n    value: ${{ steps.finalize.outputs.cache_hit }}\n  digest:\n    description: Local image ID (sha256) of the produced image.\n    value: ${{ steps.finalize.outputs.digest }}\n\nruns:\n  using: composite\n  steps:\n    - id: env\n      shell: bash\n      run: |\n        case \"${{ runner.environment }}\" in\n          self-hosted) echo \"is_self_hosted=true\"  >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\" ;;\n          *)           echo \"is_self_hosted=false\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\" ;;\n        esac\n\n    - id: base\n      shell: bash\n      env:\n        BASE: ${{ inputs.base_image }}\n      run: |\n        set -euo pipefail\n        DIGEST=$(docker manifest inspect \"$BASE\" 2>/dev/null | sha256sum | cut -c1-16) || DIGEST=\"\"\n        if [ -z \"$DIGEST\" ]; then\n          docker pull \"$BASE\" >/dev/null\n          DIGEST=$(docker inspect --format='{{.Id}}' \"$BASE\" | sed 's/^sha256://' | cut -c1-16)\n        fi\n        echo \"digest=$DIGEST\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n\n    - id: key\n      shell: bash\n      env:\n        DOCKERFILE:  ${{ inputs.dockerfile }}\n        BUILD_ARGS:  ${{ inputs.build_args }}\n        BASE_DIGEST: ${{ steps.base.outputs.digest }}\n        PREFIX:      ${{ inputs.cache_key_prefix }}\n        TAG_BASE:    ${{ inputs.tag }}\n      run: |\n        set -euo pipefail\n        if [ -z \"$PREFIX\" ]; then\n          echo \"::error::cache_key_prefix is required \u2014 see action README\"\n          exit 1\n        fi\n        SAFE_PREFIX=$(printf '%s' \"$PREFIX\" | tr '/ ' '__')\n        if [ -z \"$DOCKERFILE\" ]; then\n          HASH=\"base-${BASE_DIGEST}\"\n        else\n          DF_HASH=$(sha256sum \"$DOCKERFILE\" | cut -c1-16)\n          ARG_HASH=$(printf '%s' \"$BUILD_ARGS\" | sha256sum | cut -c1-16)\n          HASH=\"${DF_HASH}-${BASE_DIGEST}-${ARG_HASH}\"\n        fi\n        echo \"hash=$HASH\"                               >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n        echo \"tag=${TAG_BASE}:${SAFE_PREFIX}-${HASH}\"   >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n        echo \"build_scope=${SAFE_PREFIX}-buildimg\"      >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n        echo \"pull_cache_key=${SAFE_PREFIX}-pullimg-${BASE_DIGEST}\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n\n    - id: local\n      shell: bash\n      env:\n        TAG: ${{ steps.key.outputs.tag }}\n      run: |\n        if docker image inspect \"$TAG\" >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n          echo \"hit=true\"  >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n        else\n          echo \"hit=false\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n        fi\n\n    # ================================================================\n    # PATH A \u2014 dockerfile unset: pull+tag base\n    # ================================================================\n    - id: pull-cache\n      if: inputs.dockerfile == '' && steps.env.outputs.is_self_hosted != 'true' && steps.local.outputs.hit != 'true'\n      uses: actions/cache@0057852bfaa89a56745cba8c7296529d2fc39830\n      with:\n        path: /tmp/build-docker-image.tar\n        key:  ${{ steps.key.outputs.pull_cache_key }}\n\n    - name: Load pulled image from cache\n      if: inputs.dockerfile == '' && steps.local.outputs.hit != 'true' && steps.pull-cache.outputs.cache-hit == 'true'\n      shell: bash\n      env:\n        TAG: ${{ steps.key.outputs.tag }}\n      run: |\n        set -euo pipefail\n        out=$(docker load < /tmp/build-docker-image.tar)\n        echo \"$out\"\n        if ! docker image inspect \"$TAG\" >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n          src=$(printf '%s\\n' \"$out\" | sed -n -e 's/^Loaded image: //p' -e 's/^Loaded image ID: //p' | head -n1)\n          [ -n \"$src\" ] && docker tag \"$src\" \"$TAG\"\n        fi\n\n    - name: Pull base image\n      if: inputs.dockerfile == '' && steps.local.outputs.hit != 'true' && steps.pull-cache.outputs.cache-hit != 'true'\n      shell: bash\n      env:\n        BASE:           ${{ inputs.base_image }}\n        TAG:            ${{ steps.key.outputs.tag }}\n        IS_SELF_HOSTED: ${{ steps.env.outputs.is_self_hosted }}\n      run: |\n        set -euo pipefail\n        docker pull \"$BASE\"\n        docker tag \"$BASE\" \"$TAG\"\n        if [ \"$IS_SELF_HOSTED\" != \"true\" ]; then\n          docker save \"$TAG\" > /tmp/build-docker-image.tar\n        fi\n\n    # ================================================================\n    # PATH B \u2014 dockerfile set: buildx\n    # ================================================================\n    - if: inputs.dockerfile != '' && steps.local.outputs.hit != 'true'\n      uses: docker/setup-buildx-action@c47758b77c9736f4b2ef4073d4d51994fabfe349\n\n    - name: Build (github-hosted, GHA layer cache)\n      if: inputs.dockerfile != '' && steps.local.outputs.hit != 'true' && steps.env.outputs.is_self_hosted != 'true'\n      uses: docker/build-push-action@263435318d21b8e681c14492fe198d362a7d2c10\n      with:\n        context:    ${{ inputs.context }}\n        file:       ${{ inputs.dockerfile }}\n        build-args: ${{ inputs.build_args }}\n        tags:       ${{ steps.key.outputs.tag }}\n        load:       true\n        push:       false\n        cache-from: type=gha,scope=${{ steps.key.outputs.build_scope }}\n        cache-to:   type=gha,mode=max,scope=${{ steps.key.outputs.build_scope }}\n\n    - name: Build (self-hosted, docker daemon layer cache)\n      if: inputs.dockerfile != '' && steps.local.outputs.hit != 'true' && steps.env.outputs.is_self_hosted == 'true'\n      uses: docker/build-push-action@263435318d21b8e681c14492fe198d362a7d2c10\n      with:\n        context:    ${{ inputs.context }}\n        file:       ${{ inputs.dockerfile }}\n        build-args: ${{ inputs.build_args }}\n        tags:       ${{ steps.key.outputs.tag }}\n        load:       true\n        push:       false\n\n    - id: finalize\n      shell: bash\n      env:\n        TAG:       ${{ steps.key.outputs.tag }}\n        LOCAL_HIT: ${{ steps.local.outputs.hit }}\n      run: |\n        set -euo pipefail\n        DIGEST=$(docker inspect --format='{{.Id}}' \"$TAG\")\n        {\n          echo \"image=$TAG\"\n          echo \"cache_hit=$LOCAL_HIT\"\n          echo \"digest=$DIGEST\"\n        } >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n", "structuredPatch": [], "originalFile": null, "userModified": false}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_01M12XRFXXTVoDX51MsVQZc1", "duration_ms": 17}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-24T14:58:41.587585", "event": "Write", "data": {"session_id": "b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "PreToolUse", "tool_name": "Write", "tool_input": {"file_path": "/workspace/autopilot/.github/actions/build-docker-image/README.md", "content": "# build-docker-image\n\nGeneric composite action for building \u2014 or just pulling \u2014 a Docker image with unified caching across **GitHub-hosted** and **self-hosted** runners. One set of inputs, one set of outputs, no runner-type branching in the caller.\n\n## What it does\n\nTwo paths, selected by whether you pass a `dockerfile`:\n\n| `dockerfile` input | Behavior |\n|---|---|\n| unset | Pulls `base_image`, tags it locally under a content-addressable tag, caches the tarball (GitHub-hosted) or relies on the docker daemon (self-hosted). Returns the tag. |\n| set | Builds the Dockerfile (via Buildx + `docker/build-push-action`) with `base_image` as the FROM contract. GitHub-hosted uses Buildx's GHA layer cache (`type=gha`, scoped by `cache_key_prefix`); self-hosted uses the docker daemon's persistent local layer cache. Returns the tag. |\n\nFast path (both modes): if a local image with the computed content-hashed tag already exists, the build/pull step is skipped entirely.\n\n## Inputs\n\n| Input | Required | Default | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `dockerfile` | no | `\"\"` | Dockerfile path (relative to `$GITHUB_WORKSPACE`). Unset = pull-and-tag mode. |\n| `context` | no | `.` | Build context directory. Only used in build mode. |\n| `build_args` | no | `\"\"` | Newline-separated `KEY=VALUE`, forwarded to `--build-arg`. |\n| `base_image` | **yes** | \u2014 | Image reference. Pulled and tagged locally in pull mode; used for content-hash stability in build mode. The action does not rewrite your Dockerfile's `FROM` \u2014 set `base_image` to match what your Dockerfile imports. |\n| `tag` | no | `cached-image` | Local tag base. The action appends `<prefix>-<hash>`. |\n| `cache_key_prefix` | **yes** | \u2014 | Namespace for the cache and local tag. See [Cache key guidelines](#cache-key-guidelines). |\n\n## Outputs\n\n| Output | |\n|---|---|\n| `image` | Fully qualified local tag of the produced image. Pass this to `docker run`. |\n| `cache_hit` | `true` if the local tag pre-existed and neither build nor pull ran; `false` otherwise. |\n| `digest` | Local image ID (`sha256:...`). |\n\n## Cache key guidelines\n\n**You must supply `cache_key_prefix`.** There is no default. Picking the wrong value causes either cache collisions (distinct projects eating each other's entries) or cache thrash (same project, different prefix per workflow \u2192 no reuse).\n\nRules of thumb:\n- **Namespace by repo**: `${{ github.repository }}-<purpose>`, e.g. `octocat/my-app-ci-img`.\n- **Do not include volatile fields** like `github.sha`, `github.run_id`, or the date. The action already hashes Dockerfile content, build args, and base image digest into the tag \u2014 anything beyond the prefix should be stable across runs that should share a cache.\n- **Distinguish purposes** if one repo builds multiple images: `${{ github.repository }}-test-img` vs `${{ github.repository }}-agent-img`.\n- **Organization-wide images** shared across several repos can use a shared prefix, but only if you trust every workflow writing to it not to poison the cache.\n\n### What the prefix controls\n\n1. **Buildx GHA scope** (`type=gha,scope=<prefix>-buildimg`) \u2014 isolates Buildx's layer cache per project. Layer-level reuse within that scope; you don't need to invalidate manually.\n2. **`actions/cache` key** (pull mode, `<prefix>-pullimg-<base-digest>`) \u2014 isolates the pulled tarball per project.\n3. **Local docker tag** (`<tag>:<prefix>-<content-hash>`) \u2014 disambiguates images when the same self-hosted runner serves multiple projects.\n\n## Usage\n\n### Pull an image (unified across runner types)\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  run:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest     # or [self-hosted, my-label]\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - id: img\n        uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/actions/build-docker-image@main\n        with:\n          base_image:       ghcr.io/acme/runtime:latest\n          cache_key_prefix: ${{ github.repository }}-runtime\n      - run: docker run --rm ${{ steps.img.outputs.image }} my-command\n```\n\n### Build a Dockerfile\n\n```yaml\n- id: img\n  uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/actions/build-docker-image@main\n  with:\n    dockerfile:       Dockerfile.ci\n    base_image:       ghcr.io/acme/runtime:latest\n    cache_key_prefix: ${{ github.repository }}-ci-img\n    build_args: |\n      PYTHON_VERSION=3.12\n      NODE_VERSION=22\n- run: docker run --rm ${{ steps.img.outputs.image }} pytest\n```\n\nSame call shape on a self-hosted runner \u2014 the action detects `runner.environment` and drops the GHA cache layer automatically (docker daemon does it better on persistent disks).\n\n## When to use this\n\n- You want a single caching story for images across GitHub-hosted and self-hosted.\n- You're layering extra tooling onto a pinned upstream image and want Buildx's layer cache \"for free\".\n- You don't want to manually wire `docker login` / `docker pull` / `actions/cache` / `docker save` / `docker load` in every workflow.\n\n## When not to use this\n\n- You want to **publish** the image to a registry. This action only produces local tags. Use `docker/build-push-action` directly with `push: true` for publication.\n- Your workflow builds many distinct images per run. Cache keying per-image is out of scope; wire `docker/build-push-action` per image.\n"}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_01CGc4okESLmhG2e6TEPXT78"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-24T14:58:41.821004", "event": "Write", "data": {"session_id": "b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "PostToolUse", "tool_name": "Write", "tool_input": {"file_path": "/workspace/autopilot/.github/actions/build-docker-image/README.md", "content": "# build-docker-image\n\nGeneric composite action for building \u2014 or just pulling \u2014 a Docker image with unified caching across **GitHub-hosted** and **self-hosted** runners. One set of inputs, one set of outputs, no runner-type branching in the caller.\n\n## What it does\n\nTwo paths, selected by whether you pass a `dockerfile`:\n\n| `dockerfile` input | Behavior |\n|---|---|\n| unset | Pulls `base_image`, tags it locally under a content-addressable tag, caches the tarball (GitHub-hosted) or relies on the docker daemon (self-hosted). Returns the tag. |\n| set | Builds the Dockerfile (via Buildx + `docker/build-push-action`) with `base_image` as the FROM contract. GitHub-hosted uses Buildx's GHA layer cache (`type=gha`, scoped by `cache_key_prefix`); self-hosted uses the docker daemon's persistent local layer cache. Returns the tag. |\n\nFast path (both modes): if a local image with the computed content-hashed tag already exists, the build/pull step is skipped entirely.\n\n## Inputs\n\n| Input | Required | Default | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `dockerfile` | no | `\"\"` | Dockerfile path (relative to `$GITHUB_WORKSPACE`). Unset = pull-and-tag mode. |\n| `context` | no | `.` | Build context directory. Only used in build mode. |\n| `build_args` | no | `\"\"` | Newline-separated `KEY=VALUE`, forwarded to `--build-arg`. |\n| `base_image` | **yes** | \u2014 | Image reference. Pulled and tagged locally in pull mode; used for content-hash stability in build mode. The action does not rewrite your Dockerfile's `FROM` \u2014 set `base_image` to match what your Dockerfile imports. |\n| `tag` | no | `cached-image` | Local tag base. The action appends `<prefix>-<hash>`. |\n| `cache_key_prefix` | **yes** | \u2014 | Namespace for the cache and local tag. See [Cache key guidelines](#cache-key-guidelines). |\n\n## Outputs\n\n| Output | |\n|---|---|\n| `image` | Fully qualified local tag of the produced image. Pass this to `docker run`. |\n| `cache_hit` | `true` if the local tag pre-existed and neither build nor pull ran; `false` otherwise. |\n| `digest` | Local image ID (`sha256:...`). |\n\n## Cache key guidelines\n\n**You must supply `cache_key_prefix`.** There is no default. Picking the wrong value causes either cache collisions (distinct projects eating each other's entries) or cache thrash (same project, different prefix per workflow \u2192 no reuse).\n\nRules of thumb:\n- **Namespace by repo**: `${{ github.repository }}-<purpose>`, e.g. `octocat/my-app-ci-img`.\n- **Do not include volatile fields** like `github.sha`, `github.run_id`, or the date. The action already hashes Dockerfile content, build args, and base image digest into the tag \u2014 anything beyond the prefix should be stable across runs that should share a cache.\n- **Distinguish purposes** if one repo builds multiple images: `${{ github.repository }}-test-img` vs `${{ github.repository }}-agent-img`.\n- **Organization-wide images** shared across several repos can use a shared prefix, but only if you trust every workflow writing to it not to poison the cache.\n\n### What the prefix controls\n\n1. **Buildx GHA scope** (`type=gha,scope=<prefix>-buildimg`) \u2014 isolates Buildx's layer cache per project. Layer-level reuse within that scope; you don't need to invalidate manually.\n2. **`actions/cache` key** (pull mode, `<prefix>-pullimg-<base-digest>`) \u2014 isolates the pulled tarball per project.\n3. **Local docker tag** (`<tag>:<prefix>-<content-hash>`) \u2014 disambiguates images when the same self-hosted runner serves multiple projects.\n\n## Usage\n\n### Pull an image (unified across runner types)\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  run:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest     # or [self-hosted, my-label]\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - id: img\n        uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/actions/build-docker-image@main\n        with:\n          base_image:       ghcr.io/acme/runtime:latest\n          cache_key_prefix: ${{ github.repository }}-runtime\n      - run: docker run --rm ${{ steps.img.outputs.image }} my-command\n```\n\n### Build a Dockerfile\n\n```yaml\n- id: img\n  uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/actions/build-docker-image@main\n  with:\n    dockerfile:       Dockerfile.ci\n    base_image:       ghcr.io/acme/runtime:latest\n    cache_key_prefix: ${{ github.repository }}-ci-img\n    build_args: |\n      PYTHON_VERSION=3.12\n      NODE_VERSION=22\n- run: docker run --rm ${{ steps.img.outputs.image }} pytest\n```\n\nSame call shape on a self-hosted runner \u2014 the action detects `runner.environment` and drops the GHA cache layer automatically (docker daemon does it better on persistent disks).\n\n## When to use this\n\n- You want a single caching story for images across GitHub-hosted and self-hosted.\n- You're layering extra tooling onto a pinned upstream image and want Buildx's layer cache \"for free\".\n- You don't want to manually wire `docker login` / `docker pull` / `actions/cache` / `docker save` / `docker load` in every workflow.\n\n## When not to use this\n\n- You want to **publish** the image to a registry. This action only produces local tags. Use `docker/build-push-action` directly with `push: true` for publication.\n- Your workflow builds many distinct images per run. Cache keying per-image is out of scope; wire `docker/build-push-action` per image.\n"}, "tool_response": {"type": "create", "filePath": "/workspace/autopilot/.github/actions/build-docker-image/README.md", "content": "# build-docker-image\n\nGeneric composite action for building \u2014 or just pulling \u2014 a Docker image with unified caching across **GitHub-hosted** and **self-hosted** runners. One set of inputs, one set of outputs, no runner-type branching in the caller.\n\n## What it does\n\nTwo paths, selected by whether you pass a `dockerfile`:\n\n| `dockerfile` input | Behavior |\n|---|---|\n| unset | Pulls `base_image`, tags it locally under a content-addressable tag, caches the tarball (GitHub-hosted) or relies on the docker daemon (self-hosted). Returns the tag. |\n| set | Builds the Dockerfile (via Buildx + `docker/build-push-action`) with `base_image` as the FROM contract. GitHub-hosted uses Buildx's GHA layer cache (`type=gha`, scoped by `cache_key_prefix`); self-hosted uses the docker daemon's persistent local layer cache. Returns the tag. |\n\nFast path (both modes): if a local image with the computed content-hashed tag already exists, the build/pull step is skipped entirely.\n\n## Inputs\n\n| Input | Required | Default | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `dockerfile` | no | `\"\"` | Dockerfile path (relative to `$GITHUB_WORKSPACE`). Unset = pull-and-tag mode. |\n| `context` | no | `.` | Build context directory. Only used in build mode. |\n| `build_args` | no | `\"\"` | Newline-separated `KEY=VALUE`, forwarded to `--build-arg`. |\n| `base_image` | **yes** | \u2014 | Image reference. Pulled and tagged locally in pull mode; used for content-hash stability in build mode. The action does not rewrite your Dockerfile's `FROM` \u2014 set `base_image` to match what your Dockerfile imports. |\n| `tag` | no | `cached-image` | Local tag base. The action appends `<prefix>-<hash>`. |\n| `cache_key_prefix` | **yes** | \u2014 | Namespace for the cache and local tag. See [Cache key guidelines](#cache-key-guidelines). |\n\n## Outputs\n\n| Output | |\n|---|---|\n| `image` | Fully qualified local tag of the produced image. Pass this to `docker run`. |\n| `cache_hit` | `true` if the local tag pre-existed and neither build nor pull ran; `false` otherwise. |\n| `digest` | Local image ID (`sha256:...`). |\n\n## Cache key guidelines\n\n**You must supply `cache_key_prefix`.** There is no default. Picking the wrong value causes either cache collisions (distinct projects eating each other's entries) or cache thrash (same project, different prefix per workflow \u2192 no reuse).\n\nRules of thumb:\n- **Namespace by repo**: `${{ github.repository }}-<purpose>`, e.g. `octocat/my-app-ci-img`.\n- **Do not include volatile fields** like `github.sha`, `github.run_id`, or the date. The action already hashes Dockerfile content, build args, and base image digest into the tag \u2014 anything beyond the prefix should be stable across runs that should share a cache.\n- **Distinguish purposes** if one repo builds multiple images: `${{ github.repository }}-test-img` vs `${{ github.repository }}-agent-img`.\n- **Organization-wide images** shared across several repos can use a shared prefix, but only if you trust every workflow writing to it not to poison the cache.\n\n### What the prefix controls\n\n1. **Buildx GHA scope** (`type=gha,scope=<prefix>-buildimg`) \u2014 isolates Buildx's layer cache per project. Layer-level reuse within that scope; you don't need to invalidate manually.\n2. **`actions/cache` key** (pull mode, `<prefix>-pullimg-<base-digest>`) \u2014 isolates the pulled tarball per project.\n3. **Local docker tag** (`<tag>:<prefix>-<content-hash>`) \u2014 disambiguates images when the same self-hosted runner serves multiple projects.\n\n## Usage\n\n### Pull an image (unified across runner types)\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  run:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest     # or [self-hosted, my-label]\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - id: img\n        uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/actions/build-docker-image@main\n        with:\n          base_image:       ghcr.io/acme/runtime:latest\n          cache_key_prefix: ${{ github.repository }}-runtime\n      - run: docker run --rm ${{ steps.img.outputs.image }} my-command\n```\n\n### Build a Dockerfile\n\n```yaml\n- id: img\n  uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/actions/build-docker-image@main\n  with:\n    dockerfile:       Dockerfile.ci\n    base_image:       ghcr.io/acme/runtime:latest\n    cache_key_prefix: ${{ github.repository }}-ci-img\n    build_args: |\n      PYTHON_VERSION=3.12\n      NODE_VERSION=22\n- run: docker run --rm ${{ steps.img.outputs.image }} pytest\n```\n\nSame call shape on a self-hosted runner \u2014 the action detects `runner.environment` and drops the GHA cache layer automatically (docker daemon does it better on persistent disks).\n\n## When to use this\n\n- You want a single caching story for images across GitHub-hosted and self-hosted.\n- You're layering extra tooling onto a pinned upstream image and want Buildx's layer cache \"for free\".\n- You don't want to manually wire `docker login` / `docker pull` / `actions/cache` / `docker save` / `docker load` in every workflow.\n\n## When not to use this\n\n- You want to **publish** the image to a registry. This action only produces local tags. Use `docker/build-push-action` directly with `push: true` for publication.\n- Your workflow builds many distinct images per run. Cache keying per-image is out of scope; wire `docker/build-push-action` per image.\n", "structuredPatch": [], "originalFile": null, "userModified": false}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_01CGc4okESLmhG2e6TEPXT78", "duration_ms": 18}}
