{"timestamp": "2026-04-24T15:07:25.246558", "event": "Edit", "data": {"session_id": "b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "PostToolUse", "tool_name": "Edit", "tool_input": {"file_path": "/workspace/autopilot/.github/actions/ensure-docker-image/action.yml", "old_string": "name: Build Docker Image\ndescription: |\n  Build (or pull) a docker image with a unified interface across GitHub-hosted\n  and self-hosted runners. Always uses Buildx for builds.", "new_string": "name: Ensure Docker Image\ndescription: |\n  Ensure a local docker image tag exists \u2014 either by pulling a base image or by\n  building a Dockerfile on top of it \u2014 with a unified caching story across\n  GitHub-hosted and self-hosted runners. Idempotent: a fast path skips work\n  entirely when the content-hashed local tag already exists.", "replace_all": false}, "tool_response": {"filePath": "/workspace/autopilot/.github/actions/ensure-docker-image/action.yml", "oldString": "name: Build Docker Image\ndescription: |\n  Build (or pull) a docker image with a unified interface across GitHub-hosted\n  and self-hosted runners. Always uses Buildx for builds.", "newString": "name: Ensure Docker Image\ndescription: |\n  Ensure a local docker image tag exists \u2014 either by pulling a base image or by\n  building a Dockerfile on top of it \u2014 with a unified caching story across\n  GitHub-hosted and self-hosted runners. Idempotent: a fast path skips work\n  entirely when the content-hashed local tag already exists.", "originalFile": "name: Build Docker Image\ndescription: |\n  Build (or pull) a docker image with a unified interface across GitHub-hosted\n  and self-hosted runners. Always uses Buildx for builds.\n\n  Two paths:\n    - dockerfile unset  \u2192 pulls `base_image`, tags it locally, outputs the tag.\n    - dockerfile set    \u2192 builds the Dockerfile on top of `base_image`, outputs the built tag.\n\n  Caching:\n    - GitHub-hosted build path \u2192 Buildx GHA cache (type=gha), scoped by cache_key_prefix.\n    - GitHub-hosted pull path  \u2192 actions/cache over a docker save tarball, keyed by base digest.\n    - Self-hosted (both paths) \u2192 docker daemon's persistent local layer cache (no external layer).\n    - Fast path: when a local tag with the computed content hash already exists, build/pull is skipped entirely.\n\ninputs:\n  dockerfile:\n    description: Path to the Dockerfile, relative to $GITHUB_WORKSPACE. Leave empty to only pull+tag `base_image`.\n    required: false\n    default: \"\"\n  context:\n    description: Build context directory, relative to $GITHUB_WORKSPACE. Only used when `dockerfile` is set.\n    required: false\n    default: \".\"\n  build_args:\n    description: |\n      Newline-separated KEY=VALUE build args, forwarded to the builder.\n      Included in the content hash, so a change invalidates the local tag (but not\n      necessarily the GHA layer cache, which buildx reuses at layer granularity).\n    required: false\n    default: \"\"\n  base_image:\n    description: |\n      Image reference to pull and tag locally, and to use as the FROM contract for\n      any Dockerfile. REQUIRED. The action does NOT rewrite the Dockerfile's FROM \u2014\n      the Dockerfile still decides the base; this input is what drives the pull+tag\n      path and the cache-key stability.\n    required: true\n  tag:\n    description: Local tag base. A `<prefix>-<hash>` suffix is appended, producing `<tag>:<prefix>-<hash>`.\n    required: false\n    default: cached-image\n  cache_key_prefix:\n    description: |\n      REQUIRED. Namespace for the cache and the local docker tag.\n      Use a project-specific value (e.g. `${{ github.repository }}-img`).\n      Distinct projects MUST use distinct prefixes to avoid cross-project cache\n      interference on shared cache scopes and to keep self-hosted docker tags\n      disambiguated. There is no default: omitting this is a usage error.\n    required: true\n\noutputs:\n  image:\n    description: Fully qualified local tag of the produced image. Ready to `docker run`.\n    value: ${{ steps.finalize.outputs.image }}\n  cache_hit:\n    description: \"true\" if the local tag pre-existed and neither build nor pull ran; \"false\" otherwise.\n    value: ${{ steps.finalize.outputs.cache_hit }}\n  digest:\n    description: Local image ID (sha256) of the produced image.\n    value: ${{ steps.finalize.outputs.digest }}\n\nruns:\n  using: composite\n  steps:\n    - id: env\n      shell: bash\n      run: |\n        case \"${{ runner.environment }}\" in\n          self-hosted) echo \"is_self_hosted=true\"  >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\" ;;\n          *)           echo \"is_self_hosted=false\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\" ;;\n        esac\n\n    - id: base\n      shell: bash\n      env:\n        BASE: ${{ inputs.base_image }}\n      run: |\n        set -euo pipefail\n        DIGEST=$(docker manifest inspect \"$BASE\" 2>/dev/null | sha256sum | cut -c1-16) || DIGEST=\"\"\n        if [ -z \"$DIGEST\" ]; then\n          docker pull \"$BASE\" >/dev/null\n          DIGEST=$(docker inspect --format='{{.Id}}' \"$BASE\" | sed 's/^sha256://' | cut -c1-16)\n        fi\n        echo \"digest=$DIGEST\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n\n    - id: key\n      shell: bash\n      env:\n        DOCKERFILE:  ${{ inputs.dockerfile }}\n        BUILD_ARGS:  ${{ inputs.build_args }}\n        BASE_DIGEST: ${{ steps.base.outputs.digest }}\n        PREFIX:      ${{ inputs.cache_key_prefix }}\n        TAG_BASE:    ${{ inputs.tag }}\n      run: |\n        set -euo pipefail\n        if [ -z \"$PREFIX\" ]; then\n          echo \"::error::cache_key_prefix is required \u2014 see action README\"\n          exit 1\n        fi\n        SAFE_PREFIX=$(printf '%s' \"$PREFIX\" | tr '/ ' '__')\n        if [ -z \"$DOCKERFILE\" ]; then\n          HASH=\"base-${BASE_DIGEST}\"\n        else\n          DF_HASH=$(sha256sum \"$DOCKERFILE\" | cut -c1-16)\n          ARG_HASH=$(printf '%s' \"$BUILD_ARGS\" | sha256sum | cut -c1-16)\n          HASH=\"${DF_HASH}-${BASE_DIGEST}-${ARG_HASH}\"\n        fi\n        echo \"hash=$HASH\"                               >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n        echo \"tag=${TAG_BASE}:${SAFE_PREFIX}-${HASH}\"   >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n        echo \"build_scope=${SAFE_PREFIX}-buildimg\"      >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n        echo \"pull_cache_key=${SAFE_PREFIX}-pullimg-${BASE_DIGEST}\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n\n    - id: local\n      shell: bash\n      env:\n        TAG: ${{ steps.key.outputs.tag }}\n      run: |\n        if docker image inspect \"$TAG\" >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n          echo \"hit=true\"  >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n        else\n          echo \"hit=false\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n        fi\n\n    # ================================================================\n    # PATH A \u2014 dockerfile unset: pull+tag base\n    # ================================================================\n    - id: pull-cache\n      if: inputs.dockerfile == '' && steps.env.outputs.is_self_hosted != 'true' && steps.local.outputs.hit != 'true'\n      uses: actions/cache@0057852bfaa89a56745cba8c7296529d2fc39830\n      with:\n        path: /tmp/build-docker-image.tar\n        key:  ${{ steps.key.outputs.pull_cache_key }}\n\n    - name: Load pulled image from cache\n      if: inputs.dockerfile == '' && steps.local.outputs.hit != 'true' && steps.pull-cache.outputs.cache-hit == 'true'\n      shell: bash\n      env:\n        TAG: ${{ steps.key.outputs.tag }}\n      run: |\n        set -euo pipefail\n        out=$(docker load < /tmp/build-docker-image.tar)\n        echo \"$out\"\n        if ! docker image inspect \"$TAG\" >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n          src=$(printf '%s\\n' \"$out\" | sed -n -e 's/^Loaded image: //p' -e 's/^Loaded image ID: //p' | head -n1)\n          [ -n \"$src\" ] && docker tag \"$src\" \"$TAG\"\n        fi\n\n    - name: Pull base image\n      if: inputs.dockerfile == '' && steps.local.outputs.hit != 'true' && steps.pull-cache.outputs.cache-hit != 'true'\n      shell: bash\n      env:\n        BASE:           ${{ inputs.base_image }}\n        TAG:            ${{ steps.key.outputs.tag }}\n        IS_SELF_HOSTED: ${{ steps.env.outputs.is_self_hosted }}\n      run: |\n        set -euo pipefail\n        docker pull \"$BASE\"\n        docker tag \"$BASE\" \"$TAG\"\n        if [ \"$IS_SELF_HOSTED\" != \"true\" ]; then\n          docker save \"$TAG\" > /tmp/build-docker-image.tar\n        fi\n\n    # ================================================================\n    # PATH B \u2014 dockerfile set: buildx\n    # ================================================================\n    - if: inputs.dockerfile != '' && steps.local.outputs.hit != 'true'\n      uses: docker/setup-buildx-action@c47758b77c9736f4b2ef4073d4d51994fabfe349\n\n    - name: Build (github-hosted, GHA layer cache)\n      if: inputs.dockerfile != '' && steps.local.outputs.hit != 'true' && steps.env.outputs.is_self_hosted != 'true'\n      uses: docker/build-push-action@263435318d21b8e681c14492fe198d362a7d2c10\n      with:\n        context:    ${{ inputs.context }}\n        file:       ${{ inputs.dockerfile }}\n        build-args: ${{ inputs.build_args }}\n        tags:       ${{ steps.key.outputs.tag }}\n        load:       true\n        push:       false\n        cache-from: type=gha,scope=${{ steps.key.outputs.build_scope }}\n        cache-to:   type=gha,mode=max,scope=${{ steps.key.outputs.build_scope }}\n\n    - name: Build (self-hosted, docker daemon layer cache)\n      if: inputs.dockerfile != '' && steps.local.outputs.hit != 'true' && steps.env.outputs.is_self_hosted == 'true'\n      uses: docker/build-push-action@263435318d21b8e681c14492fe198d362a7d2c10\n      with:\n        context:    ${{ inputs.context }}\n        file:       ${{ inputs.dockerfile }}\n        build-args: ${{ inputs.build_args }}\n        tags:       ${{ steps.key.outputs.tag }}\n        load:       true\n        push:       false\n\n    - id: finalize\n      shell: bash\n      env:\n        TAG:       ${{ steps.key.outputs.tag }}\n        LOCAL_HIT: ${{ steps.local.outputs.hit }}\n      run: |\n        set -euo pipefail\n        DIGEST=$(docker inspect --format='{{.Id}}' \"$TAG\")\n        {\n          echo \"image=$TAG\"\n          echo \"cache_hit=$LOCAL_HIT\"\n          echo \"digest=$DIGEST\"\n        } >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n", "structuredPatch": [{"oldStart": 1, "oldLines": 7, "newStart": 1, "newLines": 9, "lines": ["-name: Build Docker Image", "+name: Ensure Docker Image", " description: |", "-  Build (or pull) a docker image with a unified interface across GitHub-hosted", "-  and self-hosted runners. Always uses Buildx for builds.", "+  Ensure a local docker image tag exists \u2014 either by pulling a base image or by", "+  building a Dockerfile on top of it \u2014 with a unified caching story across", "+  GitHub-hosted and self-hosted runners. Idempotent: a fast path skips work", "+  entirely when the content-hashed local tag already exists.", " ", "   Two paths:", "     - dockerfile unset  \u2192 pulls `base_image`, tags it locally, outputs the tag."]}], "userModified": false, "replaceAll": false}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_016QmYeEQmCkqjYfhXQptJ8P", "duration_ms": 17}}
