{"timestamp": "2026-04-24T15:16:32.059756", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Prototype of what `.github/workflows/agent.yml` looks like if the consumer owns the orchestration instead of calling the reusable workflow. This is the escape-hatch form \u2014 step-level visibility, but the consumer writes ~10x more YAML.\n\n```yaml\nname: Agent (inlined)\n\n# Prototype: same agent flow, but with the job DAG and image-prep step\n# expressed in this file rather than hidden behind a single `uses:` at the\n# job level. Consumer owns the cross-runner handoff and the upstream-pr\n# environment gate directly.\n#\n# NOT the recommended shape. Prefer `uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/workflows/coding-agent.yml@main`.\n# This version exists only to exercise step-level composition when the\n# consumer needs something the reusable workflow doesn't expose (e.g.\n# pre-pull auth to a private registry, matrix dispatch, custom env gating).\n\non:\n  workflow_dispatch:\n    inputs:\n      runner_label:\n        description: GitHub username (matches self-hosted runner label)\n        required: true\n        type: string\n      issue_number:\n        description: Issue number to work on\n        required: true\n        type: string\n\npermissions: {}   # granted per-job below\n\njobs:\n  # --- Light orchestration jobs on ubuntu-latest ----------------------------\n\n  fetch-issue:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions: { contents: read, issues: read }\n    outputs:\n      title:    ${{ steps.f.outputs.title }}\n      body_raw: ${{ steps.f.outputs.body_raw }}\n    steps:\n      - id: f\n        env:\n          GH_TOKEN:     ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\n          REPO:         ${{ github.repository }}\n          ISSUE_NUMBER: ${{ inputs.issue_number }}\n        run: |\n          J=$(gh api \"repos/$REPO/issues/$ISSUE_NUMBER\")\n          echo \"title=$(echo \"$J\" | jq -r .title)\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n          { echo \"body_raw<<EOF\"; echo \"$J\" | jq -r '.body // \"\"'; echo \"EOF\"; } >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n\n  parse-issue:\n    needs: fetch-issue\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    outputs:\n      agent_task_text:     ${{ steps.p.outputs.agent_task_text }}\n      pr_branch:           ${{ steps.p.outputs.pr_branch }}\n      base_branch:         ${{ steps.p.outputs.base_branch }}\n      timeout_secs:        ${{ steps.p.outputs.timeout_secs }}\n      model:               ${{ steps.p.outputs.model }}\n      merge_into_upstream: ${{ steps.p.outputs.merge_into_upstream }}\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@de0fac2e4500dabe0009e67214ff5f5447ce83dd\n      - id: p\n        uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/actions/parse-issue@main\n        with:\n          title:        ${{ needs.fetch-issue.outputs.title }}\n          body_raw:     ${{ needs.fetch-issue.outputs.body_raw }}\n          issue_number: ${{ inputs.issue_number }}\n\n  validate-runner:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - env:\n          GH_TOKEN:     ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\n          RUNNER_LABEL: ${{ inputs.runner_label }}\n        run: |\n          runners=$(gh api repos/${{ github.repository }}/actions/runners \\\n            --jq '.runners[] | select(.labels[].name == \"'\"$RUNNER_LABEL\"'\") | .id')\n          [ -n \"$runners\" ] || { echo \"::error::No self-hosted runner for $RUNNER_LABEL\"; exit 1; }\n\n  choose-branch:\n    needs: [parse-issue]\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    outputs:\n      branch:      ${{ steps.c.outputs.branch }}\n      base_branch: ${{ steps.c.outputs.base_branch }}\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@de0fac2e4500dabe0009e67214ff5f5447ce83dd\n      - id: gather\n        env:\n          GH_TOKEN:     ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\n          REPO:         ${{ github.repository }}\n          ISSUE_NUMBER: ${{ inputs.issue_number }}\n        run: |\n          EXISTING=$(gh api \"repos/$REPO/branches\" --paginate -q \".[].name\" \\\n            | grep -E \"^agent/$ISSUE_NUMBER(-|$)\" | head -1 || true)\n          DEFAULT=$(gh api \"repos/$REPO\" -q .default_branch)\n          echo \"existing=$EXISTING\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n          echo \"default=$DEFAULT\"   >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n      - id: c\n        uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/actions/choose-branch@main\n        with:\n          pr_branch:             ${{ needs.parse-issue.outputs.pr_branch }}\n          agent_branch_default:  ${{ needs.parse-issue.outputs.pr_branch }}\n          existing_agent_branch: ${{ steps.gather.outputs.existing }}\n          base_from_issue:       ${{ needs.parse-issue.outputs.base_branch }}\n          default_branch:        ${{ steps.gather.outputs.default }}\n\n  # --- Self-hosted: image prep + agent run ----------------------------------\n\n  # THIS is the job where step-level composition buys something: the consumer\n  # can insert `docker login` for a private base image, add a matrix, etc.\n  run-agent:\n    needs: [validate-runner, parse-issue, choose-branch]\n    runs-on: [self-hosted, \"${{ inputs.runner_label }}\"]\n    permissions: { contents: write }\n    outputs:\n      has_new_commit:  ${{ steps.detect.outputs.has_new_commit }}\n      agent_exit_code: ${{ steps.agent.outputs.exit_code }}\n      constraints_md:  ${{ steps.constraints-out.outputs.body }}\n      commit_msg:      ${{ steps.commit-msg.outputs.body }}\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@de0fac2e4500dabe0009e67214ff5f5447ce83dd\n        with:\n          fetch-depth: 0\n          persist-credentials: true\n\n      # Example of what step-level composition enables: pre-pull auth for a\n      # private base image, before ensure-docker-image pulls.\n      # - uses: docker/login-action@v3\n      #   with: { registry: ghcr.io, username: ${{ github.actor }}, password: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }} }\n\n      - id: image\n        uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/actions/ensure-docker-image@main\n        with:\n          base_image:       ghcr.io/clockwork-pilot/autopilot-ws:latest\n          # dockerfile:       Dockerfile.agent-sample   # <- optional custom image\n          tag:              autopilot-agent\n          cache_key_prefix: ${{ github.repository }}-agent-img\n\n      - name: Checkout work branch\n        env:\n          BRANCH:      ${{ needs.choose-branch.outputs.branch }}\n          BASE_BRANCH: ${{ needs.choose-branch.outputs.base_branch }}\n        run: |\n          git fetch origin\n          if git show-ref --verify --quiet \"refs/remotes/origin/$BRANCH\"; then\n            git checkout -B \"$BRANCH\" \"origin/$BRANCH\"\n          else\n            git checkout -B \"$BRANCH\" \"origin/$BASE_BRANCH\"\n          fi\n\n      - name: Prepare docker-files\n        run: |\n          : \"${DOCKER_FILES:?DOCKER_FILES not set in runner env}\"\n          mkdir -p \"$DOCKER_FILES/.credentials\" \"$DOCKER_FILES/.cargo\" \"$DOCKER_FILES/.local\"\n          [ -s \"$DOCKER_FILES/.claude.local.json\" ] || printf '{}\\n' > \"$DOCKER_FILES/.claude.local.json\"\n\n      - id: agent\n        env:\n          MODEL:        ${{ needs.parse-issue.outputs.model }}\n          TIMEOUT_SECS: ${{ needs.parse-issue.outputs.timeout_secs }}\n          PROMPT:       ${{ needs.parse-issue.outputs.agent_task_text }}\n          AGENT_IMAGE:  ${{ steps.image.outputs.image }}\n        run: |\n          set +e\n          bash .github/scripts/run-in-docker-claude.sh\n          echo \"exit_code=$?\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n\n      - id: constraints\n        if: always()\n        env:\n          AGENT_IMAGE: ${{ steps.image.outputs.image }}\n        run: |\n          set +e\n          bash .github/scripts/run-in-docker-no-claude.sh \\\n            '$PLUGIN_ROOT/bin/check --dry-run --full-report' \\\n            > /tmp/constraints.md 2>&1\n          echo \"exit_code=$?\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n\n      - id: constraints-out\n        if: always()\n        run: |\n          { echo \"body<<EOF\"; cat /tmp/constraints.md; echo \"EOF\"; } >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n\n      - id: head-before\n        if: always()\n        run: echo \"sha=$(git rev-parse HEAD)\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n\n      - if: always() && steps.agent.outputs.exit_code == '0' && steps.constraints.outputs.exit_code == '0'\n        env:\n          MODEL:       ${{ needs.parse-issue.outputs.model }}\n          PROMPT:      commit changes\n          AGENT_IMAGE: ${{ steps.image.outputs.image }}\n        run: bash .github/scripts/run-in-docker-claude.sh --allow-git-commit || true\n\n      - id: detect\n        if: always()\n        run: |\n          if [ \"${{ steps.head-before.outputs.sha }}\" != \"$(git rev-parse HEAD)\" ]; then\n            echo \"has_new_commit=true\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n          else\n            echo \"has_new_commit=false\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n          fi\n\n      - if: steps.detect.outputs.has_new_commit == 'true'\n        run: git push origin \"${{ needs.choose-branch.outputs.branch }}\"\n\n      - id: commit-msg\n        if: steps.detect.outputs.has_new_commit == 'true'\n        run: |\n          { echo \"body<<EOF\"; git log -1 --pretty=%B HEAD; echo \"EOF\"; } >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n\n  # --- Back to ubuntu-latest for PR + commenting ----------------------------\n\n  open-pr:\n    needs: [fetch-issue, parse-issue, choose-branch, run-agent]\n    if: |\n      always() && needs.run-agent.result != 'skipped' && needs.run-agent.result != 'cancelled'\n      && (needs.parse-issue.outputs.merge_into_upstream != 'true'\n          || needs.run-agent.outputs.has_new_commit != 'true')\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions: { pull-requests: write, issues: write }\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@de0fac2e4500dabe0009e67214ff5f5447ce83dd\n        with: { persist-credentials: false }\n\n      - if: needs.run-agent.outputs.has_new_commit == 'true' && needs.parse-issue.outputs.merge_into_upstream != 'true'\n        uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/actions/create-pr@main\n        with:\n          gh-token:    ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\n          pr-repo:     ${{ github.repository }}\n          pr-head:     ${{ needs.choose-branch.outputs.branch }}\n          pr-title:    ${{ needs.fetch-issue.outputs.title }}\n          issue-ref:   ${{ github.repository }}#${{ inputs.issue_number }}\n          commit-body: ${{ needs.run-agent.outputs.commit_msg }}\n\n      - uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/actions/comment-agent-result@main\n        with:\n          gh-token:        ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\n          repo:            ${{ github.repository }}\n          issue-number:    ${{ inputs.issue_number }}\n          constraints-md:  ${{ needs.run-agent.outputs.constraints_md }}\n          has-new-commit:  ${{ needs.run-agent.outputs.has_new_commit }}\n          agent-exit-code: ${{ needs.run-agent.outputs.agent_exit_code }}\n\n  # Environment-gated: UPSTREAM_PR_TOKEN never enters the self-hosted runner.\n  open-upstream-pr:\n    needs: [fetch-issue, parse-issue, choose-branch, run-agent]\n    if: needs.run-agent.outputs.has_new_commit == 'true' && needs.parse-issue.outputs.merge_into_upstream == 'true'\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    environment: upstream-pr\n    permissions: { contents: read, issues: write }\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@de0fac2e4500dabe0009e67214ff5f5447ce83dd\n        with: { persist-credentials: false }\n      # \u2026 resolve upstream repo, open cross-repo PR, comment on issue \u2026\n      # (omitted; mirrors open-upstream-pr job in coding-agent.yml)\n```\n\n### Takeaways\n\n- **Length**: ~180 lines vs 8 in the current `agent.yml`. All of that is orchestration consumers would otherwise not own.\n- **What step-level composition buys**:\n  - The `docker login` comment in `run-agent` \u2014 inject pre-pull auth.\n  - Tweak matrices, conditions, per-job permissions without touching autopilot.\n  - Replace any composite-action call with a custom variant.\n- **What it costs**:\n  - Every autopilot version bump may require updating this file \u2014 no one-line `@main` \u2192 `@v2` ref swap at the job level; the consumer owns the job graph.\n  - Cross-runner handoffs (`ubuntu-latest` \u2192 `self-hosted` \u2192 `ubuntu-latest`) expressed explicitly via `needs:`.\n  - `upstream-pr` environment gating is now the consumer's responsibility \u2014 easy to get wrong (missing `environment:` leaks the PAT).\n\n### When you'd actually do this\n\n- You need pre-pull auth to a private registry for the base image.\n- You want to run the agent in a matrix (multiple models, multiple issue numbers).\n- You want to inject your own steps between `ensure-docker-image` and `run-in-docker-claude.sh` (e.g. warm a cache dir, mount secrets).\n- You're forking autopilot enough that you're customizing the flow.\n\nOtherwise the 8-line reusable-workflow caller is the right shape."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
