{"timestamp": "2026-04-24T15:20:10.436295", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "data": {"session_id": "b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "so what is the real options to add a ensure-docker-image step, regardless of how it implemented as action or workflow. \njobs:\n  run:\n    uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/workflows/coding-agent.yml@main\n    with:\n      runner_label:     ${{ inputs.runner_label }}\n      issue_number:     ${{ inputs.issue_number }}\n      dockerfile:       Dockerfile.agent-sample\n      cache_key_prefix: ${{ github.repository }}-agent-img\n    secrets:\n      UPSTREAM_PR_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.UPSTREAM_PR_TOKEN }}\n", "session_title": "autopilot-selftest"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-24T15:21:07.921039", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Four real options, each with a different trade:\n\n### Option 1 \u2014 Status quo (current)\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  run:\n    uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/workflows/coding-agent.yml@main\n    with:\n      dockerfile:       Dockerfile.agent-sample\n      cache_key_prefix: ${{ github.repository }}-agent-img\n      ...\n```\n\nThe `ensure-docker-image` step lives inside `coding-agent.yml`'s `prepare-image` job. From the caller's file: invisible. From the **run log**: visible as the `prepare-image` job \u2192 \"Ensure Docker Image\" step, with cache hit/miss legible.\n\n**Trade**: zero consumer code; image prep is not a peer step of the reusable workflow call, only a child step inside one of its jobs.\n\n---\n\n### Option 2 \u2014 Expose `ensure-docker-image.yml` as a reusable-workflow shim, caller composes two jobs\n\nAdd a thin upstream reusable workflow that wraps the action so it can be called at job level:\n\n```yaml\n# autopilot/.github/workflows/ensure-docker-image.yml (new)\non: { workflow_call: { inputs: { ... }, outputs: { image: { value: ... } } } }\njobs:\n  ensure:\n    runs-on: [self-hosted, \"${{ inputs.runner_label }}\"]\n    outputs: { image: ${{ steps.e.outputs.image }} }\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@...\n      - id: e\n        uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/actions/ensure-docker-image@main\n        with: { ... }\n```\n\nConsumer caller:\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  image:\n    uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/workflows/ensure-docker-image.yml@main\n    with:\n      runner_label:     ${{ inputs.runner_label }}\n      dockerfile:       Dockerfile.agent-sample\n      cache_key_prefix: ${{ github.repository }}-agent-img\n\n  run:\n    needs: image\n    uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/workflows/coding-agent.yml@main\n    with:\n      runner_label: ${{ inputs.runner_label }}\n      issue_number: ${{ inputs.issue_number }}\n      agent_image:  ${{ needs.image.outputs.image }}   # pass the prepared tag\n    secrets:\n      UPSTREAM_PR_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.UPSTREAM_PR_TOKEN }}\n```\n\n`coding-agent.yml`'s `prepare-image` job becomes a no-op when `agent_image` is already resolved (fast-path: local tag present on the same self-hosted runner \u2192 skip).\n\n**Requires**: both jobs land on the **same** self-hosted runner (so the local docker tag from job 1 is visible to job 2). If your runner_label maps to a single runner, this holds naturally. With a pool of runners sharing the label, this breaks \u2014 solve either by pushing to a registry (next option) or by narrowing the label.\n\n**Trade**: two visible job-level `uses:` entries in the caller; caller can insert other jobs between them; requires same-runner assumption or a registry.\n\n---\n\n### Option 3 \u2014 Consumer builds + pushes their own image, passes via `agent_image`\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  image:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    outputs: { ref: ${{ steps.push.outputs.ref }} }\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@...\n      - uses: docker/login-action@v3\n        with: { registry: ghcr.io, username: ${{ github.actor }}, password: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }} }\n      - id: push\n        uses: docker/build-push-action@v6\n        with:\n          file: Dockerfile.agent-sample\n          tags: ghcr.io/${{ github.repository }}/agent:${{ github.sha }}\n          push: true\n          cache-from: type=gha,scope=agent-img\n          cache-to:   type=gha,mode=max,scope=agent-img\n      - run: echo \"ref=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository }}/agent:${{ github.sha }}\" >> $GITHUB_OUTPUT\n\n  run:\n    needs: image\n    uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/workflows/coding-agent.yml@main\n    with:\n      runner_label: ${{ inputs.runner_label }}\n      issue_number: ${{ inputs.issue_number }}\n      agent_image:  ${{ needs.image.outputs.ref }}\n    secrets:\n      UPSTREAM_PR_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.UPSTREAM_PR_TOKEN }}\n```\n\nThe `dockerfile:` input on `coding-agent.yml` is unused \u2014 the consumer did the build themselves.\n\n**Trade**: works across runner pools and registries; consumer owns login + push; cost is the registry roundtrip on every run (mitigated by `cache-from/cache-to`). The `dockerfile:` / `cache_key_prefix:` inputs on `coding-agent.yml` become redundant.\n\n---\n\n### Option 4 \u2014 Split `coding-agent.yml` into two reusable workflows\n\nUpstream refactor: extract `prepare-agent-image.yml` (self-hosted, outputs `image`) and a trimmed `run-coding-agent.yml` (accepts `image` input, does the rest). Consumer wires two `uses:`.\n\nSame caller shape as Option 2 but the split is load-bearing upstream \u2014 `prepare-agent-image.yml` always runs on self-hosted, `run-coding-agent.yml` runs the full rest-of-DAG. Consumers can swap either side independently, reuse the image-prep workflow outside the agent context, etc.\n\n**Trade**: cleanest composition story long-term; invasive change to `coding-agent.yml`; changes the versioning contract (consumers now pin two refs).\n\n---\n\n### Comparison\n\n| | Caller LoC | Visible step at caller level | Works with runner pool | Registry needed | Upstream churn |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 1. Status quo | ~8 | No (in run graph only) | Yes | No | None |\n| 2. `ensure-docker-image.yml` shim | ~15 | Yes (as a job) | Same-runner only | No | Small (new file) |\n| 3. Consumer push + `agent_image` | ~25 | Yes (as a job) | Yes | Yes | None |\n| 4. Split `coding-agent.yml` | ~15 | Yes (as a job) | Same-runner only | No | Large |\n\n### Recommendation\n\nIf the motivation is **visibility**: Option 1 already gives you a visible step inside a visible job (`prepare-image \u2192 Ensure Docker Image`). The caller file is terse because the orchestration is owned upstream \u2014 that's the reusable-workflow contract working as designed.\n\nIf the motivation is **consumer control** (pre-pull auth, custom build, matrix over Dockerfiles): Option 3. Uses existing inputs, no upstream change, works across any runner topology.\n\nOption 2 is the middle ground but the same-runner assumption makes it fragile. Option 4 is the \"right\" long-term architecture but an expensive move to make today."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
