{"timestamp": "2026-04-24T15:24:23.155267", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "data": {"session_id": "b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "is it possible to make coding-agent an action?", "session_title": "autopilot-selftest"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-24T15:25:19.441476", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Not as *one* action, for the reasons I laid out before (multi-runner, per-job env, per-job permissions, `secrets:` block). But the inner loop \u2014 image prep + agent execution + constraint check + commit/push \u2014 is single-runner (self-hosted) and **can** collapse into a composite action. The orchestration around it stays as consumer-owned jobs.\n\nHere's what that split would look like.\n\n### New composite action \u2014 `run-agent` (self-hosted, single-job)\n\n```yaml\n# autopilot/.github/actions/run-agent/action.yml\nname: Run Coding Agent\ndescription: |\n  Single-runner inner loop: ensure image \u2192 checkout work branch \u2192 run Claude\n  \u2192 run constraints \u2192 commit/push. Must run on a self-hosted runner labeled\n  with the target user's GitHub login.\n\ninputs:\n  issue_number:        { required: true }\n  branch:              { required: true }\n  base_branch:         { required: true }\n  agent_task_text:     { required: true }\n  model:               { required: true }\n  timeout_secs:        { required: true }\n  base_image:          { required: false, default: ghcr.io/clockwork-pilot/autopilot-ws:latest }\n  dockerfile:          { required: false, default: \"\" }\n  build_args:          { required: false, default: \"\" }\n  cache_key_prefix:    { required: true }\n\noutputs:\n  has_new_commit:  { value: ${{ steps.detect.outputs.has_new_commit }} }\n  agent_exit_code: { value: ${{ steps.agent.outputs.exit_code }} }\n  constraints_md:  { value: ${{ steps.cm.outputs.body }} }\n  commit_msg:      { value: ${{ steps.cmsg.outputs.body }} }\n\nruns:\n  using: composite\n  steps:\n    - uses: actions/checkout@...\n      with: { fetch-depth: 0, persist-credentials: true }\n\n    - id: image\n      uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/actions/ensure-docker-image@main\n      with:\n        base_image:       ${{ inputs.base_image }}\n        dockerfile:       ${{ inputs.dockerfile }}\n        build_args:       ${{ inputs.build_args }}\n        tag:              autopilot-agent\n        cache_key_prefix: ${{ inputs.cache_key_prefix }}\n\n    # ... checkout work branch, prepare docker-files, run Claude,\n    #     run constraints, commit, detect new commit, push ...\n    # (all the existing steps that live in run-agent job today)\n```\n\n### New composite action \u2014 `open-agent-pr` (ubuntu-latest, single-job)\n\nWraps `create-pr` + `comment-agent-result`. Thin.\n\n### Consumer caller becomes\n\n```yaml\nname: Agent\n\non:\n  workflow_dispatch:\n    inputs:\n      runner_label: { required: true, type: string }\n      issue_number: { required: true, type: string }\n\njobs:\n  fetch-issue:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    outputs: { title: ..., body_raw: ... }\n    steps: [ gh api repos/.../issues/<n> ]\n\n  parse-issue:\n    needs: fetch-issue\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    outputs: { ..., merge_into_upstream: ... }\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@...\n      - uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/actions/parse-issue@main\n        with: { title: ..., body_raw: ..., issue_number: ... }\n\n  choose-branch:\n    needs: [parse-issue]\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    outputs: { branch: ..., base_branch: ... }\n    steps: [ ... gh api + choose-branch action ... ]\n\n  agent:\n    needs: [parse-issue, choose-branch]\n    runs-on: [self-hosted, \"${{ inputs.runner_label }}\"]\n    permissions: { contents: write }\n    outputs: { has_new_commit: ..., constraints_md: ..., ... }\n    steps:\n      # The consumer can now insert pre-steps here (docker login, matrix, etc.)\n      - uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/actions/run-agent@main\n        with:\n          issue_number:     ${{ inputs.issue_number }}\n          branch:           ${{ needs.choose-branch.outputs.branch }}\n          base_branch:      ${{ needs.choose-branch.outputs.base_branch }}\n          agent_task_text:  ${{ needs.parse-issue.outputs.agent_task_text }}\n          model:            ${{ needs.parse-issue.outputs.model }}\n          timeout_secs:     ${{ needs.parse-issue.outputs.timeout_secs }}\n          dockerfile:       Dockerfile.agent-sample\n          cache_key_prefix: ${{ github.repository }}-agent-img\n\n  open-pr:\n    needs: [fetch-issue, parse-issue, choose-branch, agent]\n    if: needs.parse-issue.outputs.merge_into_upstream != 'true' || needs.agent.outputs.has_new_commit != 'true'\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions: { pull-requests: write, issues: write }\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@...\n      - uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/actions/open-agent-pr@main\n        with: { ... }\n\n  open-upstream-pr:\n    needs: [fetch-issue, parse-issue, choose-branch, agent]\n    if: needs.agent.outputs.has_new_commit == 'true' && needs.parse-issue.outputs.merge_into_upstream == 'true'\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    environment: upstream-pr\n    steps: [ ... open-upstream-pr logic ... ]\n```\n\n### What this trades\n\n**Wins**:\n- Consumer can inject steps around `run-agent` (pre-pull auth, matrix, custom env).\n- `ensure-docker-image` is a step inside `run-agent`, still visible in the run log, and the consumer *can* run it explicitly themselves before `run-agent` if they want it as a peer step (action's fast-path skips the duplicate work).\n- No reusable-workflow-vs-step conflict: everything is step-level.\n- Individual pieces (`run-agent`, `open-agent-pr`) reusable outside the standard flow.\n\n**Losses**:\n- Consumer caller goes from ~8 lines to ~80 lines.\n- Consumer now owns the job DAG and the cross-runner handoffs.\n- Consumer now owns the `environment: upstream-pr` gate \u2014 the single biggest security footgun in the whole flow.\n- `@main` \u2192 `@v2` bumps are no longer a one-line edit; the consumer may need to adjust the DAG if job interfaces change.\n\n### Honest recommendation\n\nOffer **both**:\n- **Reusable workflow** (`coding-agent.yml`) as the default, documented path \u2014 8-line caller, all orchestration owned upstream.\n- **Composite actions** (`run-agent`, `open-agent-pr`) as the advanced/customization path for consumers who need step-level control.\n\nThe reusable workflow can be implemented *in terms of* the composite actions \u2014 so there's one source of truth and the two surfaces stay in sync:\n\n```yaml\n# autopilot/.github/workflows/coding-agent.yml (refactored)\njobs:\n  # ... fetch-issue, parse-issue, validate-runner, choose-branch ... (unchanged)\n  agent:\n    runs-on: [self-hosted, \"${{ inputs.runner_label }}\"]\n    steps:\n      - uses: ./.github/actions/run-agent\n        with: { ... }\n  open-pr:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: ./.github/actions/open-agent-pr\n        with: { ... }\n  open-upstream-pr:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    environment: upstream-pr\n    steps: [ ... ]\n```\n\nThis is the cleanest answer: \"coding-agent can't be one composite action, but its moving parts can, and the reusable workflow becomes a thin orchestrator over them.\""}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
