{"timestamp": "2026-04-24T15:44:51.712820", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "data": {"session_id": "b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "why not?   # .github/workflows/agent.yml\n  jobs:\n    image:\n      uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/workflows/ensure-docker-image.yml@main\n      with:                                                       \n        runner_label:     ${{ inputs.runner_label }}\n        base_image:       ghcr.io/clockwork-pilot/autopilot-ws:latest\n        dockerfile:       Dockerfile.agent-sample                  # <-- only here\n        cache_key_prefix: ${{ github.repository }}-agent-img       # <-- only here\n                                                                                                                                                                        \n    run:                                                          \n      needs: image\n      uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/workflows/coding-agent.yml@main\n      with:\n        runner_label:     ${{ inputs.runner_label }}              \n        issue_number:     ${{ inputs.issue_number }}\n        docker_image:     ${{ needs.image.outputs.docker_image }}\n      secrets:\n        UPSTREAM_PR_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.UPSTREAM_PR_TOKEN }}\n", "session_title": "autopilot-selftest"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-24T15:45:49.979572", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "You're right \u2014 that's the better design. Pass the **built image ref** itself, not the ingredients. Let me reconcile.\n\n### What needs to change upstream\n\n`coding-agent.yml` needs a new input that **bypasses its internal `prepare-image` work entirely** when a pre-built image is handed in:\n\n```yaml\n# autopilot/.github/workflows/coding-agent.yml\non:\n  workflow_call:\n    inputs:\n      # ... existing ...\n      docker_image:\n        description: |\n          Pre-built local docker tag. When set, prepare-image skips\n          ensure-docker-image and uses this ref directly. Mutually exclusive\n          with `dockerfile:` / `cache_key_prefix:` \u2014 those inputs are ignored.\n          Requires both the caller's image-prep job and this workflow's\n          prepare-image/run-agent jobs to land on the SAME self-hosted runner\n          (local tags don't cross docker daemons).\n        required: false\n        type: string\n        default: \"\"\n\njobs:\n  prepare-image:\n    needs: [validate-runner, image-digest]\n    runs-on: [self-hosted, \"${{ inputs.runner_label }}\"]\n    outputs:\n      image: ${{ steps.resolve.outputs.image }}\n    steps:\n      - id: resolve\n        if: inputs.docker_image != ''\n        run: echo \"image=${{ inputs.docker_image }}\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n\n      # fallback: existing ensure-docker-image path when docker_image is unset\n      - if: inputs.docker_image == '' && inputs.dockerfile != ''\n        uses: actions/checkout@...\n      - if: inputs.docker_image == ''\n        id: build\n        uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/actions/ensure-docker-image@main\n        with:\n          base_image:       ${{ inputs.agent_image != '' && inputs.agent_image || needs.image-digest.outputs.image }}\n          dockerfile:       ${{ inputs.dockerfile }}\n          build_args:       ${{ inputs.build_args }}\n          tag:              autopilot-agent\n          cache_key_prefix: ${{ inputs.cache_key_prefix }}\n      - if: inputs.docker_image == ''\n        run: echo \"image=${{ steps.build.outputs.image }}\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n```\n\nNow prepare-image is **genuinely a no-op** (one `echo`) when the consumer pre-built, not a fast-path hit. And `dockerfile:`/`cache_key_prefix:` inputs on `coding-agent.yml` become optional fallbacks rather than co-required.\n\n### Your caller is correct and minimal\n\n```yaml\n# .github/workflows/agent.yml\njobs:\n  image:\n    uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/workflows/ensure-docker-image.yml@main\n    with:\n      runner_label:     ${{ inputs.runner_label }}\n      base_image:       ghcr.io/clockwork-pilot/autopilot-ws:latest\n      dockerfile:       Dockerfile.agent-sample\n      cache_key_prefix: ${{ github.repository }}-agent-img\n\n  run:\n    needs: image\n    uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/workflows/coding-agent.yml@main\n    with:\n      runner_label: ${{ inputs.runner_label }}\n      issue_number: ${{ inputs.issue_number }}\n      docker_image: ${{ needs.image.outputs.docker_image }}\n    secrets:\n      UPSTREAM_PR_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.UPSTREAM_PR_TOKEN }}\n```\n\nOne source of truth per value. `coding-agent.yml` knows nothing about Dockerfiles when you use this mode \u2014 it's handed an image and runs.\n\n### `ensure-docker-image.yml` output naming\n\nYour caller uses `${{ needs.image.outputs.docker_image }}`. I'd name the output `image` (matches the action's output) and the `coding-agent.yml` input `docker_image` \u2014 or align both on one name. Either choice is fine; pick once and stick with it:\n\n```yaml\n# ensure-docker-image.yml\noutputs:\n  docker_image:\n    value: ${{ jobs.ensure.outputs.image }}\n```\n\n### Why this beats the echo approach\n\n| | Echo inputs | Pass built image ref (your proposal) |\n|---|---|---|\n| Values declared in caller | Once each (with echoed outputs) | Once each |\n| `coding-agent.yml` internal prep | fast-path hit (~2s no-op) | literal echo (~0.1s) |\n| `coding-agent.yml` knows about Dockerfile | Yes (redundant inputs) | No (opaque ref) |\n| Input surface of `coding-agent.yml` | grows | shrinks |\n| Works across runner pool | No (same constraint) | No (same constraint) |\n| Conceptual clarity | Two workflows each re-deriving the same tag | One workflow produces a tag, one consumes it |\n\n### The unchanged caveat\n\nBoth workflows must land on the **same self-hosted runner** for the local tag to cross the job boundary. This is true in both designs \u2014 but in your design it's load-bearing (the consumer's ref is literally passed in), while in the echo design it's obscured (both workflows re-derive a matching tag via fast-path). Failing same-runner: your design errors at `docker run` with \"image not found\" (loud, fast); echo design silently rebuilds (quiet, wasteful). Your failure mode is better too.\n\n### Want me to implement this?\n\nThree changes:\n1. Add `autopilot/.github/workflows/ensure-docker-image.yml` reusable workflow.\n2. Add `docker_image:` input to `coding-agent.yml`; make `prepare-image` short-circuit when set.\n3. Update `.github/workflows/agent.yml` + `agent-with-dockerfile.yml` in selftest to the two-job shape.\n\nSay the word."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
