{"timestamp": "2026-04-24T15:47:20.653663", "event": "Write", "data": {"session_id": "b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "PreToolUse", "tool_name": "Write", "tool_input": {"file_path": "/workspace/autopilot/.github/workflows/ensure-docker-image.yml", "content": "name: Ensure Docker Image\n\n# Reusable workflow: thin wrapper around the ensure-docker-image composite\n# action, so callers can hoist image preparation into its own job when they\n# want it visible at the caller level (matrix, approval gate, handoff to\n# another reusable workflow).\n#\n# Runs on [self-hosted, <runner_label>] so the produced local docker tag is\n# on the same daemon that downstream agent/check jobs will use. If the caller\n# passes `docker_image` downstream, both jobs MUST land on the same runner\n# (local tags don't cross docker daemons).\n\non:\n  workflow_call:\n    inputs:\n      runner_label:\n        description: GitHub username (matches self-hosted runner label).\n        required: true\n        type: string\n      base_image:\n        description: Base image ref. Pulled and tagged locally; also used as the FROM contract if a dockerfile is supplied.\n        required: true\n        type: string\n      dockerfile:\n        description: Optional path to a Dockerfile to build on top of base_image. Leave empty to only pull+tag base_image.\n        required: false\n        type: string\n        default: \"\"\n      build_args:\n        description: Newline-separated KEY=VALUE, forwarded to the builder.\n        required: false\n        type: string\n        default: \"\"\n      cache_key_prefix:\n        description: REQUIRED. See .github/actions/ensure-docker-image/README.md.\n        required: true\n        type: string\n      tag:\n        description: Local tag base (a content hash is appended).\n  