rk", "-# ends up with after adopting autopilot from the Marketplace. Consumes", "-# coding-agent.yml as a reusable workflow via a cross-repo `uses:` ref \u2014", "-# never a local `./` path. The repo boundary is what enforces this: a", "-# `./` reference simply cannot resolve across repos, so the separation", "-# between implementation (autopilot) and consumer (autopilot-selftest) is", "-# mechanical, not conventional.", "+# Consumer caller workflow: demonstrates the two-job shape where image", "+# preparation is hoisted into its own visible job (via ensure-docker-image.yml)", "+# and its output is handed to coding-agent.yml as a pre-built ref.", " #", "-# Manual trigger only \u2014 pick an existing issue number and the runner label", "-# (your GitHub username) matching your self-hosted runner. Apply the normal", "-# merge_into_upstream/timeout/model frontmatter on the issue as usual; this", "-# file just hands off to coding-agent.yml.", "+# Both reusable workflows' self-hosted jobs share the same runner_label, so", "+# the local docker tag produced in the `image` job is visible to the", "+# prepare-image / run-agent jobs inside coding-agent.yml.", " #", "-# PR testing loop: when there is a PR open against autopilot, flip the", "-# `@main` ref below to `@<pr-branch>` to run this repo's pinned test", "-# issues against the in-flight implementation, then flip back to `@main`", "-# on merge. This is the same one-line edit a downstream contributor makes", "-# to smoke-test a version bump, so the flow is dogfooded by design.", "+# PR testing loop: flip the `@main` refs to `@<pr-branch>` to smoke-test", "+# against an in-flight autopilot PR, then flip back on merge.", " ", " on:", "   workflow_dispatch:"]}, {"oldStart": 37, "oldLines": 11, "newStart": 29, "newLines": 20, "lines": ["   issues: write", " ", " jobs:", "-  run:", "-    uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/workflows/coding-agent.yml@main", "+  image:", "+    uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/workflows