{"timestamp": "2026-04-24T16:08:05.114628", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/b6280e45-69a0-4be3-81ec-a2d05890506f.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace/autopilot", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "You're right. Let me audit and propose the fix before implementing \u2014 I don't want to edit something you'd revert again.\n\n### Current state (hardcoded occurrences in autopilot)\n\n| File | Line | What |\n|---|---|---|\n| `.github/workflows/check-constraints.yml` | 54 | `base_image: ghcr.io/clockwork-pilot/autopilot-ws:latest` passed to ensure-docker-image |\n| `.github/actions/check-constraints/action.yml` | 20 | `docker tag \"$IMAGE\" ghcr.io/clockwork-pilot/autopilot-ws:cached` (retag hack) |\n| `.github/actions/check-constraints/action.yml` | 25 | `AGENT_IMAGE: ghcr.io/clockwork-pilot/autopilot-ws:cached` (env for shell script) |\n| `.github/workflows/image-digest.yml` | 9 | `default: ghcr.io/clockwork-pilot/autopilot-ws` (input default) |\n| `.github/workflows/coding-agent.yml` | \u2014 | calls `image-digest.yml` without passing `image_repo` \u2192 inherits above default |\n| `.github/scripts/run-in-docker-no-claude.sh` | 13 | `: \"${AGENT_IMAGE:=ghcr.io/clockwork-pilot/autopilot-ws:latest}\"` fallback |\n\nPlus docstrings/comments.\n\n### Proposal \u2014 one flowing input, one optional default\n\nMake `base_image` a first-class workflow input on both reusable workflows, forwarded through internally. No hardcoded fallbacks sprinkled elsewhere; the single default lives at the workflow input layer (where consumers can see and override it).\n\nChanges:\n\n1. **`coding-agent.yml`**: add `base_image` input (default `ghcr.io/clockwork-pilot/autopilot-ws:latest`). Pass it to the `image-digest` call and to the internal `ensure-docker-image` step.\n2. **`image-digest.yml`**: remove the hardcoded default on `image_repo` input \u2014 require the caller to pass it. (Only autopilot itself calls this, so safe.)\n3. **`check-constraints.yml`**: add `base_image` input with same default. Pass it to `ensure-docker-image`.\n4. **`check-constraints` action**: drop the retag-to-`autopilot-ws:cached` hack. Pass `inputs.image` directly to `run-in-docker-no-claude.sh` as `AGENT_IMAGE`. No mention of autopilot-ws in the action.\n5. **`run-in-docker-no-claude.sh`**: drop the fallback default. If `AGENT_IMAGE` is unset, fail loud. Callers always set it.\n6. **Consumer workflows** (`autopilot-selftest/.github/workflows/agent.yml`, `check-constraints.yml`): already pass `base_image` explicitly \u2014 unchanged.\n\nNet: `ghcr.io/clockwork-pilot/autopilot-ws` appears exactly **once** per reusable workflow file (the input default), and in docs/comments. Zero appearances in actions or scripts.\n\n### Trade-off\n\nStep 2 (removing `image_repo` default on `image-digest.yml`) is a mild breaking change if anyone calls `image-digest.yml` directly. I can keep its default instead if you prefer \u2014 then it appears twice (`coding-agent.yml` default + `image-digest.yml` default), which is still better than today's 6 places.\n\n### Question before implementing\n\n- **OK with the \"one input per reusable workflow\" default + no hardcoded fallbacks in actions/scripts** shape?\n- **Remove `image-digest.yml`'s default** (stricter, one breaking change) or **keep it** (less strict, two places mention the ref)?\n\nSay go with your preferences."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
