{"timestamp": "2026-04-25T08:45:28.690588", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "9bc3bb23-3a03-4c50-bc77-cab9263aed1b", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/9bc3bb23-3a03-4c50-bc77-cab9263aed1b.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace/autopilot", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "GitHub requires workflow YAMLs to live directly in `.github/workflows/`, so `act-step-runner.yml` itself can't move into a subfolder. But we can create `.github/act-step-runner/` (a sibling of `actions/`, `scripts/`, `workflows/`) and move its two related scripts there:\n\n- `.github/scripts/act-step-dispatch.sh` \u2192 `.github/act-step-runner/dispatch.sh`\n- `.github/scripts/test/run-act-step-checks.sh` \u2192 `.github/act-step-runner/run-checks.sh`\n\nThen update the workflow's `run:` step, the test runner's internal call to the dispatcher, and the two constraints whose `cmd` invokes those scripts (`dispatcher_fails_on_missing_step`, `*_via_action`).\n\nTradeoff: it improves locality (everything for this runner in one place) but adds a non-standard top-level folder under `.github/`. Alternative: put it under `.github/actions/act-step-runner/` to mirror the convention we just established for fixtures, even though it isn't a composite action.\n\nWant me to proceed with `.github/act-step-runner/`, or prefer the `.github/actions/act-step-runner/` layout?"}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
