{"timestamp": "2026-04-25T09:04:02.896018", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "a2e5b048-da64-4878-9ce6-db1206e63e36", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/a2e5b048-da64-4878-9ce6-db1206e63e36.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Where should the value come from in the selftest? On the agent runs the var is set in the runner's systemd env, but `/workspace/.github/workflows/check-constraints.yml` runs on `ubuntu-latest` so nothing sets it there.\n\nA few options:\n1. Source it from a repo variable: `CLAUDE_EXTRA_DOCKER_ARGS: ${{ vars.CLAUDE_EXTRA_DOCKER_ARGS }}`\n2. Hardcode a smoke value to prove the wire works\n3. Switch the selftest check job to `runs-on: ${{ inputs.runner_label }}` (self-hosted) so it inherits naturally\n\nWhich do you want?"}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
