{"timestamp": "2026-04-25T09:06:44.757260", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "a2e5b048-da64-4878-9ce6-db1206e63e36", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/a2e5b048-da64-4878-9ce6-db1206e63e36.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Both do, but in different places:\n\n- **`.github/workflows/agent.yml`** \u2192 delegates to `coding-agent.yml`, which on the **self-hosted runner** runs:\n  - `run-in-docker-claude.sh` (agent step + commit step) \u2014 coding-agent.yml:307, 353\n  - `run-in-docker-no-claude.sh` (constraint check `--dry-run`) \u2014 coding-agent.yml:324\n  \n  Self-hosted \u21d2 `CLAUDE_EXTRA_DOCKER_ARGS` is already inherited from the runner's systemd env. No selftest change needed.\n\n- **`.github/workflows/check-constraints.yml`** \u2192 uses the `check-constraints` composite action on **`ubuntu-latest`**, which calls:\n  - `run-in-docker-no-claude.sh` \u2014 check-constraints/action.yml:21\n  \n  GitHub-hosted \u21d2 env var is **not** set, so propagation needs an explicit source (the question from my previous turn).\n\nSo the selftest change is only meaningful for `check-constraints.yml`."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
