{"timestamp": "2026-04-25T09:07:44.099251", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "a2e5b048-da64-4878-9ce6-db1206e63e36", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/a2e5b048-da64-4878-9ce6-db1206e63e36.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Here's the wiring through both layers. The composite action just needs to forward the env (so callers can set it at the step level); the reusable workflow exposes an input that flows down to the action.\n\n**1. Composite action \u2014 explicitly forward the env var** (`autopilot/.github/actions/check-constraints/action.yml`):\n\n```yaml\ninputs:\n  image:\n    description: ...\n    required: true\n  command:\n    description: ...\n    required: false\n    default: check_spec_constraints.py\n  extra_docker_args:\n    description: Extra args spliced into `docker run` (forwarded as CLAUDE_EXTRA_DOCKER_ARGS).\n    required: false\n    default: \"\"\n\nruns:\n  using: composite\n  steps:\n    - name: Run check inside image\n      shell: bash\n      env:\n        AGENT_IMAGE: ${{ inputs.image }}\n        CMD: ${{ inputs.command }}\n        CLAUDE_EXTRA_DOCKER_ARGS: ${{ inputs.extra_docker_args }}\n      run: bash \"$GITHUB_ACTION_PATH/../../scripts/run-in-docker-no-claude.sh\" \"$CMD\"\n```\n\n**2. Reusable workflow \u2014 add an input and pass it through** (`autopilot/.github/workflows/check-constraints.yml`):\n\n```yaml\non:\n  workflow_call:\n    inputs:\n      # ... existing inputs ...\n      extra_docker_args:\n        description: Extra args spliced into `docker run` for the check container.\n        required: false\n        type: string\n        default: \"\"\n\njobs:\n  check-constraints:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      # ... checkout + ensure-docker-image ...\n      - uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/actions/check-constraints@main\n        with:\n          image: ${{ steps.image.outputs.image }}\n          extra_docker_args: ${{ inputs.extra_docker_args }}\n```\n\n**3. Caller (selftest)** \u2014 either invoke the reusable workflow with the input, or (since the selftest calls the action directly) set the env on the step:\n\n```yaml\n# /workspace/.github/workflows/check-constraints.yml\n- uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/actions/check-constraints@main\n  with:\n    image: ${{ steps.image.outputs.image }}\n    extra_docker_args: ${{ vars.CLAUDE_EXTRA_DOCKER_ARGS }}\n```\n\nWant me to apply these edits?"}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
