{"timestamp": "2026-04-25T20:31:27.408329", "event": "Edit", "data": {"session_id": "c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "PostToolUse", "tool_name": "Edit", "tool_input": {"file_path": "/workspace/autopilot/.github/actions/parse-issue/action.yml", "old_string": "  merge_into_upstream:  { description: \"true\" or empty.,    value: \"${{ steps.p.outputs.merge_into_upstream }}\" }", "new_string": "  merge_into_upstream:  { description: '\"true\" or empty.',    value: \"${{ steps.p.outputs.merge_into_upstream }}\" }", "replace_all": false}, "tool_response": {"filePath": "/workspace/autopilot/.github/actions/parse-issue/action.yml", "oldString": "  merge_into_upstream:  { description: \"true\" or empty.,    value: \"${{ steps.p.outputs.merge_into_upstream }}\" }", "newString": "  merge_into_upstream:  { description: '\"true\" or empty.',    value: \"${{ steps.p.outputs.merge_into_upstream }}\" }", "originalFile": "name: parse-issue\ndescription: Parse issue title/body (with optional YAML frontmatter) into structured agent-run inputs.\n\ninputs:\n  title:        { required: true,  description: Issue title. }\n  body_raw:     { required: true,  description: Issue body (may contain YAML frontmatter). }\n  issue_number: { required: true,  description: Issue number, used for default branch name. }\n\noutputs:\n  agent_task_text:      { description: Body text with frontmatter stripped., value: \"${{ steps.p.outputs.agent_task_text }}\" }\n  pr_branch:            { description: Override branch from frontmatter (or empty).,   value: \"${{ steps.p.outputs.pr_branch }}\" }\n  base_branch:          { description: Base branch from frontmatter (or empty).,        value: \"${{ steps.p.outputs.base_branch }}\" }\n  timeout_secs:         { description: Timeout in seconds., value: \"${{ steps.p.outputs.timeout_secs }}\" }\n  model:                { description: Model id.,           value: \"${{ steps.p.outputs.model }}\" }\n  agent_branch_default: { description: Default agent branch if no override., value: \"${{ steps.p.outputs.agent_branch_default }}\" }\n  merge_into_upstream:  { description: \"true\" or empty.,    value: \"${{ steps.p.outputs.merge_into_upstream }}\" }\n\nruns:\n  using: composite\n  steps:\n    - id: p\n      shell: bash\n      env:\n        TITLE:        ${{ inputs.title }}\n        BODY_RAW:     ${{ inputs.body_raw }}\n        ISSUE_NUMBER: ${{ inputs.issue_number }}\n      run: bash \"$GITHUB_ACTION_PATH/script.sh\"\n", "structuredPatch": [{"oldStart": 13, "oldLines": 7, "newStart": 13, "newLines": 7, "lines": ["   timeout_secs:         { description: Timeout in seconds., value: \"${{ steps.p.outputs.timeout_secs }}\" }", "   model:                { description: Model id.,           value: \"${{ steps.p.outputs.model }}\" }", "   agent_branch_default: { description: Default agent branch if no override., value: \"${{ steps.p.outputs.agent_branch_default }}\" }", "-  merge_into_upstream:  { description: \"true\" or empty.,    value: \"${{ steps.p.outputs.merge_into_upstream }}\" }", "+  merge_into_upstream:  { description: '\"true\" or empty.',    value: \"${{ steps.p.outputs.merge_into_upstream }}\" }", " ", " runs:", "   using: composite"]}], "userModified": false, "replaceAll": false}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_01B2zGR8rJMGai5wTGYXiPmi", "duration_ms": 9}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-25T20:32:03.977068", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "data": {"session_id": "c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "main question: Why our test suite didn't catch error?"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-25T20:33:03.620482", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace/autopilot", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "The test suite couldn't have caught it. Two reasons:\n\n**1. The fixture harness bypasses `action.yml` entirely.**\n\n`.github/workflows/act-step-runner.yml:41-50` defines the `parse-issue` test job to directly invoke the script:\n\n```yaml\nparse-issue:\n  ...\n  steps:\n    - uses: actions/checkout@...\n    - run: bash .github/actions/parse-issue/script.sh\n```\n\nThe comment above it spells this out: *\"The `run:` step invokes the composite action's script directly (bypassing `uses:`), which is what act-step-dispatch.sh can execute.\"* So `run-act-step-checks.sh` only exercises `script.sh` against fixtures \u2014 it never asks GitHub/act to parse `action.yml`. The malformed `outputs:` block is invisible to that path.\n\n**2. No YAML/actionlint gate runs on this file in CI.**\n\n`.github/actionlint.yaml` exists, but none of the workflows (`act-step-runner`, `check-constraints`, `coding-agent`, `ensure-docker-image`, `issue-trigger`) run actionlint over `.github/actions/**/action.yml`. And actionlint's own YAML loader is fairly permissive about unquoted descriptions inside flow mappings even when it does run.\n\nThe bug only manifests when a downstream workflow does `uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/actions/parse-issue@main` \u2014 i.e., real issue-trigger runs \u2014 because that's the only place GitHub's YAML parser actually loads the file.\n\n**Fix options** (to plug the gap):\n- Add a job that runs `python3 -c \"import yaml; [yaml.safe_load(open(f)) for f in glob('.github/actions/*/action.yml')]\"` (or `actionlint`) on every PR.\n- Or change the test harness to actually `uses:` the composite action so action.yml is loaded as part of fixture runs."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-25T20:34:03.672531", "event": "Notification", "source": "input", "data": {"session_id": "c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace/autopilot", "hook_event_name": "Notification", "message": "Claude is waiting for your input", "notification_type": "idle_prompt"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-25T20:34:38.610157", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "data": {"session_id": "c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace/autopilot", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "mor4e details about 1 and actionlint"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-25T20:35:20.616388", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace/autopilot", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "## (1) Why the test harness can't see action.yml\n\nThe composite-action test path looks like this end-to-end:\n\n```\nrun-act-step-checks.sh parse-issue\n  \u2192 act-step-dispatch.sh act-step-runner.yml parse-issue\n       \u2192 reads .github/workflows/act-step-runner.yml\n       \u2192 finds job `parse-issue:` with steps[].run = \"bash .github/actions/parse-issue/script.sh\"\n       \u2192 exports the job's env: (TITLE, BODY_RAW, ISSUE_NUMBER) from --inputs JSON\n       \u2192 exec the run block\n       \u2192 diff $GITHUB_OUTPUT against fixtures/<case>/expected.json\n```\n\nTwo structural reasons it can't catch a malformed `action.yml`:\n\n**a. `act-step-runner.yml:48-50` doesn't `uses:` the composite action.** It open-codes the job: `actions/checkout` + `bash .github/actions/parse-issue/script.sh`. Only `script.sh` is touched. `action.yml` is never opened by `act`, never opened by `yq`, never opened by Python. From the harness's perspective, `parse-issue/action.yml` could be deleted and tests would still be green.\n\nThe dispatcher *does* have a fallback (lines 60-72 of `act-step-dispatch.sh`) for jobs that only have `uses:` \u2014 it follows `./.github/actions/<name>` and runs `script.sh` directly. So even if you flipped `act-step-runner.yml` to `uses:` the composite, the dispatcher would still bypass `action.yml` and shell straight into the script. Both the harness job *and* the dispatcher's fallback are designed around the assumption that `script.sh` is the unit under test.\n\n**b. Outputs are checked against the script's `$GITHUB_OUTPUT`, not the action's declared `outputs:`.** `parse_github_output_to_json` (in `run-act-step-checks.sh`) reads the file the script wrote. The action.yml `outputs:` block \u2014 the part that broke \u2014 is metadata GitHub Actions uses to wire `steps.p.outputs.*` upward to the job's `outputs:`. The harness doesn't model that wiring at all; it inspects the raw `$GITHUB_OUTPUT` file. So even an output declared with completely wrong syntax (or missing entirely) wouldn't change a fixture diff.\n\nNet: the harness tests script behavior, not action contract. The `action.yml` is effectively untyped glue from the test's point of view.\n\n## actionlint\n\nTwo separate questions: is it wired up, and would it have caught this?\n\n**Is it wired up?** No. `grep -rn actionlint .github/` returns only the config file `.github/actionlint.yaml`. No workflow runs `actionlint`, no pre-commit hook, nothing in `scripts/test/`. The config exists to suppress false positives (`property \"fetch-issue\" is not defined` in the test harness) for *whoever runs actionlint locally* \u2014 but CI doesn't run it. So in practice, actionlint contributes zero gating today.\n\n**Would it have caught this even if wired up?** Probably not, and this is the more interesting part. actionlint's domain is *workflow* files (`.github/workflows/*.yml`) \u2014 it lints expressions, `needs.*`, runner labels, shellcheck on `run:` blocks, etc. It does **not** lint composite `action.yml` files by default. You'd need `actionlint -action .github/actions/parse-issue/action.yml` or similar, and even then its action-metadata checks are shallow (input/output names, required fields) \u2014 a description containing unbalanced quotes inside a flow mapping is a pure YAML-syntax issue that surfaces before any actionlint-specific rule fires.\n\nConcretely, the failure mode here was:\n\n```yaml\n{ description: \"true\" or empty., value: \"...\" }\n```\n\nYAML 1.1/1.2 flow-mapping rules: after `\"true\"` closes the quoted scalar, the parser expects `,` or `}`. It hits ` or empty.` as a bare scalar and bails. PyYAML refuses to load the file at all (you saw `expected ',' or '}', but got '<scalar>'`). GitHub's parser does the same when a real workflow `uses:` it. But actionlint piggybacks on a YAML parser too \u2014 if the file doesn't parse, actionlint's report is \"syntax error at line 16,\" which is the same thing you'd get from `python3 -c \"import yaml; yaml.safe_load(...)\"`. It doesn't add value over a 5-line YAML-validity check.\n\n**The cheapest gate** that would actually have caught this is not actionlint but a one-liner over every action.yml:\n\n```bash\npython3 -c \"\nimport sys, yaml, glob\nfor f in glob.glob('.github/actions/*/action.yml'):\n    yaml.safe_load(open(f))\n\"\n```\n\nOr `yq '.' .github/actions/*/action.yml >/dev/null` in a workflow step. That would fail loudly on exactly the class of bug you hit. Wiring actionlint properly is also worth doing \u2014 it'd catch a different class of bug (bad `${{ }}` references, wrong runner labels) \u2014 but it's not the gap that let *this* one through."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-25T20:37:23.616397", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "data": {"session_id": "c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace/autopilot", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "actionlint - not yet. Lets discuss a condition of autopilot/.github/actions/parse-issue/fixtures and how this can bbe inforced in testing using current or involved autopilot/.github/scripts/test"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-25T20:38:27.326879", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace/autopilot", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "## Fixture state\n\nFour fixtures, all asserting on the same 7 output keys: `agent_branch_default, agent_task_text, base_branch, merge_into_upstream, model, pr_branch, timeout_secs`. They cover: full frontmatter, no frontmatter, branch overrides, slug-length cap. They do *not* cross-check against `action.yml` at all \u2014 `expected.json` is a free-form bag of strings.\n\n## Invariants worth enforcing\n\nThese are cheap to add to `run-act-step-checks.sh` as a preflight (or a sibling `validate-action-contract.sh <step>` it calls before the per-fixture loop). Listed roughly in order of cost vs. payoff.\n\n### 1. `action.yml` must parse as YAML\n\nThe thing that would have caught the actual bug. Literally:\n\n```bash\npython3 -c \"import sys, yaml; yaml.safe_load(open(sys.argv[1]))\" \\\n  \".github/actions/$STEP/action.yml\"\n```\n\nOne line in the preflight; fail the run if it errors. This is a structural property of the action package, independent of fixtures, so it belongs in `run-act-step-checks.sh` (or a `for action in .github/actions/*/; do \u2026` loop in CI). PyYAML's error message is already line/column precise \u2014 same quality as actionlint for syntax issues, without the dependency.\n\n### 2. `expected.json` keys \u2286 `action.yml` outputs\n\nFor every fixture, every key in `expected.json` must be declared in `action.yml`'s `outputs:`. Catches: typo in fixture (`merge_into_upsream`), or a fixture asserting on an output that was renamed/removed. Cheap:\n\n```bash\ndeclared=$(yq -r '.outputs | keys[]' \"$ACTION_YML\" | sort)\nasserted=$(jq -r 'keys[]' \"$case_dir/expected.json\" | sort)\ncomm -23 <(echo \"$asserted\") <(echo \"$declared\") | grep . && fail\n```\n\n### 3. `action.yml` outputs \u2286 union of `expected.json` keys\n\nInverse of (2), across all fixtures. Forces \"if you add an output, add fixture coverage for it.\" This is the rule that makes a future `merge_into_upstream`-shaped addition impossible to ship untested \u2014 adding the output to `action.yml` without touching any fixture would fail the preflight.\n\nThis one is opinionated; some teams find it annoying. The looser form is \"at least one fixture asserts on each output,\" which is what I'd default to.\n\n### 4. Every `value: \"${{ steps.X.outputs.Y }}\"` in `action.yml` must correspond to a `Y=` write in `script.sh`\n\nThis is the one that closes the loop end-to-end:\n\n```bash\nyq -r '.outputs | to_entries[] | .value' \"$ACTION_YML\" \\\n  | grep -oP 'steps\\.\\w+\\.outputs\\.\\K\\w+' | sort -u \\\n  > /tmp/declared_keys\ngrep -oP '^\\s*\\K\\w+(?==)' \"$SCRIPT_SH\" \\\n  | sort -u > /tmp/script_keys   # rough; tighten to GITHUB_OUTPUT writes\ncomm -23 /tmp/declared_keys /tmp/script_keys && fail\n```\n\nCatches the silent class: `action.yml` declares `outputs.foo`, fixtures don't assert on it, script never writes it \u2192 real consumers see empty string forever. Pairs naturally with (3): (3) forces fixture coverage; (4) forces script coverage; together they force the three legs (action.yml \u2194 script.sh \u2194 fixtures) to stay in sync.\n\n### 5. `act-step-runner.yml` job env keys \u2287 `action.yml` inputs\n\nThe harness's whole premise is \"the job's `env:` block mirrors the composite action's input contract\" (per the comment at line 35-40 of `act-step-runner.yml`). Enforce it:\n\n```bash\ninputs=$(yq -r '.inputs | keys[] | ascii_upcase' \"$ACTION_YML\" | sort)\nenv_keys=$(yq -r \".jobs[\\\"$STEP\\\"].env | keys[]\" \\\n                .github/workflows/act-step-runner.yml | sort)\ncomm -23 <(echo \"$inputs\") <(echo \"$env_keys\") | grep . && fail\n```\n\nCatches the harness-drift class: someone adds `inputs.foo` to the composite action, forgets to mirror it in the test wrapper, and fixtures continue to \"pass\" against an under-specified script. Note this assumes the convention that `inputs.foo` \u2194 env `FOO`, which `parse-issue` follows (`title \u2192 TITLE`, `body_raw \u2192 BODY_RAW`); if other actions break that convention you'd need a name map.\n\n## Where to put it\n\nI'd extend `run-act-step-checks.sh` rather than make a new file. Add a `preflight()` function that runs (1)+(2)+(3)+(4) for `$STEP` before the `for case_dir` loop, and bail on first failure. (5) is harness-wide \u2014 it makes more sense as a one-shot at the top of the script, run once regardless of `$STEP`. None of this needs new tooling beyond `yq`/`jq`/`python3`, all already used.\n\nEnd result: the bug you hit fails preflight (1) with a clean error before any fixture runs, and the broader class of \"fixture/script/action.yml drift\" becomes structurally hard to land."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-25T20:40:08.604170", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "data": {"session_id": "c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace/autopilot", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "to much text, here is cmd which was initially added as part of test. I need to how make this approach for catching tmentioned and future errors. cd $PROJECT_ROOT && bash .github/scripts/test/run-act-step-checks.sh act-step-runner.yml parse-issue"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-25T20:40:27.985490", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace/autopilot", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Add a preflight at the top of `run-act-step-checks.sh` (after the `[ -d \"$FIX_ROOT\" ] || \u2026` line) so the same invocation fails before any fixture runs:\n\n```bash\nACTION_YML=\".github/actions/$STEP/action.yml\"\n\n# 1. action.yml must parse\npython3 -c \"import sys,yaml; yaml.safe_load(open(sys.argv[1]))\" \"$ACTION_YML\" \\\n  || { echo \"FAIL: $ACTION_YML invalid YAML\" >&2; exit 1; }\n\n# 2. every output declared in action.yml must be wired to a steps.*.outputs.* key\n#    that script.sh writes to $GITHUB_OUTPUT\ndeclared=$(yq -r '.outputs | to_entries[] | .value' \"$ACTION_YML\" \\\n           | grep -oP 'steps\\.\\w+\\.outputs\\.\\K\\w+' | sort -u)\nwritten=$(grep -oE '^[[:space:]]*[a-z_]+=' .github/actions/$STEP/script.sh \\\n          | tr -d ' =' | sort -u)\nmissing=$(comm -23 <(echo \"$declared\") <(echo \"$written\"))\n[ -z \"$missing\" ] || { echo \"FAIL: outputs declared but never written: $missing\" >&2; exit 1; }\n\n# 3. every fixture's expected.json keys \u2286 declared outputs\ndeclared_outs=$(yq -r '.outputs | keys[]' \"$ACTION_YML\" | sort -u)\nfor f in \"$FIX_ROOT\"/*/expected.json; do\n  bad=$(comm -23 <(jq -r 'keys[]' \"$f\" | sort -u) <(echo \"$declared_outs\"))\n  [ -z \"$bad\" ] || { echo \"FAIL: $f asserts undeclared outputs: $bad\" >&2; exit 1; }\ndone\n\n# 4. every declared output must be asserted in at least one fixture\nunion=$(jq -s 'map(keys[])|unique[]' \"$FIX_ROOT\"/*/expected.json | tr -d '\"' | sort -u)\nuncovered=$(comm -23 <(echo \"$declared_outs\") <(echo \"$union\"))\n[ -z \"$uncovered\" ] || { echo \"FAIL: declared outputs with no fixture coverage: $uncovered\" >&2; exit 1; }\n```\n\nWhat each check buys you:\n\n| # | Catches the bug you hit? | Catches future class |\n|---|---|---|\n| 1 | **yes** \u2014 PyYAML rejects the malformed flow mapping | any action.yml syntax break |\n| 2 | no, but catches the symmetric one (declare output, forget to write it) | drift between action.yml and script.sh |\n| 3 | typos in fixture keys, renamed outputs | |\n| 4 | new output added without fixture coverage | forces (1)+(2)+(3) to stay meaningful |\n\nSame invocation, now fails fast on the contract before touching `act`."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-25T20:41:56.778550", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "data": {"session_id": "c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace/autopilot", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "i want actually execute parse-issue. This is requirement. cmd in autopilot \"cd $PROJECT_ROOT && bash .github/scripts/test/run-act-step-checks.sh act-step-runner.yml parse-issue\" was initially designed to do it. Some drift happened, constraint should evolve as well"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-25T20:42:50.586314", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace/autopilot", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Right \u2014 the goal is for the harness to actually load and execute through `action.yml`, not shortcut to `script.sh`. Two coordinated changes do it:\n\n## Change 1 \u2014 `act-step-runner.yml`: invoke the composite action for real\n\nReplace the open-coded `parse-issue` job with a real `uses:` + `with:` form:\n\n```yaml\nparse-issue:\n  runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n  steps:\n    - uses: actions/checkout@de0fac2e4500dabe0009e67214ff5f5447ce83dd\n    - uses: ./.github/actions/parse-issue\n      with:\n        title:        ${{ needs.fetch-issue.outputs.title }}\n        body_raw:     ${{ needs.fetch-issue.outputs.body_raw }}\n        issue_number: ${{ inputs.issue_number }}\n```\n\nThe `with:` expressions match the fixture `input.json` keys (`needs.fetch-issue.outputs.title`, etc.) \u2014 so the existing 4 fixtures keep working unchanged.\n\n## Change 2 \u2014 `act-step-dispatch.sh`: execute composite actions through `action.yml`\n\nToday's `uses:` fallback (lines 60-72) still calls `bash $ACTION_DIR/script.sh` directly. Replace it with a real composite-action driver:\n\n```bash\nACTION_REF=$(yq -r \".jobs[\\\"$STEP_ID\\\"].steps[] | select(.uses != null) | .uses\n                    | select(startswith(\\\"./.github/actions/\\\"))\" \"$WF\" | head -1)\n\nif [ -n \"$ACTION_REF\" ] && [ \"$ACTION_REF\" != \"null\" ]; then\n  ACTION_DIR=\"${ACTION_REF#./}\"\n  ACTION_YML=\"$ACTION_DIR/action.yml\"\n\n  # Loads action.yml \u2014 this is where a malformed YAML now fails the test.\n  yq '.' \"$ACTION_YML\" >/dev/null\n\n  # Resolve `with:` against INPUTS_JSON, just like env: today.\n  declare -A INPUTS\n  while IFS= read -r line; do\n    k=\"${line%%=*}\"; v=\"${line#*=}\"\n    if [[ \"$v\" =~ ^\\$\\{\\{[[:space:]]*(.+)[[:space:]]*\\}\\}$ ]]; then\n      expr=\"${BASH_REMATCH[1]}\"; expr=\"$(echo \"$expr\" | xargs)\"\n      INPUTS[$k]=$(echo \"$INPUTS_JSON\" | jq -r --arg k \"$expr\" '.[$k] // \"\"')\n    else\n      INPUTS[$k]=\"$v\"\n    fi\n  done < <(yq -r \".jobs[\\\"$STEP_ID\\\"].steps[] | select(.uses != null) | .with\n                  | to_entries[] | \\\"\\(.key)=\\(.value)\\\"\" \"$WF\")\n\n  # Walk runs.steps[]: for each step, evaluate env: by substituting ${{ inputs.X }},\n  # export, then exec run:. GITHUB_ACTION_PATH lets the script find sibling files.\n  export GITHUB_ACTION_PATH=\"$PWD/$ACTION_DIR\"\n  step_count=$(yq -r '.runs.steps | length' \"$ACTION_YML\")\n  for i in $(seq 0 $((step_count-1))); do\n    while IFS= read -r line; do\n      k=\"${line%%=*}\"; v=\"${line#*=}\"\n      # Substitute every ${{ inputs.<name> }} with the resolved INPUTS[<name>].\n      while [[ \"$v\" =~ \\$\\{\\{[[:space:]]*inputs\\.([a-zA-Z_]+)[[:space:]]*\\}\\} ]]; do\n        name=\"${BASH_REMATCH[1]}\"\n        v=\"${v//${BASH_REMATCH[0]}/${INPUTS[$name]:-}}\"\n      done\n      export \"$k=$v\"\n    done < <(yq -r \".runs.steps[$i].env // {} | to_entries[] | \\\"\\(.key)=\\(.value)\\\"\" \"$ACTION_YML\")\n\n    RUN=$(yq -r \".runs.steps[$i].run\" \"$ACTION_YML\")\n    bash -c \"$RUN\"\n  done\n  exit 0\nfi\n```\n\n## Why this matches what you want\n\n- `yq '.' \"$ACTION_YML\"` is the moment of truth: malformed `outputs:` block (or any other YAML break) fails *before* the script runs. No separate preflight needed; the harness's own load step is the gate.\n- The script.sh execution now goes through the action's declared `inputs:` \u2192 `env:` \u2192 `run:` chain. If someone renames `TITLE` to `ISSUE_TITLE` in `action.yml` but forgets `script.sh`, fixtures will diff. If someone declares an output but binds it to a non-existent step id, the wiring is still loaded (won't catch this by execution alone \u2014 that one needs the static check from before).\n- Fixtures and the calling command stay byte-identical: `bash .github/scripts/test/run-act-step-checks.sh act-step-runner.yml parse-issue` keeps working.\n\n## What to verify before committing\n\n- Run the four existing fixtures end-to-end and confirm they still produce matching `expected.json`.\n- Temporarily re-introduce the broken `description: \"true\" or empty.,` to confirm the harness fails at the `yq '.'` line with a clear YAML error.\n- For other composite actions wired into `act-step-runner.yml`, audit whether their jobs are also open-coded (same drift) and convert them to `uses:` + `with:` so they go through the same path."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
