{"timestamp": "2026-04-25T20:45:08.694076", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace/autopilot", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Concrete delta. Two new constraints under the existing `step_output_checks` feature in `spec.k.json` \u2014 one static (locks the harness shape), one structural (the YAML-loadability gate). Then the harness change that makes them pass.\n\n## Step 1 \u2014 add the constraints (currently failing)\n\nEdit `spec.k.json`, inside the `step_output_checks` feature's `constraints` object:\n\n```json\n\"parse_issue_test_uses_composite_action\": {\n  \"id\": \"parse_issue_test_uses_composite_action\",\n  \"cmd\": \"F=$PROJECT_ROOT/.github/workflows/act-step-runner.yml; USES=$(yq -r '.jobs[\\\"parse-issue\\\"].steps[] | select(.uses != null) | .uses' \\\"$F\\\"); echo \\\"$USES\\\" | grep -qx './.github/actions/parse-issue' || { echo \\\"act-step-runner.yml job 'parse-issue' must invoke the composite action via uses: ./.github/actions/parse-issue (got: $USES). Bypassing action.yml hides metadata bugs.\\\"; exit 1; }\",\n  \"description\": \"Architectural: the parse-issue test job in act-step-runner.yml must invoke the composite action via 'uses: ./.github/actions/parse-issue', not by open-coding 'run: bash .github/actions/parse-issue/script.sh'. This forces every test run to load action.yml, so malformed metadata (broken outputs:, mistyped expressions) fails the suite instead of going undetected.\",\n  \"fails_count\": 0\n},\n\"composite_actions_yaml_loadable\": {\n  \"id\": \"composite_actions_yaml_loadable\",\n  \"cmd\": \"for f in $PROJECT_ROOT/.github/actions/*/action.yml; do python3 -c \\\"import sys,yaml; yaml.safe_load(open(sys.argv[1]))\\\" \\\"$f\\\" || { echo \\\"Invalid YAML: $f\\\"; exit 1; }; done\",\n  \"description\": \"Static: every .github/actions/*/action.yml must parse as valid YAML. Catches malformed flow-mapping descriptions, unclosed quotes, and similar metadata breaks that the behavioral fixture harness would miss when it bypasses action.yml.\",\n  \"fails_count\": 0\n}\n```\n\n`fails_count: 0` is correct at creation time \u2014 the discipline says you run them next and watch them fail at least once before fixing.\n\n## Step 2 \u2014 run constraints, observe failures\n\n```\ncd $PROJECT_ROOT && <your constraint runner>\n```\n\nExpected:\n- `parse_issue_test_uses_composite_action` \u2192 FAIL (current `act-step-runner.yml` open-codes `run: bash .github/actions/parse-issue/script.sh`).\n- `composite_actions_yaml_loadable` \u2192 PASS *now* (you already fixed the description bug). To prove it really catches the class, temporarily revert your one-line edit at `parse-issue/action.yml:16`, run, see FAIL, restore.\n\nBump `fails_count` to `1` for each after observing the failure (per the constraint discipline \u2014 proves the test actually tests something).\n\n## Step 3 \u2014 make `parse_issue_test_uses_composite_action` pass\n\nTwo edits, exactly the ones from the prior message:\n\n**`.github/workflows/act-step-runner.yml`** \u2014 replace the `parse-issue` job body:\n\n```yaml\nparse-issue:\n  runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n  steps:\n    - uses: actions/checkout@de0fac2e4500dabe0009e67214ff5f5447ce83dd\n    - uses: ./.github/actions/parse-issue\n      with:\n        title:        ${{ needs.fetch-issue.outputs.title }}\n        body_raw:     ${{ needs.fetch-issue.outputs.body_raw }}\n        issue_number: ${{ inputs.issue_number }}\n```\n\n(Drop the `env:` block on the job \u2014 inputs now flow through `with:` per the action's contract.)\n\n**`.github/scripts/test/act-step-dispatch.sh`** \u2014 extend the `uses:` fallback (the `if [ -n \"$ACTION_REF\" ]` branch around lines 60-72) to actually load `action.yml`, resolve `with:` against `INPUTS_JSON`, evaluate `runs.steps[].env` by substituting `${{ inputs.X }}`, and exec `runs.steps[].run`. Sketch from the previous message.\n\n## Step 4 \u2014 verify the suite now exercises action.yml\n\n```\ncd $PROJECT_ROOT && bash .github/scripts/test/run-act-step-checks.sh act-step-runner.yml parse-issue\n```\n\nShould print `OK: parse-issue/{frontmatter-branches,full,no-frontmatter,slug-cap}` as before. To prove the new path actually goes through `action.yml`: revert the description fix again \u2014 `parse_issue_via_action` should now FAIL (because `action.yml` won't load). Restore.\n\n## Why this matches the framework\n\n- `parse_issue_test_uses_composite_action` is the *contract-shape* constraint \u2014 it locks the harness against re-drift. If anyone \"optimizes\" the test job back to open-coded `run: bash \u2026script.sh`, the constraint flips red.\n- `composite_actions_yaml_loadable` is the *cheap structural* gate \u2014 independent of fixtures, runs in milliseconds, covers every action in the tree (not just `parse-issue`).\n- `parse_issue_via_action` (existing) gains real teeth: now that the harness goes through `action.yml`, the existing behavioral check becomes the third leg, catching wiring drift between `inputs:`, `outputs:`, and `script.sh`.\n\nThree constraints, three failure modes, no overlap.\n\n## Optional follow-up (same pattern)\n\n`choose_branch_via_action` likely has the same drift in `act-step-runner.yml`. Add a parallel `choose_branch_test_uses_composite_action` constraint and convert that job too \u2014 same edits."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
