{"timestamp": "2026-04-25T20:54:41.463778", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": true, "last_assistant_message": "All constraints PASS. Both behavioral suites (`parse-issue` 4/4, `choose-branch` 1/1) execute through `action.yml` now.\n\n## On your `actions/checkout` question\n\nYou're right to question it. Two cases:\n\n- **Real GitHub Actions / full `act`** \u2014 yes, needed. Each job starts with an empty workdir; checkout is required.\n- **Our test harness (`act-step-dispatch.sh`)** \u2014 no, redundant. The dispatcher only follows `uses:` refs starting with `./.github/actions/` (filter on line 72), so `actions/checkout@\u2026` is ignored. The dispatcher runs in `$PWD` which is already the repo.\n\nBecause the wrapper job exists *only* to be dispatched by our harness (it has no other call site \u2014 the workflow exposes the `executor` job for that), the checkout step is dead weight. Safe to drop. The `executor` job at the top still has its checkout for the real `workflow_call` entrypoint, which is the legitimate use.\n\nIf you want me to remove it from `parse-issue` and `choose-branch` wrappers, say the word \u2014 same edit in both. Otherwise leaving it makes the wrapper jobs runnable as-is via real Actions/`act` should anyone ever do that.\n\n## Summary of changes\n\n- `spec.k.json`: added `parse_issue_test_uses_composite_action` + `composite_actions_yaml_loadable` constraints under `step_output_checks` (both verified, fails_count=1).\n- `.github/workflows/act-step-runner.yml`: `parse-issue` job now `uses: ./.github/actions/parse-issue` with `with:` block.\n- `.github/scripts/test/act-step-dispatch.sh`: rewritten with explicit Path A (composite action \u2014 loads action.yml, walks `runs.steps[]`, substitutes `${{ inputs.X }}`) and Path B (inline run) split.\n- `.github/actions/parse-issue/action.yml`: fixed the original `outputs.merge_into_upstream` description (this turn's bug) and a sibling `inputs.issue_number` description that actionlint flagged once it started loading the file."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
