{"timestamp": "2026-04-26T01:08:13.226115", "event": "Edit", "data": {"session_id": "c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace/autopilot", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "PreToolUse", "tool_name": "Edit", "tool_input": {"file_path": "/workspace/autopilot/.github/actions/ensure-docker-image/action.yml", "old_string": "  tag:\n    description: Local tag base. A `<tag_prefix>-<hash>` suffix is appended, producing `<tag>:<tag_prefix>-<hash>`.\n    required: false\n    default: cached-image\n  tag_prefix:\n    description: |\n      REQUIRED. Project namespace. Dual-purpose:\n        - Tag partition (both runner types): appears in the local docker\n          tag as `<tag>:<tag_prefix>-<hash>`, preventing tag collisions\n          when multiple projects share one docker daemon. This is the\n          natural \"tag\" role on self-hosted runners.\n        - Buildx GHA cache scope (GitHub-hosted build path only): isolates\n          one project's layer cache from another's while staying stable\n          across edits to that project's Dockerfile, so layer reuse still\n          works as the Dockerfile evolves. This is the natural \"cache key\n          prefix\" role on hosted runners.\n      Use a project-specific value (e.g. `<org>/<repo>-img`, typically\n      derived from github.repository at the call site). Distinct projects\n      MUST use distinct prefixes. No default: omitting this is a usage error.\n    required: true", "new_string": "  tag_prefix:\n    description: |\n      REQUIRED. Project namespace. Dual-purpose, single string:\n        - Docker tag (both runner types): the produced local tag is\n          `<tag_prefix>:<hash>`, so this is what `docker images` shows in\n          the REPOSITORY column. Multiple projects sharing one daemon\n          (typical on a per-user self-hosted runner) keep their tags\n          partitioned because each project picks a distinct prefix.\n        - Buildx GHA cache scope (GitHub-hosted build path only): scopes\n          the layer cache (`type=gha,scope=<tag_prefix>-buildimg`) and the\n          actions/cache pull-tarball key (`<tag_prefix>-pullimg-<digest>`)\n          per project, so distinct projects don't poison each other's cache\n          and a single project's edits still hit per-layer reuse.\n      Pick something short and project-specific (e.g. `agent-img`,\n      `check-img`). Distinct projects MUST use distinct prefixes. Including\n      `${{ github.repository }}` is a defensive convention for templates\n      copy-pasted across many repos, but a hand-picked unique name is\n      equivalent. No default: omitting this is a usage error.\n    required: true", "replace_all": false}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_01Ky5joXtY8gh6X9yHYZffQ9"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-26T01:08:13.439728", "event": "Edit", "data": {"session_id": "c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/c966cf96-0585-4339-a113-e99e77a184d4.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace/autopilot", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "PostToolUse", "tool_name": "Edit", "tool_input": {"file_path": "/workspace/autopilot/.github/actions/ensure-docker-image/action.yml", "old_string": "  tag:\n    description: Local tag base. A `<tag_prefix>-<hash>` suffix is appended, producing `<tag>:<tag_prefix>-<hash>`.\n    required: false\n    default: cached-image\n  tag_prefix:\n    description: |\n      REQUIRED. Project namespace. Dual-purpose:\n        - Tag partition (both runner types): appears in the local docker\n          tag as `<tag>:<tag_prefix>-<hash>`, preventing tag collisions\n          when multiple projects share one docker daemon. This is the\n          natural \"tag\" role on self-hosted runners.\n        - Buildx GHA cache scope (GitHub-hosted build path only): isolates\n          one project's layer cache from another's while staying stable\n          across edits to that project's Dockerfile, so layer reuse still\n          works as the Dockerfile evolves. This is the natural \"cache key\n          prefix\" role on hosted runners.\n      Use a project-specific value (e.g. `<org>/<repo>-img`, typically\n      derived from github.repository at the call site). Distinct projects\n      MUST use distinct prefixes. No default: omitting this is a usage error.\n    required: true", "new_string": "  tag_prefix:\n    description: |\n      REQUIRED. Project namespace. Dual-purpose, single string:\n        - Docker tag (both runner types): the produced local tag is\n          `<tag_prefix>:<hash>`, so this is what `docker images` shows in\n          the REPOSITORY column. Multiple projects sharing one daemon\n          (typical on a per-user self-hosted runner) keep their tags\n          partitioned because each project picks a distinct prefix.\n        - Buildx GHA cache scope (GitHub-hosted build path only): scopes\n          the layer cache (`type=gha,scope=<tag_prefix>-buildimg`) and the\n          actions/cache pull-tarball key (`<tag_prefix>-pullimg-<digest>`)\n          per project, so distinct projects don't poison each other's cache\n          and a single project's edits still hit per-layer reuse.\n      Pick something short and project-specific (e.g. `agent-img`,\n      `check-img`). Distinct projects MUST use distinct prefixes. Including\n      `${{ github.repository }}` is a defensive convention for templates\n      copy-pasted across many repos, but a hand-picked unique name is\n      equivalent. No default: omitting this is a usage error.\n    required: true", "replace_all": false}, "tool_response": {"filePath": "/workspace/autopilot/.github/actions/ensure-docker-image/action.yml", "oldString": "  tag:\n    description: Local tag base. A `<tag_prefix>-<hash>` suffix is appended, producing `<tag>:<tag_prefix>-<hash>`.\n    required: false\n    default: cached-image\n  tag_prefix:\n    description: |\n      REQUIRED. Project namespace. Dual-purpose:\n        - Tag partition (both runner types): appears in the local docker\n          tag as `<tag>:<tag_prefix>-<hash>`, preventing tag collisions\n          when multiple projects share one docker daemon. This is the\n          natural \"tag\" role on self-hosted runners.\n        - Buildx GHA cache scope (GitHub-hosted build path only): isolates\n          one project's layer cache from another's while staying stable\n          across edits to that project's Dockerfile, so layer reuse still\n          works as the Dockerfile evolves. This is the natural \"cache key\n          prefix\" role on hosted runners.\n      Use a project-specific value (e.g. `<org>/<repo>-img`, typically\n      derived from github.repository at the call site). Distinct projects\n      MUST use distinct prefixes. No default: omitting this is a usage error.\n    required: true", "newString": "  tag_prefix:\n    description: |\n      REQUIRED. Project namespace. Dual-purpose, single string:\n        - Docker tag (both runner types): the produced local tag is\n          `<tag_prefix>:<hash>`, so this is what `docker images` shows in\n          the REPOSITORY column. Multiple projects sharing one daemon\n          (typical on a per-user self-hosted runner) keep their tags\n          partitioned because each project picks a distinct prefix.\n        - Buildx GHA cache scope (GitHub-hosted build path only): scopes\n          the layer cache (`type=gha,scope=<tag_prefix>-buildimg`) and the\n          actions/cache pull-tarball key (`<tag_prefix>-pullimg-<digest>`)\n          per project, so distinct projects don't poison each other's cache\n          and a single project's edits still hit per-layer reuse.\n      Pick something short and project-specific (e.g. `agent-img`,\n      `check-img`). Distinct projects MUST use distinct prefixes. Including\n      `${{ github.repository }}` is a defensive convention for templates\n      copy-pasted across many repos, but a hand-picked unique name is\n      equivalent. No default: omitting this is a usage error.\n    required: true", "originalFile": "name: Ensure Docker Image\ndescription: |\n  Ensure a local docker image tag exists \u2014 either by pulling a base image or by\n  building a Dockerfile on top of it \u2014 with a unified caching story across\n  GitHub-hosted and self-hosted runners. Idempotent: a fast path skips work\n  entirely when the content-hashed local tag already exists.\n\n  Two paths:\n    - dockerfile unset  \u2192 pulls `base_image`, tags it locally, outputs the tag.\n    - dockerfile set    \u2192 builds the Dockerfile on top of `base_image`, outputs the built tag.\n\n  Caching:\n    - GitHub-hosted build path \u2192 Buildx GHA cache (type=gha), scoped by tag_prefix.\n    - GitHub-hosted pull path  \u2192 actions/cache over a docker save tarball, keyed by base digest.\n    - Self-hosted (both paths) \u2192 docker daemon's persistent local layer cache (no external layer).\n    - Fast path: when a local tag with the computed content hash already exists, build/pull is skipped entirely.\n\ninputs:\n  dockerfile:\n    description: Path to the Dockerfile, relative to $GITHUB_WORKSPACE. Leave empty to only pull+tag `base_image`.\n    required: false\n    default: \"\"\n  context:\n    description: Build context directory, relative to $GITHUB_WORKSPACE. Only used when `dockerfile` is set.\n    required: false\n    default: \".\"\n  build_args:\n    description: |\n      Newline-separated KEY=VALUE build args, forwarded to the builder.\n      Included in the content hash, so a change invalidates the local tag (but not\n      necessarily the GHA layer cache, which buildx reuses at layer granularity).\n    required: false\n    default: \"\"\n  base_image:\n    description: |\n      Image reference to pull and tag locally, and to use as the FROM contract for\n      any Dockerfile. REQUIRED. The action does NOT rewrite the Dockerfile's FROM \u2014\n      the Dockerfile still decides the base; this input is what drives the pull+tag\n      path and the cache-key stability.\n    required: true\n  tag:\n    description: Local tag base. A `<tag_prefix>-<hash>` suffix is appended, producing `<tag>:<tag_prefix>-<hash>`.\n    required: false\n    default: cached-image\n  tag_prefix:\n    description: |\n      REQUIRED. Project namespace. Dual-purpose:\n        - Tag partition (both runner types): appears in the local docker\n          tag as `<tag>:<tag_prefix>-<hash>`, preventing tag collisions\n          when multiple projects share one docker daemon. This is the\n          natural \"tag\" role on self-hosted runners.\n        - Buildx GHA cache scope (GitHub-hosted build path only): isolates\n          one project's layer cache from another's while staying stable\n          across edits to that project's Dockerfile, so layer reuse still\n          works as the Dockerfile evolves. This is the natural \"cache key\n          prefix\" role on hosted runners.\n      Use a project-specific value (e.g. `<org>/<repo>-img`, typically\n      derived from github.repository at the call site). Distinct projects\n      MUST use distinct prefixes. No default: omitting this is a usage error.\n    required: true\n\noutputs:\n  image:\n    description: Fully qualified local tag of the produced image. Ready to `docker run`.\n    value: ${{ steps.finalize.outputs.image }}\n  cache_hit:\n    description: '\"true\" if the local tag pre-existed and neither build nor pull ran; \"false\" otherwise.'\n    value: ${{ steps.finalize.outputs.cache_hit }}\n  digest:\n    description: Local image ID (sha256) of the produced image.\n    value: ${{ steps.finalize.outputs.digest }}\n\nruns:\n  using: composite\n  steps:\n    - id: env\n      shell: bash\n      run: |\n        case \"${{ runner.environment }}\" in\n          self-hosted) echo \"is_self_hosted=true\"  >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\" ;;\n          *)           echo \"is_self_hosted=false\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\" ;;\n        esac\n\n    - id: base\n      shell: bash\n      env:\n        BASE: ${{ inputs.base_image }}\n      run: |\n        set -euo pipefail\n        DIGEST=$(docker manifest inspect \"$BASE\" 2>/dev/null | sha256sum | cut -c1-16) || DIGEST=\"\"\n        if [ -z \"$DIGEST\" ]; then\n          docker pull \"$BASE\" >/dev/null\n          DIGEST=$(docker inspect --format='{{.Id}}' \"$BASE\" | sed 's/^sha256://' | cut -c1-16)\n        fi\n        echo \"digest=$DIGEST\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n\n    - id: key\n      shell: bash\n      env:\n        DOCKERFILE:  ${{ inputs.dockerfile }}\n        BUILD_ARGS:  ${{ inputs.build_args }}\n        BASE_DIGEST: ${{ steps.base.outputs.digest }}\n        PREFIX:      ${{ inputs.tag_prefix }}\n        TAG_BASE:    ${{ inputs.tag }}\n      run: |\n        set -euo pipefail\n        if [ -z \"$PREFIX\" ]; then\n          echo \"::error::tag_prefix is required \u2014 see action README\"\n          exit 1\n        fi\n        SAFE_PREFIX=$(printf '%s' \"$PREFIX\" | tr '/ ' '__')\n        if [ -z \"$DOCKERFILE\" ]; then\n          HASH=\"base-${BASE_DIGEST}\"\n        else\n          DF_HASH=$(sha256sum \"$DOCKERFILE\" | cut -c1-16)\n          ARG_HASH=$(printf '%s' \"$BUILD_ARGS\" | sha256sum | cut -c1-16)\n          HASH=\"${DF_HASH}-${BASE_DIGEST}-${ARG_HASH}\"\n        fi\n        echo \"hash=$HASH\"                               >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n        echo \"tag=${TAG_BASE}:${SAFE_PREFIX}-${HASH}\"   >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n        echo \"build_scope=${SAFE_PREFIX}-buildimg\"      >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n        echo \"pull_cache_key=${SAFE_PREFIX}-pullimg-${BASE_DIGEST}\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n\n    - id: local\n      shell: bash\n      env:\n        TAG: ${{ steps.key.outputs.tag }}\n      run: |\n        if docker image inspect \"$TAG\" >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n          echo \"hit=true\"  >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n        else\n          echo \"hit=false\" >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n        fi\n\n    # ================================================================\n    # PATH A \u2014 dockerfile unset: pull+tag base\n    # ================================================================\n    - id: pull-cache\n      if: inputs.dockerfile == '' && steps.env.outputs.is_self_hosted != 'true' && steps.local.outputs.hit != 'true'\n      uses: actions/cache@0057852bfaa89a56745cba8c7296529d2fc39830\n      with:\n        path: /tmp/ensure-docker-image.tar\n        key:  ${{ steps.key.outputs.pull_cache_key }}\n\n    - name: Load pulled image from cache\n      if: inputs.dockerfile == '' && steps.local.outputs.hit != 'true' && steps.pull-cache.outputs.cache-hit == 'true'\n      shell: bash\n      env:\n        TAG: ${{ steps.key.outputs.tag }}\n      run: |\n        set -euo pipefail\n        out=$(docker load < /tmp/ensure-docker-image.tar)\n        echo \"$out\"\n        if ! docker image inspect \"$TAG\" >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n          src=$(printf '%s\\n' \"$out\" | sed -n -e 's/^Loaded image: //p' -e 's/^Loaded image ID: //p' | head -n1)\n          [ -n \"$src\" ] && docker tag \"$src\" \"$TAG\"\n        fi\n\n    - name: Pull base image\n      if: inputs.dockerfile == '' && steps.local.outputs.hit != 'true' && steps.pull-cache.outputs.cache-hit != 'true'\n      shell: bash\n      env:\n        BASE:           ${{ inputs.base_image }}\n        TAG:            ${{ steps.key.outputs.tag }}\n        IS_SELF_HOSTED: ${{ steps.env.outputs.is_self_hosted }}\n      run: |\n        set -euo pipefail\n        docker pull \"$BASE\"\n        docker tag \"$BASE\" \"$TAG\"\n        if [ \"$IS_SELF_HOSTED\" != \"true\" ]; then\n          docker save \"$TAG\" > /tmp/ensure-docker-image.tar\n        fi\n\n    # ================================================================\n    # PATH B \u2014 dockerfile set: buildx\n    # ================================================================\n    - if: inputs.dockerfile != '' && steps.local.outputs.hit != 'true'\n      uses: docker/setup-buildx-action@4d04d5d9486b7bd6fa91e7baf45bbb4f8b9deedd\n\n    - name: Build (github-hosted, GHA layer cache)\n      if: inputs.dockerfile != '' && steps.local.outputs.hit != 'true' && steps.env.outputs.is_self_hosted != 'true'\n      uses: docker/build-push-action@bcafcacb16a39f128d818304e6c9c0c18556b85f\n      with:\n        context:    ${{ inputs.context }}\n        file:       ${{ inputs.dockerfile }}\n        build-args: ${{ inputs.build_args }}\n        tags:       ${{ steps.key.outputs.tag }}\n        load:       true\n        push:       false\n        cache-from: type=gha,scope=${{ steps.key.outputs.build_scope }}\n        cache-to:   type=gha,mode=max,scope=${{ steps.key.outputs.build_scope }}\n\n    - name: Build (self-hosted, docker daemon layer cache)\n      if: inputs.dockerfile != '' && steps.local.outputs.hit != 'true' && steps.env.outputs.is_self_hosted == 'true'\n      uses: docker/build-push-action@bcafcacb16a39f128d818304e6c9c0c18556b85f\n      with:\n        context:    ${{ inputs.context }}\n        file:       ${{ inputs.dockerfile }}\n        build-args: ${{ inputs.build_args }}\n        tags:       ${{ steps.key.outputs.tag }}\n        load:       true\n        push:       false\n\n    - id: finalize\n      shell: bash\n      env:\n        TAG:       ${{ steps.key.outputs.tag }}\n        LOCAL_HIT: ${{ steps.local.outputs.hit }}\n      run: |\n        set -euo pipefail\n        DIGEST=$(docker inspect --format='{{.Id}}' \"$TAG\")\n        {\n          echo \"image=$TAG\"\n          echo \"cache_hit=$LOCAL_HIT\"\n          echo \"digest=$DIGEST\"\n        } >> \"$GITHUB_OUTPUT\"\n", "structuredPatch": [{"oldStart": 38, "oldLines": 25, "newStart": 38, "newLines": 24, "lines": ["       the Dockerfile still decides the base; this input is what drives the pull+tag", "       path and the cache-key stability.", "     required: true", "-  tag:", "-    description: Local tag base. A `<tag_prefix>-<hash>` suffix is appended, producing `<tag>:<tag_prefix>-<hash>`.", "-    required: false", "-    default: cached-image", "   tag_prefix:", "     description: |", "-      REQUIRED. Project namespace. Dual-purpose:", "-        - Tag partition (both runner types): appears in the local docker", "-          tag as `<tag>:<tag_prefix>-<hash>`, preventing tag collisions", "-          when multiple projects share one docker daemon. This is the", "-          natural \"tag\" role on self-hosted runners.", "-        - Buildx GHA cache scope (GitHub-hosted build path only): isolates", "-          one project's layer cache from another's while staying stable", "-          across edits to that project's Dockerfile, so layer reuse still", "-          works as the Dockerfile evolves. This is the natural \"cache key", "-          prefix\" role on hosted runners.", "-      Use a project-specific value (e.g. `<org>/<