{"timestamp": "2026-04-26T09:23:46.498780", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "f3f66d06-7f92-4db6-97f8-5f5513c17dd2", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/f3f66d06-7f92-4db6-97f8-5f5513c17dd2.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "`continue-on-error: true` on a step means: if the step fails (non-zero exit), the job keeps going and is still marked successful overall. The step itself shows as failed in the UI, but `if: always()` downstream steps run as if it had passed.\n\nI added it to preserve the old `|| true` behavior \u2014 the previous inline `run:` swallowed the agent's exit code so a failed commit attempt wouldn't fail the job. With the composite action, the equivalent knob at the workflow level is `continue-on-error: true`.\n\nNote: `steps.agent-commit.outcome` will be `failure` while `steps.agent-commit.conclusion` is `success` \u2014 useful if you ever want to branch on it. Want me to drop it (let a failed commit fail the job) or keep parity with the old behavior?"}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
