{"timestamp": "2026-04-26T09:27:16.286820", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "f3f66d06-7f92-4db6-97f8-5f5513c17dd2", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/f3f66d06-7f92-4db6-97f8-5f5513c17dd2.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "You're right \u2014 I confused myself. You said \"red\" = fail the job on a failed Agent commit, which is exactly what dropping `continue-on-error` does. So the change I made matches what you asked for: a failed Agent commit now turns the job red instead of being swallowed."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-26T09:29:28.793097", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "data": {"session_id": "f3f66d06-7f92-4db6-97f8-5f5513c17dd2", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/f3f66d06-7f92-4db6-97f8-5f5513c17dd2.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "Which guards can we set to avoid similar errors we trying to solve bash: .github/scripts/run-in-docker-claude.sh: No such file or directory"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-26T09:29:59.234768", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "f3f66d06-7f92-4db6-97f8-5f5513c17dd2", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/f3f66d06-7f92-4db6-97f8-5f5513c17dd2.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "A few practical guards, ordered by cost/value:\n\n1. **Forbid `.github/scripts/` paths in reusable workflows.** The root cause: a reusable workflow runs in the *consumer's* checkout, so `bash .github/scripts/foo.sh` only works by accident. Convention: workflows only `uses:` composite actions; scripts are invoked via `$GITHUB_ACTION_PATH` inside the action. Enforce with a one-line CI check:\n\n   ```bash\n   ! grep -nE '^\\s*run:.*\\.github/scripts/' .github/workflows/*.yml\n   ```\n\n2. **Run [actionlint](https://github.com/rhysd/actionlint) in CI.** Catches a lot of workflow mistakes (bad `uses:` refs, undefined outputs, shell errors). Won't catch this exact bug, but raises the floor cheaply.\n\n3. **End-to-end selftest must exercise the success path.** The autopilot-selftest comment says it's the canonical caller. If the Agent-commit step had been hit on a green run there, this would've blown up. Make sure the selftest fixture has at least one issue where agent + constraints both pass, so commit step actually executes.\n\n4. **Per-step act fixtures.** You already have `act-step-dispatch.sh` for parse-issue/choose-branch invariants. Add one for the agent-commit step that just verifies the action resolves and the script path exists \u2014 cheap, no docker needed.\n\n5. **`shellcheck` on the scripts themselves** \u2014 orthogonal but worth having; catches the inverse class (script bugs).\n\nThe single highest-leverage one is #1 \u2014 a grep in CI that bans `run: bash .github/scripts/` in workflow files. Want me to add it?"}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-26T09:30:59.325747", "event": "Notification", "source": "input", "data": {"session_id": "f3f66d06-7f92-4db6-97f8-5f5513c17dd2", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/f3f66d06-7f92-4db6-97f8-5f5513c17dd2.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "hook_event_name": "Notification", "message": "Claude is waiting for your input", "notification_type": "idle_prompt"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-26T09:37:27.432547", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "data": {"session_id": "f3f66d06-7f92-4db6-97f8-5f5513c17dd2", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/f3f66d06-7f92-4db6-97f8-5f5513c17dd2.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "list me reusable workflows where it shuld not exist, and where it should. And give short explanation why it can be used in one and can't in other"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-26T09:38:18.120698", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "f3f66d06-7f92-4db6-97f8-5f5513c17dd2", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/f3f66d06-7f92-4db6-97f8-5f5513c17dd2.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "The rule isn't \"reusable vs non-reusable\" \u2014 it's **whose checkout sits at `$GITHUB_WORKSPACE` when the `run:` executes.**\n\n## Where `bash .github/scripts/...` must NOT exist\n\nAll workflow files in `autopilot/.github/workflows/`:\n\n- `coding-agent.yml`\n- `check-constraints.yml`\n- `ensure-docker-image.yml`\n- `issue-trigger.yml`\n- `act-step-runner.yml` *(latent \u2014 see below)*\n\n**Why:** these are all `workflow_call` reusables. When a consumer invokes them, `actions/checkout` pulls the *consumer's* repo into `$GITHUB_WORKSPACE`. A `run:` step's working dir is that workspace, so `.github/scripts/foo.sh` resolves against the consumer's tree \u2014 which doesn't have autopilot's scripts. That's exactly the failure you just hit.\n\n## Where it CAN exist\n\nComposite actions in `autopilot/.github/actions/*/action.yml`:\n\n- `run-agent`, `check-constraints`, `ensure-docker-image`, `parse-issue`, `choose-branch`, `comment-agent-result`, `create-pr`\n\n**Why:** when a composite action runs, GitHub sets `$GITHUB_ACTION_PATH` to the directory containing that `action.yml` \u2014 i.e. the *autopilot* repo checkout fetched implicitly by the `uses:` resolver. So `bash \"$GITHUB_ACTION_PATH/../../scripts/foo.sh\"` finds autopilot's own scripts regardless of what's in `$GITHUB_WORKSPACE`. The two paths are independent.\n\n## The exception\n\n`act-step-runner.yml` line 32 still does `bash .github/scripts/test/act-step-dispatch.sh`. It works today only because autopilot's own CI is the only caller and `actions/checkout` happens to fetch autopilot. If anyone else `workflow_call`s it, it breaks the same way. Same fix applies \u2014 wrap the dispatch logic in a composite action, or document that this workflow is autopilot-internal only.\n\n## The guard\n\nSingle grep enforces the rule for the workflows directory:\n\n```bash\n! grep -nE '^\\s*run:.*\\.github/scripts/' .github/workflows/*.yml\n```\n\nComposite actions are exempt (they use `$GITHUB_ACTION_PATH`, which the regex doesn't match)."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
