{"timestamp": "2026-04-26T09:41:32.204472", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "f3f66d06-7f92-4db6-97f8-5f5513c17dd2", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/f3f66d06-7f92-4db6-97f8-5f5513c17dd2.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Yes \u2014 `act` accepts `-W <dir>` to point at any workflow directory, so the file isn't required to live under `.github/workflows/`.\n\nBenefits of moving it (e.g., to `.github/scripts/test/workflows/act-step-runner.yml`):\n\n- GitHub no longer registers it as a real reusable workflow. Right now it shows up in the Actions tab and is technically `workflow_call`-able by anyone with the right `uses:` ref \u2014 a latent footgun.\n- Frees it from the \"no `.github/scripts/` in workflows\" rule we just discussed, since GitHub never loads it.\n- Co-locates the test harness with its fixtures.\n\nTouchpoints to update:\n\n1. `.github/scripts/test/run-act-step-checks.sh` \u2014 pass `act -W <new-dir>` (or `cd` first).\n2. `.github/actionlint.yaml` line 2 \u2014 update the path key.\n3. `spec.k.json` constraint cmds at lines 139 and 151 \u2014 `F=$PROJECT_ROOT/<new-path>/act-step-runner.yml`.\n4. `spec.k.md` descriptions at lines 69, 72, 84, 87 \u2014 update the path string.\n\nPretty mechanical. Want me to do it?"}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
