{"timestamp": "2026-04-26T12:15:17.225807", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "7a1f01a6-1a9b-4c52-a425-29713aa330f7", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/7a1f01a6-1a9b-4c52-a425-29713aa330f7.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "`ensure-label` is skipped whenever `inputs.action != 'opened'`.\n\nIn practice that means it runs **only on the `issues.opened` event**. It is skipped for every other issue event the consumer wires up \u2014 most notably:\n\n- `issues.labeled` (the actual trigger path \u2014 `trigger` job runs instead)\n- `issues.unlabeled`, `edited`, `closed`, `reopened`, `assigned`, `transferred`, etc.\n- Any non-issue event the consumer might forward (e.g. `workflow_dispatch`-driven test calls).\n\nThe intent is one-shot label bootstrap: when an issue is first opened in a fresh repo, ensure the `agent-run` label exists so users have something to click. On every subsequent event the label already exists (or doesn't need to), so the job is a no-op and is gated out."}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-26T12:16:17.290048", "event": "Notification", "source": "input", "data": {"session_id": "7a1f01a6-1a9b-4c52-a425-29713aa330f7", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/7a1f01a6-1a9b-4c52-a425-29713aa330f7.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "hook_event_name": "Notification", "message": "Claude is waiting for your input", "notification_type": "idle_prompt"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-26T12:22:51.809885", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "data": {"session_id": "7a1f01a6-1a9b-4c52-a425-29713aa330f7", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/7a1f01a6-1a9b-4c52-a425-29713aa330f7.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "UserPromptSubmit", "prompt": "i think ensure image should split to 2 actions where 1 is when triggered on github hosted runner (on check-constraints), and 2 - when agent run. So we see comething like ensure-image-on-github-runner and ensure-image-on-self-hosted-runner but actually be more short and consice"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-26T12:24:03.397167", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "7a1f01a6-1a9b-4c52-a425-29713aa330f7", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/7a1f01a6-1a9b-4c52-a425-29713aa330f7.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Yes, the split is clean here because both callers already know their runner type statically:\n\n- `check-constraints.yml` \u2192 `runs-on: ubuntu-latest` (always hosted)\n- `coding-agent.yml`'s ensure step \u2192 `[self-hosted, $runner_label]` (always self-hosted)\n\nSo nothing actually exercises the `runner.environment` branch dynamically \u2014 that flexibility is unused.\n\n**What the split buys you**\n\n| | `ensure-image-hosted` | `ensure-image-local` |\n|---|---|---|\n| Pull path | actions/cache + `docker save`/`load` tarball, keyed by base digest | just `docker pull` (daemon caches) |\n| Build path | `docker/build-push-action` + GHA `cache-from/to type=gha` | `docker/build-push-action` (no cache args) |\n| Setup-buildx | required | required for build path only |\n| Steps | ~7 | ~4 |\n| Inputs | unchanged | drop `tag_prefix`'s \"GHA cache scope\" half of its dual purpose \u2014 now just a docker tag prefix |\n\nThe local action's input contract genuinely shrinks \u2014 `tag_prefix`'s GHA-cache-scope responsibility evaporates because there's no GHA cache. README halves.\n\n**Naming**\n\n`ensure-image-hosted` / `ensure-image-local` reads cleanest to me \u2014 short, the contrast is obvious, \"local\" is the runner-side terminology already used in the action's \"local tag\" / \"local layer cache\" prose. Alternatives I considered and rejected: `\u2026-gh`/`\u2026-sh` (cryptic), `\u2026-cached`/`\u2026-uncached` (misleading \u2014 both cache, just differently), `\u2026-on-github-runner` (your own dispreferred form).\n\n**Tradeoffs to weigh**\n\n1. The `ensure-docker-image` reusable workflow (`workflows/ensure-docker-image.yml`) currently picks self-hosted unconditionally (`runs-on: [self-hosted, $runner_label]`) and wraps the unified action. After the split it either (a) stays as a self-hosted-only wrapper around `ensure-image-local`, or (b) gets retired and callers invoke the action directly. (b) is cleaner.\n2. The `actionlint` / spec constraints reference `ensure-docker-image` by name \u2014 those need updating in lockstep (3-4 constraints touch this).\n3. If anyone ever wants check-constraints on self-hosted (faster, no GHA cache miss), they'd swap action names \u2014 slightly more friction than today's runtime auto-detection, but very cheap.\n\n**My take:** worth doing. The runtime `runner.environment` switch was speculative flexibility that no caller needed, and the local-side simplification (no buildx setup-action, no cache plumbing, no tarball dance) is real. Want me to do the split + caller updates + constraint renames in one pass?"}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
