{"timestamp": "2026-04-26T12:26:52.984564", "event": "Stop", "status": "allowed", "data": {"session_id": "7a1f01a6-1a9b-4c52-a425-29713aa330f7", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/7a1f01a6-1a9b-4c52-a425-29713aa330f7.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "Stop", "stop_hook_active": false, "last_assistant_message": "Audit done. **No verified constraints get invalidated**, provided we keep `workflows/ensure-docker-image.yml` as a thin wrapper.\n\n**Only one constraint touches the path:** `ensure_docker_image_uses_tag_prefix_not_tag` (workflow_hygiene, verified, locked). It asserts:\n```\n$PROJECT_ROOT/.github/workflows/ensure-docker-image.yml has input tag_prefix, not tag\n```\nIt targets the **workflow file**, not the composite action. So:\n\n- \u2705 If we keep `workflows/ensure-docker-image.yml` as a self-hosted wrapper around the new `ensure-image-local` action \u2192 constraint keeps passing. The `tag_prefix` input stays.\n- \u274c If we delete that workflow and have callers invoke composite actions directly \u2192 constraint fails forever (file gone), and it's locked-in-place. Stuck.\n\n**Recommended path** (preserves all constraints intact):\n1. Add `actions/ensure-image-hosted/` + `actions/ensure-image-local/`.\n2. `check-constraints.yml` switches its `uses:` from `actions/ensure-docker-image` \u2192 `actions/ensure-image-hosted`.\n3. `workflows/ensure-docker-image.yml` switches its `uses:` to `actions/ensure-image-local`. The workflow's name, file path, inputs, and outputs stay identical \u2014 it's just that its inner step calls the local-only action now. The `tag_prefix` input in the workflow stays, so the locked constraint stays green.\n4. Delete `actions/ensure-docker-image/`.\n\n**Description rot** (acceptable, not blocking):\n- `coding_agent_inputs_minimal` description mentions \"ensure-docker-image.yml\" \u2014 still accurate, the workflow keeps that name.\n- `ensure_docker_image_uses_tag_prefix_not_tag` description is still accurate.\n\n**Optional new constraints** (only if you want stricter coverage of the new split \u2014 none required):\n- One pinning `actions/ensure-image-hosted/action.yml` to require `tag_prefix` input.\n- One pinning `actions/ensure-image-local/action.yml` to require `tag_prefix` input.\n\nI'd skip those \u2014 marginal value, more surface to maintain. The workflow-level constraint already locks the public contract; the composite actions are internal.\n\nWant me to proceed with the split using the recommended path?"}, "vars": {"PROJECT_ROOT": "/workspace", "PLUGIN_ROOT": "/plugin", "WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/workspace"}}
