{"timestamp": "2026-04-26T12:30:10.472245", "event": "Write", "data": {"session_id": "7a1f01a6-1a9b-4c52-a425-29713aa330f7", "transcript_path": "/home/node/.claude/projects/-workspace/7a1f01a6-1a9b-4c52-a425-29713aa330f7.jsonl", "cwd": "/workspace", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "hook_event_name": "PreToolUse", "tool_name": "Write", "tool_input": {"file_path": "/workspace/autopilot/.github/actions/ensure-docker-image/action.yml", "content": "name: Ensure Docker Image\ndescription: |\n  Dispatcher: routes to ensure-image-hosted or ensure-image-local based on the\n  runner type. The two leaf actions have very different caching strategies\n  (GHA caches vs. daemon layer cache) and a unified action used to switch\n  internally; splitting cleaned that up. Inputs/outputs preserved for callers.\n\n  Prefer calling the leaf actions directly when the caller's runner type is\n  static (which is almost always). Use this dispatcher only when a single\n  caller may run on either runner type.\n\ninputs:\n  dockerfile:\n    description: Path to the Dockerfile, relative to $GITHUB_WORKSPACE. Leave empty to only pull+tag `base_image`.\n    required: false\n    default: \"\"\n  context:\n    description: Build context directory, relative to $GITHUB_WORKSPACE. Only used when `dockerfile` is set.\n    required: false\n    default: \".\"\n  build_args:\n    description: Newline-separated KEY=VALUE build args, forwarded to the builder.\n    required: false\n    default: \"\"\n  base_image:\n    description: Image reference to pull and tag locally, and the FROM contract for any Dockerfile.\n    required: true\n  tag_prefix:\n    description: REQUIRED. Project namespace. See ensure-image-hosted / ensure-image-local for details.\n    required: true\n\noutputs:\n  image:\n    description: Fully qualified local tag of the produced image.\n    value: ${{ steps.hosted.outputs.image || steps.local.outputs.image }}\n  cache_hit:\n    description: '\"true\" if the local tag pre-existed and neither build nor pull ran.'\n    value: ${{ steps.hosted.outputs.cache_hit || steps.local.outputs.cache_hit }}\n  digest:\n    description: Local image ID (sha256) of the produced image.\n    value: ${{ steps.hosted.outputs.digest || steps.local.outputs.digest }}\n\nruns:\n  using: composite\n  steps:\n    - id: hosted\n      if: runner.environment != 'self-hosted'\n      uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/actions/ensure-image-hosted@main\n      with:\n        dockerfile: ${{ inputs.dockerfile }}\n        context:    ${{ inputs.context }}\n        build_args: ${{ inputs.build_args }}\n        base_image: ${{ inputs.base_image }}\n        tag_prefix: ${{ inputs.tag_prefix }}\n\n    - id: local\n      if: runner.environment == 'self-hosted'\n      uses: Clockwork-Pilot/autopilot/.github/actions/ensure-image-local@main\n      with:\n        dockerfile: ${{ inputs.dockerfile }}\n        context:    ${{ inputs.context }}\n        build_args: ${{ inputs.build_args }}\n        base_image: ${{ inputs.base_image }}\n        tag_prefix: ${{ inputs.tag_prefix }}\n"}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_015RyghGbZxp44jFaq7HZocw"}}
